title: shrimp and sausage jambalaya
directions: Cut sausage into 1/2-inch pieces.
Salt shrimp; fry in hot oil quickly until brown.
Set aside.
Fry sausage until well browned; drain off fat.
Put shrimp back in pot.
Add minced vegetables and tomato sauce; heat until cooked down, stirring often.
Add rice; fry until brown.
Add water and spices.
Cover; simmer for 20 to 30 minutes, stirring only once, until rice is tender.

title: grandma's date bars
directions: Combine dates, water and sugar; cook over medium heat until thick.
Cream margarine or butter and brown sugar; add flour, soda and salt.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Add oats and mix until crumbly.
Pat 1/2 of crumb mixture in a 7 x 11-inch greased baking pan.
Spread with date mixture.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix ingredients well and serve with fresh fruit.

title: orange slice cookies(with shortening)
directions: Cut orange slices and nuts in small pieces.
Pour melted butter over brown sugar and cream.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat after each addition.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together. Add dry ingredients a little at a time.
Add vanilla, pecans and orange slices.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove from pan, cool and cut in squares.
Makes 2 dozen servings.

title: cream puff cake
directions: Put butter and water in pan.
Bring to boil over low heat; add flour all at once.
Stir until mixture leaves sides of pan. Remove from heat.
Add eggs all at once, beating thoroughly until smooth.
Place mixture in bottom of a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
While it is baking, check on it periodically and jab any air bubbles with a fork.

title: hawaiian pork chops
directions: Salt and pepper pork chops and bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a casserole dish.
Pour off fat.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over pork chops.
Continue baking until pork chops are done, approximately 30 minutes.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix well and make into small balls. Brown meatballs on all sides. Place in roaster and add about 1 gal. of cream of mushroom soup. Place in oven and heat until bubbly.

title: pepper relish
directions: Chop peppers and onions finely.
Mix together.
Combine all ingredients.
Cook 10 minutes.
Pour at once into sterilized jars and seal.

title: mud pies
directions: Blend dirt and water with hands in pan or dish.
Stir briskly until thick.
Gradually mix in sand.
Season with crushed leaves and shape into small pies.
Wash all pebbles and press in decorative patterns on top.
Bake in hot sun until crisp.
Cool in shade.
Serves 6.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well and drop on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until brown at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cut chicken in small pieces; layer.
Mix the soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Crumble crackers over pan.
Melt margarine; pour over crackers.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple coconut pecan cake
directions: Grease and lightly flour a 10-inch tube pan.
Into large mixing bowl, add shortening, butter and sugar.
Cream until light in color and very fluffy, about 10 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour; measure. Sift flour again with baking powder.
Add flour to creamed mixture along with milk.
Stir in undrained pineapple and vanilla.
Fold in coconut and pecans.
Pour into prepared pan.
Place in cold oven; turn oven to 325°.
Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until cake tests done.
Turn out immediately and pour glaze over cake while still hot.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Combine carrots, onion and pepper.
Mix all other ingredients; pour over vegetables.
Cover and marinate at least 12 hours.
Will keep a long time.
Leftover sauce can be re-used again and again.

title: family dinner
directions: Fry potatoes and drain off all grease.
Brown hamburger in another skillet, then drain.
Mix hamburger, potatoes and beef gravy.
Cut up some onion very fine as desired.
Cook this together very slowly for 10 to 15 minutes Serve while hot.

title: potato salad dressing for 10 pounds potatoes
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly with wire whisk.
Add to 10 pounds cubed, cooked and drained potatoes.
Use chopped celery to taste. Add onion to taste.
Add salt and white pepper to taste.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, syrup, salt, vanilla, melted butter and pecans.
Mix together well and put in uncooked pastry shell.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Check pie after 50 minutes.
If crust is getting too brown, cover with foil. Pecans rise to the top of the pie to form a crust on the top.

title: apple crunch
directions: Put in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan the sliced apples and 1 cup white sugar.
Sprinkle rest of ingredients, crumbled well over apples.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle nuts on top and bake 15 minutes more.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: In large bowl, combine flour, salt, sugar and shortening.
In small bowl, beat eggs and milk together.
Add the warm water to the yeast, then add the milk, eggs and the yeast mixture to the dry ingredients and work until the liquids are absorbed and the dough is no longer tacky.
Place in a greased bowl and slightly grease top of dough.
Let rise in warm place at least 1 hour. Punch down and at once, make into cinnamon rolls by rolling out dough.
Brush with oleo and sprinkle with cinnamon and brown sugar.
Roll and slice in greased pan.
Let rise 35 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Form into a ball and sprinkle with paprika.
Wrap in Saran Wrap.

title: no knead cinnamon rolls
directions: Measure the warm water, yeast and sugar into a bowl and let dissolve.
Stir in the salt, eggs, shortening and flour.
Mix until smooth and scrape sides of bowl. Cover and let rise 2 hours. Turn dough out onto lightly floured surface and roll into 12 x 8-inch pieces.

title: barbecue venison
directions: Trim meat; mix beer, onions, garlic, bay leaves, salt, pepper and 1 cup barbecue sauce.
Pour over meat (sauce should cover meat).
Marinate in refrigerator 12 to 24 hours, turning occasionally.
Remove meat and onions from marinade and place in crock-pot.
Pour 1 cup barbecue sauce over top; cover and cook on low 7 to 10 hours.
Enjoy!

title: soup kitchen cabbage
directions: Boil cabbage until tender, drain.
Mix mayonnaise and spices and fold into cabbage while still hot. Top with bacon pieces.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes and mash.
Add remaining ingredients and beat together.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Sprinkle grated Cheddar cheese over top just before baking.

title: brown rice
directions: Melt stick of butter in frypan.
Chop medium onion in pan. Add rice; fry until browned.
Put rice mixture in casserole dish, then pour beef consomme soup over it and stir.
Cover with tinfoil; cook about 1 hour.

title: copper penny salad
directions: Cook the carrots 15 minutes and drain.
Mix all ingredients together.
Chill well overnight.
Stir once in awhile.
It also can be served warm as a vegetable.

title: dill dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender. Blend at low speed. Refrigerate several hours for better flavor. Sprinkle with additional dill and serve with fresh vegetables.

title: alice kirkwood's zucchini squash casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Slice zucchini in chunks.
Cook for a few minutes in boiling, salted water.
Don't overcook! Drain squash; set aside.
Make a sauce combining the butter, Cheddar cheese, Gruyere cheese, sour cream, salt, chives and paprika.
Place the cooked squash in a 3-quart casserole dish.
Pour sauce over top. Sprinkle bread or cracker crumbs over entire dish and dot with butter.
Bake until brown and bubbles around the edges, approximately 30 to 35 minutes.

title: easy pink salad
directions: Open up cans; dump, mix and chill.
Can add nuts, if desired.

title: cream cheesies
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and vanilla in a bowl; add cream cheese. Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake in oven for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: candied yams
directions: Boil 6 yams for 20 minutes.
Peel, slice lengthwise and brown quickly in a little butter.
Put in baking dish.
Boil to thick syrup 2/3 cup sugar and 1 cup water.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake in preheated moderate oven (375°) for 25 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Mix soup with milk and onion.
Alternate layers of macaroni, corned beef and cheese.
Pour soup mixture over each layer.
Top with crumbs and almonds.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: "plains special" cheese ring
directions: Mix; mold with hands into desired shape.
(We mold into a ring.)
Place in refrigerator until chilled.
To serve, fill center with strawberry preserves.
Can be served as a complement to a main meal or as an hors d'oeuvre with crackers.

title: asheville salad
directions: Bring soup to boiling point and add gelatin that has been dissolved in cold water.
Pour hot mixture over mashed cream cheese.
Add onions, celery, and pepper.
Mix together well.
Add mayonnaise and mix again.
Chill.
Serves 12.

title: eggplant parmigiana
directions: Wash and trim eggplant; cut in 1/2-inch slices.
Combine crumbs and 1/4 cup cheese.
Spread mayonnaise thinly on both sides of eggplant slices coating both sides.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Repeat with remaining slices.
Bake in 425° oven about 15 minutes until browned.
Lower temperature to 375°.
Grease 11 3/4 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish.
Arrange eggplant slices slightly overlapping.
Spread each slice with small amount of sauce; cover with Mozzarella.
Sprinkle half of Parmesan over; spoon remaining tomato sauce over.
Sprinkle with rest of Parmesan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Grind cranberries and oranges with skin (remove seeds), apples, lemon (remove seeds).
Add sugar.
Refrigerate after mixing for several hours.

title: german crumb cake
directions: Mix brown sugar with sifted dry ingredients.
Cut in butter. Reserve 1/2 cup of mixture to sprinkle over cake.
To remainder, add beaten egg with sour milk or buttermilk.
Pour into small pan and sprinkle crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pumpkin-molasses cake
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, brown sugar, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and ginger. Add buttermilk, shortening, pumpkin, molasses and orange peel.
Beat with an electric mixer on low to medium speed until combined.
Beat on high speed for 2 minutes. Add eggs and beat 2 minutes more.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean. Serves 12.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all together and serve cold.

title: butter flake rolls
directions: Combine 1 c. flour, 1 tbsp sugar, dry yeast, and warm water; mix well. Cover, let rise until light and bubbly 20 to 30 minutes. Combine butter, sugar, salt, and eggs; beat until well-blended. Add yeast mixture. Gradually add flour for a stiff dough. Knead on floured surface about 30 strokes. Cover; let rise until double in size. Punch down and divide in half. Roll out each half on floured surface to an 8x12 in.
Cut in 3 in. strips. Roll each strip in melted butter. Coil each. Let rise until double in size.
Bake at 375° for 12-15 min.

title: nothings
directions: Beat egg white until stiff; add sugar and vanilla.
Fold in pecans and place on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes.
Cut oven off and leave for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry shortcake trifle
directions: Reserve 3 or 4 berries for garnish; hull and slice 1 cup of the remaining berries.
Arrange along the side of a clear, straight-sided, 1 1/2-quart bowl or dish.
Place remaining berries in blender container or food processor bowl; add sugar.
Cover and blend or process until pureed.
In a mixer bowl, beat pudding and cream cheese with an electric mixer on medium speed until combined.
Place half of the cake in the bottom of the dish.
Pour half of the pureed berries over cake and top with half of the pudding mixture.
Repeat.
Cover and chill for up to 24 hours. Before serving, top with reserved strawberries. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco, sugar and add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour, baking powder, cocoa and add to the other mixture alternately with milk.
Bake in tube pan at 250° for 2 hours, or until done.

title: toasted butter pecan cake
directions: Toast pecans in 1/4 cup butter in oven for 20 to 25 minutes. Stir frequently.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Cream 1 cup butter; gradually add sugar, creaming well.
Blend in eggs; beat well after each.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Blend well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla and 1/3 cup pecans.

title: vinegar dumplings
directions: Put ingredients in saucepan over medium heat.
Stir until it starts to boil.
Set aside.
Make a biscuit dough.
Roll out and cut into small pieces.
Put sauce in a deep glass baking dish. Put biscuit dough in sauce.
Sprinkle sugar and nutmeg over top. Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: low calorie italian salad
directions: Cut all vegetables into bite size pieces.
Use as much of each as needed.
Mix together and add olives.
Add dressing; mix well. Chill as many hours as you can before hand.
Best if made a day ahead; gives the vegetables time to absorb the dressing.

title: blueberry buckle coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all cake ingredients together in order given.
Pour batter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle topping on batter.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes.

title: artichoke chicken
directions: Layer chicken in a 6 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Saute mushrooms in frying pan with olive oil.
When tender, layer on top of chicken.
Drain artichoke hearts; layer on top of chicken (reserve liquid from 1 can).
Mix mayonnaise, cheese and artichoke liquid; layer on chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: never fail applesauce cake
directions: Sift flour, salt and spices together.
Add raisins and nut meats.
Set aside.

title: orange apricot salad
directions: Cook until thick and when this is cool, spread over chilled salad and return to refrigerator until set.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: spinach dumplings
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients and 3/4 cup of flour on waxed paper.
Measure 2 tablespoons of flour and with floured hands, shape spinach mix into 1-inch balls.
Gently roll balls in 2 tablespoons of flour to coat.
Heat 4 to 5 quarts of water to boiling and carefully add spinach balls, 1/2 at a time, to water. Cook 10 minutes or until slightly puffed.
Remove and drain.

title: s'mores
directions: Beat margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add flour and crumbs.
Mix well.
Press into bottom of greased 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool before serving.

title: easy cookies
directions: Mix sour cream and cake mix; add nuts and chips.
Drop by tablespoons on greased cookie sheet (use Pam).
Cook 8-10 minutes at 350.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Work Crisco into flour until texture of corn meal.
Add water; stir with a fork and then, very lightly, work with hands, like for pie dough.
Peel and core apples.
Put a pat of oleo in core hole. Pinch off a piece of dough and roll out into a square large enough to cover apple.
Put apple on top; sprinkle with sugars and cinnamon.
Then, corner to corner, pinch together and seal.
Place on a cookie sheet.
Repeat with remaining dough.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° for 45 minutes.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over rolled oats, cover and let stand 20 minutes.
Beat butter and sugars until fluffy.
Blend in vanilla and eggs.
Add oat mixture and mix well.
Sift together flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add to cream mixture.
Bake in well-greased and floured pan.
Coconut and nuts may be added, if you wish.

title: cold vegetable salad
directions: You will need a bowl with sealing lid.

title: funnel cake
directions: Sift together the flour, salt, soda, sugar and baking powder. Mix egg and milk together. Add to dry ingredients.
Beat until smooth.

title: no bake pecan roll
directions: Place crushed graham crackers into a large bowl.
Cut marshmallows into small pieces.
Cut dates as marshmallows.
Add pecans and stir well.
Add milk. Make into a roll on wax paper. Let chill about an hour before cutting.

title: cool summer salad
directions: Fold all ingredients together and chill.
May substitute fresh strawberries, unsweetened.

title: layered grinder sandwich loaf
directions: Lightly grease 9 x 13-inch pan (margarine or butter).
Roll out 1 package crescent rolls into rectangle.
Spread out in pan.
Begin layering ham, salami, Provolone cheese and 1/2 the peppers.
Beat eggs and grated cheese together.
Pour less than 1/2 egg mixture over pan.
Layer again and pour most of remaining mixture over top. Save a little to moisten top.

title: pumpkin custard cake
directions: Mix the cake mix, water and 3 eggs.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix pumpkin pie mix; add 2 eggs and a little salt.
Beat together. Spread over batter until smooth. Take boiling water and pour over top here and there.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with whip cream.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Put cherry pie filling on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the cake mix, melted butter and nuts; spread on top of pie filling. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: egg bake
directions: Layer the meat, bread and cheese.
Mix eggs, milk, mustard, salt and pepper.
Pour over layers.

title: bakery style andrew cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine flour, sugar and powder.
Mix in butter, shortening and egg white.
Add vanilla.
Mix well. Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Decorate with desired topping (listed above).
Bake 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes about 2 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine with whisk first 5 ingredients in large mixing bowl. Combine remaining ingredients.
Add to dry ingredients.
Stir with whisk until well blended.
Spoon mixture into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool loaves in pans 10 minutes, then remove and let cool on wire racks.

title: lima bean mushroom casserole
directions: Cook frozen lima beans as directed; drain.
Blend in mushroom soup and pimientos.
Place in casserole dish.
Pour melted butter or margarine over mixture; top with cracker crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 25 minutes.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix ingredients with a fork.
Shape into 1-inch
ball.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until done by checking the center.
These appetizers may be frozen.
Thaw slightly before baking, and increase cooking time. Makes 40 to 50 balls.

title: keebler soft batch chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Cream butter, eggs, molasses, vanilla and water in medium size bowl.
In a large bowl, sift together the sugars, baking powder, baking soda, salt and flour. Combine the moist mixture and the dry mixture.
Add the chips. Shape the dough into 1-inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet, placing them 1 inch apart.
Bake for 8 minutes or until brown around the edges.
Do not exceed cooking time.
Sugar continues to bake cookies.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: apple-walnut muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 12 muffin cups and set aside. Sift together the flour, baking powder, baking soda, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt.
Set aside.
Combine brown sugar, eggs, buttermilk and melted butter.
Beat on medium speed until the mixture is smooth.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain and set aside.

title: spinach-mushroom lasagna
directions: In a heavy saucepan over medium heat, combine tomatoes, mushrooms, red bell pepper, carrot, onion, red wine, garlic, honey, basil, rosemary, oregano, thyme and black pepper.
When mixture begins to boil, reduce heat and simmer for about 20 minutes.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix Ricotta and egg whites; set aside.
Assemble the lasagna in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place a layer of sauce in the pan and cover the sauce with a layer of cooked noodles.
Spread the Ricotta-egg mixture over the noodles; cover with the spinach.
Add another layer of noodles and another layer of sauce and then the grated cheese.
Bake for 35 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before cutting.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fruit nut bars
directions: Melt butter.
Add brown sugar and eggs.
Beat until smooth. Add sifted flour and vanilla.
Pour mixture over well lined pan of nuts.
Place diced fruit on top.
Pan should be approximately 9 x 11 1/2-inches.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.
These are a family favorite at Christmastime.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cream butter and sugar and add remaining ingredients.
Divide and pack into 2 pans.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix chicken, vegetables and potatoes together.
Mix cream of chicken soup with 1 cup of hot broth.
Pour over chicken mixture and stir.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch greased Pyrex dish.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Pound chicken breasts with mallet until 1/4-inch thick.
Place 1 slice ham and 1 slice cheese on each.
Tuck in sides and roll up jelly-roll fashion.
Skewer with 2 toothpicks; set aside.
Melt butter in microwave in 9 x 13-inch microwave dish.
Microwave breasts in melted butter on High for 3 minutes, uncovered.
Turn chicken over so seam side is down and microwave on High for 3 minutes.

title: toasted pecans
directions: Mix butter, Bitters and salt in 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Stir in pecans.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: lynchburg lemonade
directions: Pour into large pitcher.
Add ice and stir.
Garnish with lemon slices and cherries.

title: king's arms tavern sweet potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cook potatoes in boiling, salted water until done.
Peel and mash. Stir in all remaining ingredients except 2 tablespoons sugar. Turn into casserole dish and sprinkle with remaining sugar.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: leftover cracked conch cutlet salad
directions: Mix ingredients and serve cold.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: In a bowl, mix oatmeal and orange juice. Combine remaining ingredients, mixing blueberries in last.
Place in cupcake tins lined with cupcake papers. Fill 3/4 full of dough.
In a bowl, mix 1 cup sugar, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and 1/2 chopped nuts.
Sprinkle top of each muffin with about 1 teaspoon of mixture. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: baked chicken
directions: Wash and dry chicken.
Rub all over with salt and pepper.
Put celery and onion in the cavity; cover and bake at 325° for 2 hours. Uncover and bake at 400° for 15 minutes to brown chicken.
Chicken is done when the leg bone moves easily.
Transfer all stock in the bottom of the dish to a saucepan and add 1 to 1 1/2 cups water. Add the onion and celery from the cavity and mix well.

title: chicken divan
directions: Arrange drained broccoli in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Drizzle with melted margarine and top with cooked chicken (Broken into large chunks).
Mix soup, mayonnaise; add lemon juice and salt and pepper.
Pour sauce over top of chicken.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: spice cake in a jar
directions: Cream
shortening
and
sugar, add applesauce, eggs and water. Mix well.
Mix dry ingredients in another bowl and add to first mixture.
Add
nuts (or raisins or both).
Spray wide mouth pint jar
with
Pam
and
fill
1/2 full.
Place jars on cookie sheet. Cook at 350° exactly 45 minutes.
Remove jars 1 at a time and quickly screw lids on one at a time.
Makes 6 to 8 jars.
Great for small gifts around the holidays.
This cake has the shelf life
of
one year because it has been properly sealed in a canning jar.

title: aunt ida's lemon glazed cake
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Sift together the flour and baking powder.
Add to the creamed mixture alternately with the milk and extract.
Do not beat.
Stir well. Fold in the beaten egg whites.
Divide batter to make 5 (9-inch) layers. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: hint of honey loaves(makes 4 loaves)
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Pour milk over shortening, honey and salt; cool to lukewarm.
Stir in 2 cups flour.
Add dissolved yeast and oats; mix well.
Stir in enough additional flour to make soft dough.
Turn out onto lightly floured surface; knead 8 to 10 minutes or until smooth and elastic.
Shape to form ball.
Place in greased large bowl, turning once to coat surface of dough. Cover; let rise in warm place about 1 hour or until double in half; roll out each half to form a 15 x 9-inch rectangle.
Roll up, starting with narrow ends; press together ends and seam to seal.
Place in 2 greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Brush lightly with melted butter.
Cover; let rise about 45 minutes or until nearly double in size.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for about 45 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool on wire rack.

title: pecan squash
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine nuts and syrup and pour over squash.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix cream cheese, olives and onions.
Spread on tortillas. Add ham.
Roll up tightly (like a jelly roll).
Cover with wax paper.
Chill for a few hours or overnight.
Cut in 1/2-inch bite-size pieces.
Dip in picante sauce, if desired.

title: snowballs
directions: Mix all ingredients. Form balls and bake at 350° for about 10 minutes. Roll in powdered sugar while hot; when cool, roll in powdered sugar again.

title: barbecued franks
directions: Saute the sliced onion in the butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Split 8 hot dogs in half lengthwise; add to sauce. Simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve with mashed potatoes and vegetables.

title: sausage gravy
directions: Brown sausage, using Dutch oven.
Add enough milk to cover sausage or desired gravy amount.
Heat milk and sausage until hot, then add flour and water mixture.
Cook, until thickened.
Serve over home-fried potatoes, mashed potatoes or toast.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Bring to boil and cool.
Pour over pickles 1/4-inch thick, about 1 gallon.
You can add pickles to liquid.

title: german sweet chocolate cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding mix, chocolate, eggs, buttermilk and oil in large mixer bowl.
Blend, then beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 8 or 9-inch layer pans. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean and cake pulls away from sides of pans.
Do not overbake.
Cool in pans about 15 minutes.
Remove from pans and finish cooling on racks.
Fill and frost with Coconut-Pecan Filling.

title: jelly roll
directions: Beat
eggs and sugar until creamy.
Add dry ingredients and vanilla.
Beat.
Then
add
boiling
water while beating. Pour onto
wax paper lined cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Turn
pan over onto dish towel.
Cool and remove wax paper. Spread jelly over top.
Roll up and leave in towel for 10 minutes. Slice.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix lemon juice and condensed milk and stir until thickened. Fold in Cool Whip, pineapple and pecans.
Pour into pie shells. Cool in refrigerator and serve.
Makes 2 Million Dollar pies.

title: salmon yule log
directions: Debone drained salmon and bake in oven in shallow pan for 25 to 30 minutes.
Mix first 8 ingredients.
Roll on waxed paper to form log.
Refrigerate several hours to firm the roll, then roll log into parsley and nut mix.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package; drain.
Add next six ingredients; mix well.
Place in baking dish and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: drop doughnuts
directions: Sift together flour, salt, baking powder, nutmeg and cinnamon. Combine sugar, egg, milk and shortening.
Mix well together until smooth and drop from teaspoon into hot grease or oil.

title: chocolate muffins
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine together.
Mix eggs, sugar and flour well.
Add to chocolate mixture.
Line miniature muffin tins with paper cups.
Fill 2/3 full. Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes. Sprinkle tops with powdered sugar.
Yields 36 miniature muffins or 18 large muffins.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Mix all ingredients in large soup kettle.
Cook and stir to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Stir often.

title: taffy-apple salad
directions: Cook juice, sugar, flour and egg until thick like applesauce. Cool.

title: green apple cake
directions: Dump all into a mixing bowl; beat at low speed for 1 minute. Bake in ungreased loaf pan or 6 x 10 x 2-inch pan.

title: sausage gravy
directions: In large skillet, crumble sausage into small pieces and brown lightly.
Remove sausage and drain off all but 4 tablespoons of the drippings.
To the drippings in the skillet, stir in the flour.
Keep stirring until mixture is smooth and simmers. Continue simmering to brown flour (do not scorch).
Add milk, a little at a time, stirring constantly, until mixture is desired thickness for gravy.
Add sausage.
Split hot biscuits; place on serving plate.
Pour gravy over top.
Makes 4 servings.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Cook corn bread.
Crumble it into small pieces into a very large bowl.
Let cool.
Add other ingredients.
Mix with broth until desired consistency.

title: sour cream dinner rolls
directions: Scald
cream
and margarine until melted; cool.
Measure warm water
into large bowl; add yeast;	stir.
Add eggs, then add
dry ingredients.
Mixture will be a batter. Cover tightly; refrigerate overnight.
Take
out and shape into rolls 2 hours before baking.
Let
rise	until double in bulk (dough will be stiff; do not knead).
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: working woman's rolls
directions: Mix ingredients.
Grease muffin pans and fill 1/2 full.
Bake at 400° approximately 15 minutes.
Makes 16 rolls.
Serve hot.

title: velveeta salad
directions: Combine sugar, flour, liquid, eggs, vinegar and margarine. Cook on low heat, stirring until thickened.
Let cool.
Combine pineapple, pecans, cheese and marshmallows.
Add sauce and stir to coat.
Chill.

title: steak burgers
directions: Melt butter and add onions, cooking until tender.
Add steak. Add chicken soup and all other ingredients and simmer 30 minutes. Serve on hot buns.

title: pineapple supreme pie
directions: Mix pineapple and pudding, adding sour cream.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into pie shells.
Let chill.
Good for summer, easy and quick.

title: peanut butter icing
directions: Put on stove and melt butter.
Add sugar.
When mixed good, add cream from a can.
Let cook 2 or 3 minutes.
Take off stove. Add peanut butter and powdered sugar.
Beat until creamy or consistency to spread.

title: tex-mex potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Put potatoes and chicken broth in blender.
Puree.
Saute onion and peppers in butter until soft (10 minutes).
Add ham and chilies.
Saute 1 minute.
Put potato mixture in saucepan and add sauteed vegetables.
Heat.
Slowly add half and half and heat.
Do not boil.
May serve with sprinkle of grated Cheddar cheese.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease pan with butter.
Peel and core apples.
Slice thin and put in pan.
Sprinkle cinnamon over apples.
Mix sugar, flour, salt and butter with fork until crumbly.
Put mixture over apples.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: cheeseburger soup
directions: In large saucepan combine the first seven ingredients, bring to boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 15 - 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Stir in beef and 2 cups milk, heat thoroughly.
Combine flour and remaining
milk until smooth. Gradually stir into soup.
Bring to boil.
Cook and stir for two minutes or until thickened.
Reduce heat.
Add cheese until melted.
Add pepper (optional).
Top with bacon just before serving.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour pie filling in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Drain pineapple and place on top of cherry filling.
Spoon entire cake mix over pineapple.
Cut margarine into small pats and place over cake mix. Spread nuts on top.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: kiffles
directions: Cream margarine and cream cheese together.
Sift flour with salt, sugar and baking powder.
Blend dry ingredients thoroughly with cheese mixture.
Add beaten eggs; stir until blended.
Chill in refrigerator for 1/2 hour.
Pat or roll out with floured biscuit cutter.
Place 1/2 teaspoon of desired jam or other filling in center of each round.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 15 minutes.
Can be dusted with powdered sugar.

title: beets
directions: Add sugar, cornstarch, vinegar and water together in a saucepan.
Boil for 10 minutes.
Add drained beets.
Cover and let sit for 30 minutes.
Before serving, add butter and just bring to a boil.

title: sadie's persimmon pudding
directions: Mix pulp, sugar, eggs and flour with soda, salt and spices. Using mixer, stir in milk and melted butter.
Add vanilla.
Put mixture in greased baking dish.
Suggested temperature is 350°. We have found 325° is more desirable.
Bake 1 hour approximately. Pick persimmons after first frost when they get soft.
Wash and mash to make pulp.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together and place in a casserole. Top with cornflakes.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: overnight lettuce salad
directions: Layer first 6 ingredients.
Spread mayo over top.
Sprinkle over mayo the Cheddar cheese and bacon.
Cover tightly and refrigerate at least 24 hours. Toss before serving.

title: cracklin' cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together the flour, salt, baking powder and sugar.
Combine with the cornmeal.
Add the milk and egg and mix well.
Add the cracklings and blend thoroughly.
Turn into a greased 9-inch square baking pan and bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pork chops supreme
directions: Season chops with salt and pepper.
Brown chops in oil. Arrange potatoes in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Place chops on top. Mix together soup, milk and onion and pour over chops.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake until cheese melts.

title: holiday soup
directions: Wash beans.
Place in large kettle.
Cover with water 2 inches above bean line.
Add 2 teaspoons salt; soak overnight.
Drain. Add 2 quarts water, ham hocks; bring to a boil.
Add onion, tomatoes, chili powder and juice.
Pepper to taste.
Simmer 3 hours.
Remove ham from hock before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed and put chocolate chips on top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: steak kebabs
directions: In a shallow glass dish, combine soy sauce, honey, ginger, garlic, lemon peel and red pepper.
Mix well.
Add beef; stir to coat.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for 1 to 2 hours. Preheat broiler.
Remove beef from marinade and discard marinade. Using 4 (10-inch) metal skewers, alternately thread beef, tomato, mushrooms and pepper.
Place on broiler pan.
Broil 2-inches from heat, turning 2 or 3 times, until meat is medium-rare and vegetables are lightly brown, about 10 minutes.
Makes 4 kebabs.

title: pancit
directions: Saute garlic in cooking oil; add onions, pork, shrimp, carrots and cabbage.
Season with soy sauce and fry for 2 minutes.
Add broth and simmer; add celery.
When vegetables are cooked, mix in soaked and drained rice sticks and season with salt.
Garnish with spring onions.
Serve with lemon.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie shell. Sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish.
Make a batter of milk and flour.
Mix all other ingredients together and put in dish.
Pour batter over the top.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: peanut butter muffins
directions: Cream together first four ingredients.
Combine egg and milk. Sift flour with baking powder and add wheat germ.
Add the liquid mixture and the dry mixture alternately to the creamed mixture. Stir just until moistened. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cool-rise french bread
directions: Measure flour; set aside.
Combine 2 cups flour, undissolved dry yeast, sugar and salt in a large bowl.
Blend well.
Add softened oleo.
Add hot water all at once.
Beat with mixer, on medium speed, for 2 minutes; scrape bowl occasionally.
Add 1 cup more flour.
Beat on high for 1 minute or until thick and elastic. Using a wooden spoon, gradually stir in just enough flour to make a soft dough that leaves sides of bowl.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine sugar, margarine, pumpkin, vanilla and egg; blend well.
Stir in flour, baking powder, spice and salt, blending well.
Stir in nuts.

title: snap doodle breakfast bread
directions: Mix together. Pour into 13x9 pan, makes a thin layer. Then sprinkle heavily with cinnamon and brown sugar. Next dot heavily with butter or margarine. Bake at 350° for 30 min.

title: pizza sauce
directions: Cook first 7 ingredients for 1/2 hour.
Make a paste with clear jell and water.
After thickening, add Velveeta cheese, butter and brown sugar.
Put into jars and hot water bath for 10 minutes.

title: mostaccioli and sausage bake
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
In 2-quart baking dish, combine sausage, sauce, noodles and half the Mozzarella cheese; mix well. Top with remaining Mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: no fat heavenly delight(for the sweet-aholic on a diet.)
directions: Add the Marshmallow Creme sauce to the popcorn cake, then eat and enjoy.

title: sausage bread
directions: Brown sausage and drain the fat away.
Mix the sausage with two beaten eggs.
Roll out the bread dough in flour, 3/8-inch thick.
Cover the dough with the sausage mix; leave an inch of dough uncovered at each end.
Mix together the Mozzarella, Parmesan, basil, parsley and garlic salt in a bowl, then cover the sausage mix on the dough with the cheese spice mix.
Roll up into a bread; pinch the ends.
Baste with a lightly beaten egg and bake 45 minutes at 325°.
Cool 5 minutes before cutting.
Enjoy!

title: almond roca
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil.
Spread saltine crackers in a single layer in a 12 x 18-inch bar pan.
Set aside.
Melt 1 cup butter and 1 cup sugar in saucepan and boil 3 minutes, stirring constantly to avoid scorching.
Pour mixture over crackers and bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Spread chocolate chips on top of the cracker surface and let melt. Spread out the chocolate over entire surface and then top with nuts.
Refrigerate.
Bread into pieces once candy has hardened.
Store in a covered container.
Candy may be frozen for later use.

title: tamaulipas tamales
directions: Soak corn shucks in warm water 1 day before using.
Soak in warm water again before using.
Work shortening, chili powder and salt into masa.
Add water and knead with hands until smooth. Using back of spoon, spread mixture thinly and evenly on inside of shuck, covering about half of shuck.
Fill with following mixture.

title: cranberry cream salad
directions: Dissolve jello, sugar and water together.
Add cranberry sauce and chill until thick.
Add celery, nuts and sour cream; mix.
Chill in 8-inch square pan until firm.

title: grilled flank steak
directions: Cover steaks in fajita marinade the night before; cover container.

title: simple southern fried chicken
directions: Sprinkle the chicken generously with salt and pepper.
Dip each piece into the buttermilk and then coat it with the flour. Place the chicken on a rack until the coating is set.
Heat about an inch of oil in a heavy skillet or electric skillet to 375 degrees. Place as many pieces of chicken in the pan as you can without crowding.
Lightly brown the chicken on both sides. Reduce the temperature to 275 degrees. Cook, covered, for about 15 minutes, turning once during this time.
Uncover and raise the temperature to 375 degrees.
Continue frying until the chicken is crispy and well browned.
Drain well on absorbent paper. Serves 4.

title: banana oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift together first six ingredients. Add egg and mashed bananas. Beat well. Add oatmeal and nuts. Stir to mix well. Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Mix in dish.
Cover with foil and freeze.
When ready to bake, cover with Ritz cracker crumbs and grated cheese.
Melt 1 stick of margarine and pour over top.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes until bubbly at 350°.

title: peanut butter sour cream cake
directions: Sift the first 5 ingredients together.
Mix remaining ingredients in large bowl of electric mixer.
Beat on cream cycle until smooth and light.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix until well blended and smooth.
Pour into 3 well-greased small loaf pans. Bake at 350° until cake breaks from side or toothpick comes out clean 50 to 60 minutes for large cake or 40 to 50 minutes for small cakes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large mixing bowl. Refrigerate for 24 hours, covered.
Bake in greased 9 x 12-inch pan for 1 hour, uncovered, or until lightly browned.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add baking soda to applesauce.
Add applesauce to butter mixture.
Blend well.
Stir together flour and spices; add to first mixture.
Add raisins and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook celery, onion and green pepper for 15 minutes.
Mix together sour cream, cream of celery soup and salt and pepper to taste.
Layer green beans, corn, celery, onion, salt and pepper in a casserole dish.
Spread sour cream and soup mixture on top of vegetables.
Sprinkle sharp cheese on top of soup mixture.
Mix together crackers, almonds and butter.
Spread on top of casserole and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: cranberry pie
directions: Drain juices from oranges and pineapple.
Bring 7-Up and water to a boil in microwave.
Dissolve in Jell-O.
Stir cranberry sauce; add oranges, pineapple and pecans.
Place in a square pan and leave in fridge overnight.

title: granny minor's favorite persimmon pudding
directions: Make sure that persimmons have been collected after the 1st frost to assure that they will be sweet not bitter.
Add soda and sugar to persimmon pulp and beat well.
Add milk and beaten eggs and stir in thoroughly.
Add sifted flour and beat until smooth. Add butter (melted but not hot) and stir in well.
Pour into a greased and floured baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until firm and lightly brown.
Cut into squares and serve hot or cold.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Cover with
vinegar
and stir, then heat until hot, but not boiling.
Place in jars and seal while hot.

title: fluffy fruit dip
directions: Mix well.
Serve with bananas, grapes, pineapple, strawberries, cantaloupe, honeydew, watermelon, etc.

title: pineapple souffle
directions: Melt oleo; cool. Beat eggs in well and add sugar, milk and salt. Drain pineapple juice before adding pineapple to the mixture. Add bread (cubed) and mix gently. Pour into casserole dish; bake 30 minutes at 350°. Great as side dish or dessert.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water to cover for 30 minutes, or until tender.
Drain; let cool to touch.
Peel and cut into 1/4-inch strips; set aside.

title: excellent play dough
directions: Stir water, salt and alum until dissolved.
Add oil and food coloring.
Knead well and add enough flour to make consistency desired.
Keeps several months in a closed container.

title: baked acorn squash
directions: Cut squash and remove seeds.
Make a paste of butter, brown sugar, salt and pepper.
Spread in cavity.
Put squash back together.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: squash pie
directions: Cook squash with salt and a little water.
Put 1/2 in a dish and
the other 1/2 in another dish.
Drain the squash and add to 1
dish,
the chopped onion, sour cream, a little milk and beaten eggs.
Put	in an
unbaked	pie crust and then add other
drained squash.
Bake
at
for
approximately 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients until blended.
Grease and flour 4 loaf pans.
Fill each half full.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Remove from pans to cool on rack.
Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate or freeze.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix well.
Place in a casserole dish and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Cream together cheese and Miracle Whip.
Add onion, salt, shrimp and unwhipped cream.

title: heath candy bar cake
directions: Leave Heath bars in wrapper, put in freezer overnight.
Break up with hammer.
Mix brown sugar and flour.
Cut in butter with pastry blender.
Hold out 1 cup of mixture.
To remainder add soda, salt, egg and milk.
Beat and pour into 13x9-inch pan.
Sprinkle on top the reserved cup of crumb mixture and broken up Heath bars. Bake at 350° about 25 minutes.

title: date nut loaf candy
directions: You also need 1 linen tea towel.

title: pineapple nut bread
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Set aside.
Beat egg. Add oleo and vanilla. Dissolve soda in pineapple.
Add egg mixture. Add dry ingredients and stir just enough to moisten. Add raisins and pecans. Spoon batter into a greased 8 1/2 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until done.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: chocolate drops
directions: Boil mixture 5 minutes.
Add oatmeal, coconut and nuts.
Stir. Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Cool before serving.

title: all-bran pie crust
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Press into pan sprayed with Pam. Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Allow to cool.
Serves 8.

title: white fudge
directions: Combine the milk, water, sugar, salt and butter.
Mix thoroughly in a 3 qt. saucepan.
Heat to the boiling point over med. heat.
Cook to softball stage - 236 F., stirring constantly. A full rolling boil should be maintained throughout.
Remove from the heat and cool at room temperature without stirring, until lukewarm (110°).
Add the vanilla, beat until mixture snaps and holds its shape.
Add the marshmallow creme and fruit, if desired. Beat again until mixture loses it's gloss and is very stiff. Quickly spread into 8 in. square buttered pan.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
In separate bowl, combine beaten eggs and vanilla.
Add pumpkin and mix well.
Add dry ingredients, carrots and raisins.
Spray muffin tin with Pam.
Divide dough into 12.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: fudge easter eggs
directions: Melt
chocolate chips.	Stir in milk and vanilla.
Stir until it	starts to thicken.
Drop and form into eggs after it cools
a little.
Drop on a greased cookie sheet.
Refrigerate until cold. Coat with melted chocolate chips.

title: barbecued sauerkraut
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together.
Add brown sugar and sauerkraut.
Mix.
Add V-8 juice and mix.
Place in baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: coconut balls
directions: Mix together the butter, pecans, milk, sugar and coconut and chill several hours.
Roll into balls.
Melt in top of double boiler the chocolate chips and paraffin.
Dip coconut balls in chocolate mixture with toothpick.
Cool on wire rack or wax paper.

title: mint glazed carrots
directions: Combine first four ingredients in a skillet.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally.
Add hot cooked carrots and spoon the syrup over them until glazed.
Mint jelly may be used in place of sugar and mint leaves.

title: steamed stuffed fish(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Brush fish with oil outside and inside.
Mix all remaining ingredients and stuff pocket of fish.
Prepare heavy-duty foil to make large double piece.
Place fish on foil and wrap tightly so steam does not escape.
Cook over charcoal or gas grill for 15 minutes.
Turn over and cook 15 additional minutes.

title: french toast supreme
directions: Cut bread in half horizontally.
From cut side, cut in 1-inch slices, almost to crust but not through.
Place both halves, cut side up in ungreased 13 x 9-inch dish.
Beat eggs.
Add orange juice, peel, milk and margarine.
Spoon over cut surfaces of bread.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Using a pancake turner, carefully turn basted bread so cut side is down.
Mix cinnamon and brown sugar.
Sprinkle over coated bread.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Place rice in greased casserole dish. Add chicken. Mix together onion soup mix, mushroom soup and water. Pour over chicken. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: hummus(dip)
directions: *Sold at Lebanese store at 155 Northampton Street.

title: banana-nut bread
directions: Blend the first 5 ingredients.
Mix in the chopped nuts. Combine remaining ingredients and blend thoroughly.
Add all at once to dry mixture, stirring only enough to moisten dry ingredients.
Turn batter into a greased (bottom only) 9 1/2 x 5 1/4 x 2 3/4-inch loaf pan and spread batter evenly into the corners.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until a cake tester or wooden pick inserted in center of bread comes out clean.
Cool bread 10 minutes in pan on cooling rack.
Remove from pan and cool completely.
Cut bread thinly and sandwich slices together with whipped butter.
Makes 1 loaf bread.

title: cooked play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients (dry ones first) in a saucepan.
Cook until mixture pulls away from the sides of the pan.
Knead on a floured surface while hot.

title: mom's doughnuts
directions: Beat eggs until very light.
Beat in sugar gradually.
Add milk and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Add shortening and mix well. Sift flour, baking powder, spices and salt together.
Add 1/2 of dry mixture to egg mixture and beat until smooth.
Brush doughnut maker with a light coating of vegetable oil and fill with batter. Hold doughnut maker over oil at surface and release ring of batter onto surface.
Deep fry at 375° (medium) approximately 1 minute on each side, turning to brown evenly.
Remove from oil and drain on paper towels.
Frost, sprinkle or decorate as desired.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: cheddar olive filled cheese balls
directions: Mix milk and flour.
Mix by hand and knead.
Pinch piece and cover drained dried stuffed olives.
Makes 25.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: egg sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage and drain.
Cube bread; put bread in 9 x 13-inch pan and place sausage and cheese on top.
Mix eggs and half and half.
Pour over top.
Chill overnight.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add mixed dry ingredients to butter mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in a greased tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Beat eggs well. Add gradually the sugar and flour.
Pour over diced rhubarb. Pour into pastry shell. Cover with lattice top crust.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°, then 25 minutes at 350°.

title: hot lemon sauce
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch; add slowly boiling water.
Cook, stirring constantly until thickened.
Add, then blend juice and rind, butter, salt and vanilla.
Serve hot.

title: islander cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Roll into ball.
Roll in remaining 1 1/2 cups chopped pecans to cover.
Nice and refreshing cheese ball appetizer.

title: barbecue cups
directions: Brown meat until crumbly and drain off grease.
Stir in the barbecue sauce, onion and brown sugar.

Grease a muffin pan with shortening and press each biscuit into a cup in the muffin pan. Spoon the meat mixture into each cup and sprinkle with cheese. Preheat oven to 400° and bake 10 to 12 minutes until brown.

title: cherry-coconut bars
directions: Heat oven to
Mix with hands 1 cup flour, butter and confectioners
sugar until smooth.	Spread thin with hands into 8 x
x 2-inch square pan.	Bake about 25 minutes. Stir all remaining
ingredients into eggs.
Spread over base.
Bake about 25 minutes	more.
Cool.
Cut into bars or squares.
For dessert, top with whipped cream and cherry.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Take center out of mushrooms.
Chop up mushroom centers, green pepper and onion.
Fry sausage and drain grease.
Mix all ingredients.
Stuff mixture into mushroom caps.
Pour butter over each mushroom right before you put into oven.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: hot cider punch
directions: Combine cider and ginger ale in bottom of 30-cup electric percolator.
Place remaining ingredients in basket.
Allow to go through perk cycle.
Serves 24.

title: grandma's rice
directions: In heavy frypan, saute all above ingredients.
Add chicken broth and simmer until rice is done.
This can also be finished in a 325° oven.

title: lemon sugar cookies
directions: In large mixing bowl, cream butter, sugars and oil.
Beat in eggs and extract.
Combine flour, baking soda and cream of tartar; stir into creamed mixture (dough will be stiff).
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheets. Press with bottom of a glass dipped in water, then sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until edges are lightly browned.
Makes 11 dozen.

title: french butter cream cookies
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients until well blended, then gradually add flour until all mixed in.
Chill dough for 30 minutes.
Shape dough into 3/4-inch balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet. Flatten balls with fork.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 8 minutes until set, but not brown.
Remove from oven and let stand for at least 1 minute.
Remove from cookie sheet and cool on rack.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: frosted peach salad
directions: Place peach halves in a greased muffin pan.
Combine next 4 ingredients and mix well.
Mound mixture in peach cavities and freeze until firm.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in 1 cup boiling water.
Let mixture chill until slightly thickened.
Mix other ingredients; chill firm.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: mayonnaise muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients, stir until smooth. Spoon batter into greased 6-cup muffin pan, filling two-thirds full. Bake at 425 degrees for 10-12 minutes. Yield: 6 muffins.

title: zesty chuck strips
directions: Cut beef, carrots, celery and peppers into strips.
If red peppers are not available, use green peppers.
Mix flour, salt and pepper; then roll meat in seasoned flour.
Melt butter in a large skillet.
Add meat and brown.
Stir in other ingredients and mix well.
Cover and cook gently until meat is tender.
Cooking time: approximately 3 1/2 hours.
Serve over rice, prepared to package instructions.

title: spicy sausage balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray or oil cookie sheet.
Mix ingredients and make into balls.
Can be put close together on pan because they do not spread out.
Bake for 12 minutes.
These are great appetizers.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Boil eggs.
Slice eggs and scoop out yellows in mixing bowl. With a fork, mash yellows and sprinkle them with sugar until sparkly.
Add Miracle Whip (to taste).
Use tablespoons to fill egg whites with yellow filling.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: hot chicken salad or casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except eggs together well.
In a casserole dish, put a layer of chicken mix and then a layer of eggs. Continue layering until all ingredients are used.
Top with 2 cups finely crushed potato chips.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes at 375°. Almonds may be used as topping instead of potato chips.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add 1 cup sugar gradually to 1/2 cup shortening; cream well.
Blend in 2 unbeaten eggs.
Stir in mashed bananas.
Blend in sifted dry ingredients. Stir in nuts.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: baked beans quartet
directions: Cook bacon crisp, crumble.
Cook onion and garlic in drippings. Drain.
Combine bacon, onion, butter beans and next 4 ingredients. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into lightly greased 2 1/2-quart bean pot or baking dish.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 1 hour.

title: dutch apple pie
directions: Mix the sour cream and lemon juice together, stirring until well blended.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Place the apple pie filling on top of this mixture, spreading over entire pie. Bake this at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
After removing it from the oven, mix the chopped nuts and cinnamon together; sprinkle over top of pie.
Good served warm or cold.

title: fluffy 2 step cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar in large bowl with wire whisk until smooth. Gently stir in Cool Whip. Spoon into crust. Refrigerate 3 hours. Top with cherry pie filling just before serving. Makes 8 servings.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Mix Crisco and butter well. Add eggs one at a time. Add dry ingredients, milk and vanilla. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours in tube pan.

title: salmon roll
directions: Mix well and roll in chopped nuts and parsley flakes.

title: bread dip
directions: Combine the first seven ingredients together in a bowl.
Chill in refrigerator for at least 2 to 3 hours (overnight).
Cut off top of bread.
When ready to serve, hollow out bread and tear into small pieces to dip with.
Place dip into the shell of the hollowed out bread.

title: almond-apricot bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
In large bowl with wooden spoon or mixer, beat egg and sugar well. Add milk and biscuit mix.
Beat well.
Stir in almonds, apricots and extract, mixing well.
Turn batter into pan.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes until tester comes out clean from center.
Cool 10 minutes.
Loosen sides with spatula.
Cool completely on wire rack.

title: fresh mint and ginger lemonade
directions: Combine chopped mint, ginger and honey in medium bowl.
Add boiling water.
Let steep for 30 minutes.
Strain into 4-cup glass measuring cup, pressing on solids to extract the liquid.
Add lemon juice and enough cold water to measure 4 cups total.
(Can be prepared 1 day ahead, covered and refrigerated.)

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Bake cake as directed for a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Poke holes in cake.
Mix 1/2 can of Eagle Brand milk and 1/2 can of cream of coconut.
Pour mixture over hot cake.
Let cake cool, then spread Cool Whip on top of cake.
Garnish with toasted coconut.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Prepare vanilla pudding with milk according to package directions; set aside.
In a separate bowl, combine strawberry flavored gelatin and boiling water; stir in frozen strawberries.

title: beer biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix biscuit mix and sugar until well blended.
Starting with 1/2 cup beer and adding more as needed, mix in beer to form a wet, tacky dough (just a little wetter than usual biscuit dough).
Spoon dough onto flour-covered surface, lightly dust top with flour and roll dough to 1/2 inch.
Cut biscuits with 3-inch cutter.
Cover bottom of pan with melted shortening and arrange in pan.
Baste top with more shortening. Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen large biscuits or 18 to 24 regular-size biscuits.

title: peach bavarian mold
directions: Drain peaches reserving 2/3 cup juice.
Chop peaches into small pieces.
Set aside.
In a bowl dissolve gelatin and sugar in boiling water.
Stir in reserved juice.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Stir almond extract into Cool Whip.
Gently fold into gelatin mixture.
Fold in peaches, pour into an oiled 6 cup mold. Chill overnight.
Unmold, garnish with additional peaches if desired.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: hoe cakes
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Mix until you have a pancake batter consistency.
In frying pan heat oil until pan is warm to touch.
Pour batter into heated pan.
Cook 5 to 8 minutes on either side until golden brown.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: In long oblong baking pan, put peaches and juice.
Add water and sugar.
Stir well.
Pour cake mix on top.
Pour melted margarine over cake mix (do not mix).
Bake at 350° until top is golden brown.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Into a pan or skillet, sift together first the flour, then other dry ingredients.
Add milk slowly.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until thick.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and butter. Serve over hot biscuits.

title: macaroni and cheese with tomatoes
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
In a casserole dish, mix macaroni and tomatoes, half of cheese and salt and pepper.
Put remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes until cheese is melted.

title: dried beef gravy
directions: Make white sauce:
Melt margarine.
Add flour.
Stir together to make paste.
Slowly whisk in milk until smooth and desired consistency.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Tear apart dried beef and add to white sauce.
Serve over toast.

title: fried rice
directions: Heat salad oil and add the rest of the ingredients; fry together.

title: apple fruit dip
directions: Whip cream cheese with mixer until soft and fluffy.
Mix in brown sugar and Cool Whip.
Use as a dip with apple slices or other types of fruit.

title: eggplant patties
directions: Peel eggplant and cut into small pieces.
Boil in salted water until tender.
Drain well and mash.
Stir in other ingredients and mix well.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto a well-greased griddle. Fry on both sides until golden brown.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: brown betty rice
directions: Mix ingredients in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: caramel chocolate squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Heat caramels and 1/4 cup of the milk in saucepan over medium heat, stirring constantly until caramels are melted and mixture is smooth.
Keep mixture warm over low heat, stirring occasionally.
Mix cake mix, butter, remaining milk and nuts.
Spread half of the mixture in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 6 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and coconut over cake.
Spread caramel over chips and coconut. Drop remaining dough by teaspoon onto caramel layer, spreading evenly.
Bake until cake is slightly dry to touch, 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool completely.
Refrigerate until time.
Makes 48 bars.

title: cranberry mousse
directions: Drain pineapple well, reserving all liquid.
Add this to dry jello in a 2-quart saucepan.
Stir in water.
Heat to boiling, stirring to dissolve gelatin; remove from heat.
Blend in cranberry sauce.
Add lemon juice, lemon peel and nutmeg.
Chill until mixture thickens slightly.
Blend in sour cream.
Fold in pineapple and pecans.
Pour into a 2-quart mold or bowl and chill until firm.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and bring to slow boil.
Let it boil for 5 minutes.
Add or lessen red pepper to taste.

title: strawberry - vanilla pudding
directions: Place angel cake cubes in 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. In mixer bowl, combine instant pudding and milk.
Add ice cream.
Beat at low speed until well blended.
Pour over cake cubes.
Chill until firm.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries. Stir until jello begins to thicken slightly.
Pour over pudding, but do not stir.
Chill until set.

title: deep dish brownies
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease an 8 x 8 x 2-inch square or a 9 x 13-inch pan (for thinner brownies).
Mix ingredients and bake 40 to 45 minutes or until brownies begin to pull away from sides. Cool completely before cutting.

title: cold vegetable salad
directions: Drain corn, English peas and French cut green beans.
Add to drained vegetables the celery, water chestnuts and onion.

title: shrimp creole
directions: In a heavy pot, melt butter. Add oil. Saute all seasonings until done (approximately 5 minutes). Add flour and blend well. Add tomato sauce, hot water and sugar. Cook over medium heat approximately 30 minutes. Season to taste.
Add shrimp. Cook 30 minutes longer.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: instant pumpkin pie
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl.
Mix on high speed for 3 minutes. Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: lo-cal chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Chill.
Great to serve for lunch on hot summer days!

title: salsa
directions: Cook over medium heat until thick.
Stir occasionally.
You can seal in jars or keep in refrigerator.

title: succulent spareribs(makes 4 large servings)
directions: Cover spareribs in large saucepan with just enough water to cover ribs.
Add garlic and onions and bring to a boil.
Then simmer, covered, for 1 hour until ribs are tender

title: flank steak teriyaki
directions: Boil tongue.
When ready to serve, slice, flour lightly and fry.
Arrange on serving platter.
Add chili sauce; decorate with parsley and serve immediately.

title: chili sauce
directions: Grind onions and green peppers.
Add all other ingredients at once.
Cook over low heat for about 2 hours or until thick.
Pack right away in clean jars and seal.

title: skillet cabbage
directions: In a large skillet, add oil to heat, then add cabbage, carrots, bell pepper and onion.
When done, add sugar, crumbled bacon, hot sauce and salt and pepper to taste.
Cook 15 minutes; if you want crispy vegetables, do not cover pan.
Cook until well blended.

title: five vegetable casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water for 15 minutes until tender, drain.
Cool slightly and slice.
Cook cauliflower, carrots and onion in boiling water about 10 minutes, drain.
Place all vegetables in a 2-quart rectangular baking dish.
Stir together soup and milk.
Spoon over vegetables.
Bake, covered, in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Uncover, sprinkle on top and bake 3 to 4 minutes more or until cheese melts.
Serves 12.

title: orange congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello with 1 cup hot water.
Simmer on medium heat pineapple and sugar for 2 minutes.
Add to jello mixture and refrigerate until set, several hours or overnight.
After jello sets, mix remaining ingredients in order given.
Place in a medium bowl or container.

title: cheese dip
directions: Brown ground chuck; drain.
Add it to diced Velveeta cheese. Add Ro-Tel tomatoes and chopped red onion.
Cook over low heat or microwave until cheese is melted.

title: chicken stuffed shells
directions: Cook chicken breasts in water (reserve broth).
Cool and cut up.
Make stuffing according to package directions.
Mix all of the stuffing, cut up chicken and Miracle Whip.
Boil large shells al dente.
Rinse with cool water.
Allow to dry.
Stuff shells with prepared mixture.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain green beans, peas and white corn.
Chop onion, celery, green pepper and pimento.
Mix all together.

title: broccoli salad
directions: For salad, mix all ingredients:
Broccoli, celery, green onions, grapes, bacon. For dressing mix all ingredients: mayonnaise, vinegar, sugar.

title: cheesy ham sour cream potato soup
directions: Bring broth water and bouillon cubes to a boil. Boil potatoes until tender. Do not drain. Saute carrots, celery and onion in a bit of butter, then add to potato mixture. Add ham, combine milk and flour until smooth, then add to potato mixture and cook until thickened. Stir in sour cream and cheese. Simmer until cheese is melted. Season to taste.

title: crescent appetizers
directions: Make these 24 hours before they are wanted.

title: real mincemeat pie
directions: Cook meat until browned.
Add other ingredients (except vinegar);
cook until soft, stirring constantly.
When nearly cooked, add vinegar.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased pan.
Cook for 45 minutes at 350°.
Great with chili.

title: vegetable surprise
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Cook rice according to directions. Cook broccoli and cauliflower first.
May add anything else you would like (carrots, corn).
Drain everything.
Put in casserole dish.
Add rice, soup and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. You may add bread crumbs, if desired, on top.

title: aloha golden apple crisp
directions: Combine apples and pineapple; place in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine flour, sugar and seasonings; cut in butter until crumbly.
Stir in coconut and nuts; sprinkle evenly over apples.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until apples are tender and topping is golden.

title: snickerdoodle cookies
directions: Sift together flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt; set aside.
Combine butter, sugar and eggs.
Beat until light and creamy.
Add dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Chill 1 to 2 hours.
Roll teaspoonful of dough into balls, roll balls in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes, until light brown, but still soft.
They puff up, but flatten out with cracked tops. Cool on wire rack.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix and bake until firm for 30 minutes.

title: mama viv's spaghetti
directions: Boil spaghetti until tender.
Brown ground beef; drain.
Add sauce to ground beef; simmer.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat
eggs;
add sugar, syrup, salt, vanilla and butter or oleo.
Add
pecans and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 50 or 60 minutes.
Pecans
can
be
placed
in
bottom of pie crust and filling poured over them.

title: peanut raisin carob chews
directions: In a
large
bowl, combine all ingredients.
Form dough into balls with hands.
Size of balls should be about the size of a tablespoon.
Chill and serve.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt butter and mix with croutons.
Place half of this in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cook the sliced squash and chopped onion.
Salt to taste.
Drain and add soup and sour cream and pour into casserole. Spread grated cheese on top and sprinkle with remaining croutons. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: caramel cups
directions: Mix well ingredients.
Pat into tassie pans, making high rims. Prick with fork.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Combine margarine, cocoa and milk in a saucepan.
Bring mixture to a boil; do not let scorch.
Add powdered sugar, vanilla and pecans and spread on hot cake.

title: dill dip
directions: In a large mixing bowl, mix all the ingredients together well. Chill for 2 hours before serving.
Goes well with chunks of rye bread or pumpernickel bread.
Can also be used as a vegetable dip or a dip for fried vegetables.

title: microwave hot crab dip
directions: In a small bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat cream cheese until smooth and fluffy. Gradually beat in next 5 ingredients until well blended. Fold in crabmeat and pimientos. Turn into a 1-quart casserole. Cover and microwave on High 4 to 5 minutes until very warm, stirring twice.
Stir again before serving. Serve with crackers and/or fresh veggies.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugars.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add vanilla.
Put oatmeal, a little at a time, in blender or food processor; process to a fine powder.
Combine oatmeal powder, flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Add combined dry ingredients to creamed mixture; blend well.
Add chocolate chips, grated Hershey bar and nuts to dough.
Form dough into walnut-sized balls; place about 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Cookies should be barely brown and look a little underdone when removed from oven.
They set up as they cool.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Cook and drain noodles; set aside.
Cook and drain spinach; set aside.
Mix cheeses, sour cream, egg, spinach, salt and pepper in a large bowl.
Spread a thin layer of sauce in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer noodles, cheeses, sauce to top of pan, ending with sauce.
Sprinkle top with grated cheese and Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes until sides are bubbly and top is brown.

title: beef and rice
directions: Cook ground beef and onions until brown.
Cook rice and drain. Mix these 2 ingredients and add all other ingredients.
Let simmer 10 minutes.
Top with cream cheese.
Cool and serve.

title: walnut pumpkin pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Combine pumpkin, sweetened condensed milk, eggs, 3/4 t. cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg, and salt, mix well. Pout into crust.
Bake 15 minutes; remove pie.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Combine sugar, flour, and remaining 1/2 t. cinnamon; cut in margarine until crumbly.
Stir in walnuts.
Sprinkle walnut mixture over pie.
Bake 40 minutes at 350° or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Makes 1 pie.

title: key lime pie
directions: Fold by hand.
Place the ingredients in a graham cracker crust.
Quick 'n easy.

title: chocolate chip blonde brownies
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add nuts.
Set aside.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add sugar; stir until melted.
Remove from stove.
Add egg and vanilla.
Add flour mixture, a little at a time; mix well. Spread in greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 package semi-sweet chocolate chips over top.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Double recipe for a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: peanut butter stars
directions: Beat first 5 ingredients as directed.
Add flour and baking powder.
Shape dough into 2 (11-inch) rolls.
Wrap.
Chill for 4 hours.
Cut each roll into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Dip in sugar and place on baking sheets (ungreased).
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Immediately press chocolate star in center of each cookie.

title: wacky cake
directions: Measure dry ingredients into sifter.
Melt 6 tablespoons of butter.
Sift dry ingredients in 8-inch square pan, ungreased. Make 3 wells in dry ingredients.
Pour melted butter into 1st well, vinegar into 2nd well and vanilla into 3rd well.
Pour water over dry ingredients.
Stir mixture with a fork until thoroughly mixed.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: buttered carrot sticks(by children 7 - 12 years old)
directions: Wash and pare 8 carrots, then cut lengthwise into 1/2 inch strips on cutting board.
Using a measuring cup, pour 1 inch of water into saucepan.
Keep track how many cups of water you use, then add 1/2 teaspoon salt for each cup of water.
Add the carrots.
The water should just cover them.
Cover and cook over medium heat 18 to 20 minutes or until the carrots are tender when pierced with fork.
Lift the carrots to serving dish with slotted spoon, gently stir in 2 tablespoons butter.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts until done.
Cool in a bowl.
Mix milk and cream of mushroom soup until smooth.
In a greased casserole. Place uncooked macaroni noodles. Pour milk, and mushroom mixture over noodles.
Cut cooled chicken breast into quarters.
Layer on top of noodle/milk/mushrooms.
Layer with Cheddar cheese.
Top with buttered dressing.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Uncover last 5 minutes for crunchy topping.

title: pecan pie
directions: Add sugar
and	syrup to lightly beaten eggs. Add salt, vanilla and butter.
Place pecans in bottom of unbaked crusts. Add filling.
Bake at
for
to
50 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: baked potato wedges
directions: Cut medium potatoes lengthwise into wedges.
Place in baking dish.
Brush with beaten egg white.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and oregano.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.
Serves 1 to 100 per serving.

title: easy and delicious magic cookie bars
directions: Melt butter in saucepan and pour into bottom of 9 x 13-inch Pyrex rectangular baking dish so bottom of pan is completely coated, then coat with graham cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle nuts, chocolate chips and then pour over the condensed milk.
Top with shredded coconut.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool before cutting into squares.

title: fruit medley punch
directions: Prepare ice ring in advance.
In blender container, blend strawberries well (about 30 seconds).
In large punch bowl, combine strawberries, apricot nectar, water, lemon juice, orange juice and sugar.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Slowly pour in ginger ale.
Add ice ring.

title: creole mixed vegetables
directions: In a 4 to 5-quart saucepan, bring green beans and turnips to boil.
Reduce heat and cover to simmer about 20 minutes.
Remove from heat and drain. Add peas and simmer 30 minutes.

title: cheesy apples
directions: Place apples in baking dish.
Mix other 5 ingredients and put on top of apples.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken with mushrooms
directions: Heat saucepan.	Add oil;
brown garlic and ginger.
Add chicken;
brown
slightly.	Add salt, shoyu, liquor and water; simmer
for
minutes.
Add
bamboo shoots, which have been sliced,
and
mushrooms;
simmer until chicken is tender.
Add thickening made of cornstarch and water.
Add green onions and serve.

title: lots o' cookies
directions: In a mixer, cream oleo, sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla and mix well.
In a large bowl, mix the flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add the dry mixture to the blender gradually, mixing well.
In a large pan, mix all the cereals, coconut, nuts, raisins and chocolate bits.
Pour the liquid mixture into the cereal mix and use 2 large spoons to stir it all together.
Drop by teaspoon and flatten.
Bake on greased cookie sheets for 10 minutes at 350°.
Very healthy and good.

title: jiffy corn meal salad
directions: Add to Jiffy corn meal the boiled eggs, ham, onion, bell pepper and corn.
Mix all together and add large bottle of Ranch style dressing.
Refrigerate.

title: poppy seed pound cake
directions: Beat all ingredients together for 2 minutes.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour tube pan, Bundt pan or 2 loaf pans.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes, or until toothpick comes out clean.
For moist cake do not overbake.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: chicken mushroom bake
directions: Season chicken breasts with salt and pepper.
Dip chicken in melted butter and then in flour.
Bake the chicken, skin side down, for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Turn over.
Mix soup and sour cream together and pour over chicken.
Bake 45 minutes longer.

title: crock-pot barbecue spareribs
directions: Spread ribs on baking sheet; salt and pepper to taste and brown in oven.
Take out and place ribs in crock-pot.
Pour on remaining ingredients.
Cook on high for 2 hours and on low for 6 hours. May be cooked overnight on low or all day on low.

title: fried rice with pork
directions: Place rice and cold water in 4-quart saucepan; bring to boil. Steam 20 minutes on low heat; set aside to cool.
Brown pork in slightly greased 10-inch skillet.
Cover and cook for 20 to 25 minutes on low heat.
Add celery, onion and bell pepper; saute 3 minutes.
Add rice, ham, soy sauce, mushrooms, Accent and pepper. Cook about 5 minutes longer.
Add eggs and mix.
Makes 4 servings.

title: applesauce loaf
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until light.
Add eggs and beat until fluffy.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternately with applesauce and nuts.
Pour into 9 1/2 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: fresh fruit ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients in ice cream freezer.
Mix well. Freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.

title: cornbread for dressing
directions: Sift Jiffy mix and cornmeal together.
Combine dry ingredients and mix well with water. Pour mixture into greased pan.
Bake at 300° until golden brown.

title: escalloped corn
directions: Mix well all ingredients in order given (corn bread mix just out of box, do not add to it).
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: deluxe chicken pot pie
