directions: Cut chicken into small pieces qnd fry in oil until lightly browned on sides. Add mixed vegetables and cornstarch and stir well. Add soup and broth and stirring continously until mixture comes to a boil and thickens. Season to taste. Prepare

6 servings of instant mashed potatoes as directed on package. Spoon chicken mixture into heatproof dish. Pipe or spoon mashed potatoes around edge of dish. Place under pre-heated broiler until lightly browned.

title: german red cabbage
directions: Trim cabbage and shred, discarding core and heavy ribs.
In a Dutch oven, heat butter and fry the bacon in it until it is rendered but not brown.
Add sugar and saute over low heat, stirring frequently, until sugar turns brown.
Add apple and onion; saute 2 to 3 minutes.
Add cabbage and toss with apple and onion. Pour in vinegar and braise, covered, for 10 minutes or until cabbage is bright purple.
Stir occasionally.
Sprinkle with salt and add water until barely covered.
Simmer, covered, for about 2 hours.
Add water as needed and salt to taste.

title: chocolate velvet frosting
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in pot.
Stir in boiling water until blended.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickens. Add chocolate squares and butter until melted.
Remove from heat and add butter.
When cooled, it will frost a two-tier cake.

title: bishop's bread
directions: Cream sugar and eggs.
Combine dry ingredients.
Stir fruit and nuts in flour mixture.
Add to creamed sugar and eggs.

title: summer squash with cheese
directions: Boil squash until tender in small amount of water.
Drain. Make a white sauce using melted butter, flour, salt and milk.
Add squash to sauce.
Arrange in a greased casserole alternating layers of squash with thin layers of cheese.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: goblin's perky punch for halloween party
directions: Place 1 pumpkin and several pieces of candy corn alternately in each section of ice cube tray; fill with water.
Freeze overnight.
Chill remaining ingredients.
Mix orange drink, pineapple juice, apricot nectar and lemon juice in punch bowl; add 7-Up just before serving.
Add prepared ice cubes to punch; serve punch in cups with ice cube in each cup.

title: creamy baked chicken breasts
directions: Arrange the chicken in lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan; top with cheese.
Combine soup and wine; stir well and spoon over chicken.
Melt butter and stir into stuffing mix.
Bake for 45 to 55 minutes at 350°.

title: turkey soup
directions: Break up turkey carcass and simmer 1 hour in 6 cups water. Allow to cool.
Pick turkey meat from bones and return to broth.

title: grandmommy's sliced cucumber pickles
directions: To every gallon of cucumbers, add one handful of salt.
Pour boiling water over to cover.
Let stand overnight.
In the morning, drain.
Add onions.
Mix remaining ingredients and boil them.
Add cucumbers and onions and scald (not boil).
Put into jars.

title: pudding dessert
directions: Mix together first three ingredients and put into greased cake pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°. Cream together next three ingredients and spread on cooled crust.
Mix last three ingredients and spread on top.
Cover with remaining Cool Whip and chopped pecans.

title: easy corned beef
directions: Soak corned beef in water to cover for 30 minutes. Preheat oven to 300°.
Place a large sheet of heavy-duty foil in shallow pan. Remove corned beef from water and pat dry to remove any salt on surface.
Place in center of foil.
Pour 1/4 cup fresh water over beef. Sprinkle with pickling spice and arrange vegetables over and around corned beef.
Bring long sides of foil up over beef and seal with
a tight fold.
Bake 4 hours.

title: teri's amazing pina coladas
directions: Combine Coco Lopez, pineapple juice, rum and ice.
Mix well in blender.
Garnish with pineapple and cherry.
Serves 4.

title: sour cream-banana bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour jelly roll pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch.
Mix sugar, sour cream, margarine and eggs in large mixer bowl on low speed, scraping bowl occasionally, 1 minute.
Beat in bananas and vanilla on low speed 30 seconds. Beat in flour, salt and baking soda on medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally, 1 minute.
Stir in nuts.
Spread dough in pan.
Bake until light brown, 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool; frost with Browned Butter Frosting.
Cut into bars, about 2 x 1 1/2-inches.
Yields 4 dozen cookies.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix all together and bake in a tube pan at 350 for 50 to 60 minutes. Coal 10 minutes in pan and then remove.

title: aunt emmie's festive apple bread(makes 2 large loaves or 4 small loaves)
directions: Grease 2 large or 4 small pans.
You may flour pans or sprinkle with sugar which gives a crusty edge to each slice.
(I like using sugar.)

title: banana split dessert
directions: Mix graham crackers and melted oleo.
Pat into bottom of 9 1/2 x 11 1/2-inch pan.
Refrigerate.
Mix at medium speed until creamy sugar, eggs, vanilla and oleo.
Spread over crust.
Refrigerate 1/2 hour.
Top with bananas, sliced lengthwise, then crushed pineapple.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle walnuts, cherries and chocolate chips.
Cool 4 hours or overnight.

title: lite lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix pudding as directed on package.
Add half of the Cool Whip.
Add the Kool-Aid mix and pour into a pie shell.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Place in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: baked clams
directions: Saute garlic, onion, parsley and oregano in little oil a few minutes; remove from heat and add clams with juice.
Put in small shells, sprinkle with cheese and bread crumbs and bake at 375° for about 20 minutes.

title: broccoli and corn casserole
directions: Mix broccoli, corn, egg, onions, salt and pepper. Put this into a 9-inch square pan that has been greased.
Top with melted butter, mixed with cracker crumbs (may double topping).
Add bacon (precooked), cut into small pieces, to the top of crumbs.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, uncovered.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together; shape into a ball. Roll in the chopped beef. Refrigerate and serve with crackers.
This may be made ahead of time and frozen.

title: roast beef salad
directions: Combine ingredients.
Squeeze whole, fresh lime over top. Toss and refrigerate for a few hours.

title: crescent breakfast bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°. In medium skillet, cook sausage until browned and no longer pink, stirring frequently; drain. Separate dough into 4 rectangles. Place in ungreased 13 x 9 pan. Press over bottom and 1/2-inch up sides to form crust; firmly press edges and perforations to seal. Spoon sausage evenly over crust. Sprinkle with potatoes and cheese. Beat eggs in medium bowl. Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Pour over cheese in crust. Bake at 375° for 18 to 23 minutes or until center is set and edges are deep golden brown.

title: cherry coke salad
directions: Drain juice from fruit.
Add water if necessary to make 2 cups of liquid.
Heat juice to boiling.
Add jello; stir until dissolved.
Cool.
Add Coca-Cola and fruit.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart mold.

title: mom's fruit punch
directions: Cook sugar and water together to a boil; cool.
Add all the rest of the ingredients, except the Seven-Up.
Add that at last, right when you are going to serve it.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: kale ann
directions: In a large frypan, add butter and onions.
Cook until translucent.
Add lamb and fry until done.
Add tomato paste and sauce, oregano, basil, parsley and the cinnamon.
Stir together and simmer.
Mix the spinach and cottage cheese together.
In a good size casserole, put the tomato-lamb mixture on the bottom; put half of the Mozzarella on top.
Layer spinach-cheese mixture on top, then the rest of the Mozzarella.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes until bubbly and the cheese is melted.
Serve with spinach noodles and garlic bread.

title: rye bread
directions: In a bowl, dissolve yeast 1 cup warm water.
Mix in milk, molasses, 3 cups warm water and sugar.
Mix well.
Blend in shortening.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix in. Add enough white flour to make a sticky dough. Cover and let rise until doubled in size. Divide dough into fifths.
Place each into greased loaf tin and allow to rise again.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Makes 5 loaves.

title: garden pasta
directions: Put vegetables in pot and cover tightly.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, for 10 minutes.
Add seasonings. Recover and cook over medium-low heat for 5 minutes.
Add the oil and simmer for 30 minutes or until the carrots are tender.
Cook the spaghetti and drain.
Toss spaghetti and sauce together.

title: broccoli-mushroom quiche
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine eggs, milk and salt and mix well. Toss cheese with flour.
Add cheese mixture.
Add vegetables to egg mixture, stirring gently to mix.
Pour into pie shell and bake for 40 to 45 minutes, or until quiche is light brown and almost firm.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Boil sweet potatoes until tender, then peel.
In electric mixer, mash potatoes with all other ingredients until well blended.
Turn into a greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: freezer pepper cabbage
directions: Mix and boil 1 minute.

title: sweet potatoes and apple bake
directions: Peel and slice potatoes and apples (thin).
Place in baking dish and pour sugar over; dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, or until potatoes are tender.

title: veggie bar
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix with Ranch dressing and mayonnaise. Stir in chopped vegetables. Serve with Town House crackers.

title: beer batter fish
directions: Clean and dry your favorite fish thoroughly.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
If too thin add more flour, if too thick add more beer or water.
Dip dry fish and fry in hot hot oil to golden.

title: mock lemon pie
directions: Cook rhubarb, sugar and water until rhubarb is tender and water dissolved.
Mix well in saucepan the sugar, salt and flour. Then add and mix well the 1/2 cup milk, 2 egg yolks and when batter is smooth, add 1 1/2 cups of milk.
Cook over medium heat, about 8 minutes, stirring constantly, until thick.
Remove from heat and add margarine, vanilla and rhubarb.
Stir well. Place in baked pie shell. Cover with meringue.
Brown in oven.

title: extra-good mushroom soup
directions: In a saucepan over medium heat, in hot butter, cook onions, mushrooms and thyme until mushrooms are tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in soup, cream and milk.
Heat through, stirring occasionally.
Ladle into bowls; serve with crackers.

title: squash-cheese casserole
directions: Cook squash cut in 1-inch pieces in boiling salted water to 1/3 depth of squash until barely tender, approximately 8 minutes, stirring once so as to cook evenly.
Drain thoroughly.
Can use well-drained leftover squash.
Measure squash.
Grate half as much cheese as squash.
Make 1/2 as much medium white sauce as squash, using 2 tablespoons butter, 2 tablespoons flour and 1 cup milk as proportions.
Place layer of squash in greased casserole, half of cheese, half of sauce.
Add rest of squash, rest of sauce and rest of cheese.
Crumble Ritz crackers to cover cheese, dot with butter and bake at 350° (20 to 30 minutes) until crumbs are golden brown and casserole bubbles.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg.
Dissolve soda in sweet milk.
Stir milk into bananas.
Add banana mixture to sugar mixture.
Combine flour and baking powder.
Add to sugar-banana mixture.
Add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes in well-greased pan.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: To make sauce:
Cook onion in butter or margarine until tender but not brown.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 1 to 2 minutes more; remove from heat.
Place half of the sliced potatoes in a greased 2-quart casserole.
Cover with half of the sauce.
Repeat layers.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 45 minutes, stirring once.
Uncover; bake about 30 minutes more, or until potatoes are done.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: rainbow fruit sticks
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: green pepper steak
directions: Cut steak diagonally across the grain into thin slices.
Cut into strips about two inches long.
Heat salad oil in skillet over medium heat.
Place garlic clove and meat into oil and cook over medium heat until browned.
Remove garlic and discard.
Add onion, green pepper, salt, pepper and ginger.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until tender.
Combine cornstarch, bouillon and soy sauce.
Stir into mixture in skillet.
Bring to boil; cook, stirring constantly until mixture is thick and clear. Serve over hot cooked rice.

title: red lobster's cheese biscuits
directions: Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: homemade reese's cups
directions: Melt butter and work the ingredients together to form into small balls.
Dip into melted chocolate or vanilla with toothpicks.
Set on wax paper to cool.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Cook onion and pepper in oil for 3 to 5 minutes.
Add soup and milk.
Stir until smooth.
Add cheese and seasonings.
Fold in hominy.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole that has been greased well.
Top with bread crumbs.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: crazy eggs
directions: In a 9 x 9-inch buttered baking pan, put ham and bread and top with cheese and onion.
Mix the rest of the ingredients together and pour the liquids over the bread.
Let stand before baking for a while (can keep in the refrigerator overnight).
Dot with butter. Bake at 325°
for 1 hour.

title: pecan clusters
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour and chopped pecans.
Flour hands and form into small pecan shapes.
Bake in slow oven at 275° for 45 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while still warm.

title: leftover ham surprise
directions: Cook ham and seasonings in a large pot for 30 minutes. Leftovers work best.
Add macaroni.
Stir.
Cube Velveeta.
Stir in gradually as noodles cook.
Done in about 20 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix the apples and sugar thoroughly.
Add the oil, nuts, egg and vanilla.
Mix the remaining ingredients and add to the first mixture.
Put in Pammed 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until it shrinks from edges of pan and is brown. If you bake in a Pyrex pan, lower temperature 20°.
This recipe can be doubled.

title: nutty buddy pie
directions: Mix together and bake at 300° until brown.
Cool.

title: ritz chicken
directions: Spread bite size pieces of meat in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix soup and sour cream and spread over meat.
Crush crackers and spread over soup mix.
Spread with melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: copper penny salad
directions: Cook carrots until tender; mix all vegetables together.
Bring remaining ingredients to boil; cool slightly. Pour over vegetables; mix well. Let set 12 hours. Can add other vegetables if you desire.

title: crab casserole
directions: Mix crab, celery, relish, salt, mustard and salad dressing. Then add bread and cheese.
Beat eggs separately and add to mixture.
Milk and Worcestershire sauce should be added separately.
Pour into other mixture and stir in.
Grease casserole lightly.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hominy casserole
directions: In a casserole dish, spread drained hominy.
Mix soup and Cheez Whiz together and pour over hominy.
Bake in 350° oven until brown.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
(I use electric mixer.) Add eggs one at a time and beat.
Add vanilla. Sift dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture.
Chill in refrigerator; divide into thirds.
Roll dough thin and cut with cookie cutter.
Be sure not to work in much flour as cookie dough is rolled out.
Place cut out cookies on cookie sheet and bake about ten minutes or until they are as brown as you want them.

title: potato salad(aka: karen reeder's heavy potato salad)
directions: Mix together in a large bowl.
Garnish with paprika.
Keep refrigerated.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Place walnuts or pecans (if desired) in 13 x 9-inch or 2 round cake pans sprayed with Pam (nonstick), then rolls.
Mix pudding and cinnamon and sprinkle over rolls in pan.
Microwave margarine and brown sugar and drizzle over rolls.
Cover tightly with Saran Wrap. Let rise overnight or 5 to 6 hours.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Turn pans upside-down on plate or pan; leave for a few minutes and remove pans.

title: macaroni and cheese chili casserole
directions: Boil your macaroni for 20 minutes, then add package of cheese enclosed (mix together).
Warm your chili in a pan, then pour into the macaroni and cheese.
Mix again (all together).
Place single cheeses on top of casserole.
Place in microwave for 2 minutes. Done and serve.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together the eggs, oil and cornbread mix.
Stir in the cheese, corn and onion.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake about 45 minutes at 400°.

title: coney island hamburgers
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Form cakes and brown.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Place cakes in sauce and steam for 2 hours.
Makes 8 medium cakes.
Very tasty and can be made ahead.

title: mushroom baked omelet
directions: Rinse, pat dry and slice fresh mushrooms or drain canned mushrooms; set aside.
In large skillet, melt 4 tablespoons of butter.
Add onions, green pepper and mushrooms.
Saute for 3 minutes and remove from heat.
In a large bowl, lightly beat eggs with milk, salt, oregano and black pepper.
Stir in sauteed mushrooms.
Pour into buttered 10-inch pie pan or quiche dish (without removing bottom).
Bake at 350° until clear, about 40 minutes.
Cut into wedges and serve with mushroom tomato sauce.

title: fresh orange fudge
directions: Cook like any other fudge.
When cooked to soft ball stage, remove and set aside until cool.
Add nuts; beat until creamy. Pour into buttered pans.

title: m&m's or mayonnaise muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients until moist.
Do not overbeat.
Fill 6 greased muffin cups.
Bake in 350° oven for approximately 20 minutes or until brown.

title: pecan brittle
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients for 8 minutes in uncovered bowl in microwave oven.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Cook 2 minutes. Remove from microwave and add baking soda and spread on greased cookie sheet.
Cool and break apart.

title: mashed potato pie
directions: Place carrot slices around the sides of a greased 9-inch pie pan, standing up around the edge so they touch.
Cover bottom of pan with peas.
Fill pan with mashed potatoes.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and turn upside-down onto plate. Yields 5 to 6 servings.

title: graham streusel cake
directions: Mix crumbs, nuts, brown sugar, cinnamon and margarine. Reserve.
Blend cake mix, water, oil and eggs.
Beat well.
Pour 1/2 of batter into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of crumb mixture.
Spread remaining batter evenly over crumb mixture. Sprinkle with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool.
Drizzle cake with glaze made with powdered sugar and water.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Drain your salmon.
Cut up green pepper and onions fine; add to salmon along with your egg, bread crumbs or cornmeal and seasoning and make into patties.
Fry in deep fat until brown. Drain on paper towels.

title: easy apple dumplings
directions: Mix sugar, water, margarine and cinnamon.
Bring to boil and simmer 5 minutes.
Roll or flatten out can biscuits on floured board.
Fill each with about one heaping tablespoonful chopped apples.
Crimp together with fork to look like a fritter.
Spray pan and place dumplings in baking dish.
Pour syrup over dumplings frequently while baking.
Serve warm.

title: grilled venison and vegetables
directions: In a glass bowl or plastic bag, combine vinegar, honey, soy sauce, ketchup, pepper and garlic powder; set aside 1/4 cup.
Add meat to bowl or bag; stir or shake to coat.
Cover (or close bag) and refrigerate for 4 hours.

title: hot spice punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl. Keep in air tight container.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Stir in beaten egg, water and vanilla which have been beaten until light and foamy.
Sift together dry ingredients; add to top mixture.
Add oatmeal, nuts and butterscotch tips.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Save some grated Cheddar cheese to place on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or prepare at High power in microwave for 12 minutes.

title: barbecued pork
directions: Rub a small amount of fat from meat over bottom of frypan. Add meat and brown well on stove.
Combine all other ingredients and pour over the meat.
Cover; reduce heat to simmer and cook 45 minutes or until meat is tender.
Stir occasionally during cooking.
Serve over rice.

title: lemon loaf cake(the best lemon cake you ever ate)
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water and let cool.
Mix cake mix, oil and eggs (add one at a time to mixture).
Add jello mixture.
Bake in greased loaf pan or a 13 x 11-inch pan at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: all-american baked beans from the new basics
directions: Rinse and pick through beans.
Soak overnight.
Rinse soaked beans under cold water and place in heavy saucepan.
Cover with water and bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until tender, 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Drain, reserving cooking liquid.
Preheat oven to 300°.
In a Dutch oven over medium heat, saute bacon until slightly crisp and fat is rendered, 5 minutes.
Add the onions and garlic and cook over medium-low heat until dissolved, 5 minutes. Then stir in ketchup, syrup, molasses, Worcestershire, salt and pepper.
Add drained beans; mix well.
Cover and bake 2 1/2 hours; stir occasionally.
Add 3/4 cup reserved bean liquid; cover and bake 30 minutes.
Remove cover and bake 10 to 15 minutes until sauce is thick and syrupy.
Stir once.

title: mashed potato filling
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in greased pan or use to stuff foul.

title: shrimp dip
directions: In a saucepan, dissolve gelatin in 1/4 cup water.
Add tomato soup and heat together.
Remove from heat.
In a mixing bowl, cream with mixer the soup-gelatin mixture, cream cheese and salad dressing.
Add onions, bell pepper, celery and shrimp; mix well. Pour into a bowl and refrigerate until congealed.

title: vanilla cream pie
directions: For filling: In medium saucepan, combine sugar, flour or cornstarch and salt.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thick and bubbly.
Reduce heat and cook and stir for 2 minutes more.
Remove from heat.
Separate eggs.
Set whites aside for meringue.
Beat yolks slightly.
Gradually stir 1 cup of hot mix into yolks.
Return egg mixture to saucepan and bring to gentle boil.
Cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Remove from heat and stir in butter and vanilla.

title: easter eggs
directions: Mix sugar and margarine.
Add raisins, salt, coconut, walnuts, fruit and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add enough milk to make workable. Shape into eggs or other forms.
Let them air dry for several hours.

title: chocolate delicious
directions: In 9 x 12-inch pan make crust.
Mix melted margarine, flour and pecans.
Press into pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes until browned.
Let cool.

title: cheesy vegetables
directions: Cook vegetables 2 minutes and drain well.
Blend soup and cheese and heat on low until melted.
Add vegetables and half of croutons.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Cover with the other 1/2 of the croutons the last 10 minutes of baking.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: oreo delight
directions: Break up cookies in dessert pan.
Combine sugar, cream cheese and half Cool Whip.
Mix well and spread over cookies.
Make pudding according to directions on box.
Pour pudding over cream cheese mixture.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and nuts.

title: breakfast raisin bars
directions: Mix all ingredients except raisins.
Fold raisins in last. Pour into loaf pan or square pan that has been sprayed.
Bake at 350° until brown, 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into 8 equal bars.
Each bar counts as 1 bread, 1 fruit, 1/2 milk and 10 calories.

title: kindness cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and blend well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool slightly before removing from cookie sheet onto a flat surface.

title: leek and potato soup
directions: Simmer vegetables and water or stock and salt for 40 minutes. Pass through food mill.
Just before serving, add 1/2 to 1 cup of heavy cream.
Decorate with minced parsley or minced chives.
This soup can be served hot or cold.
When served cold, heavy cream may be replaced with sour cream.

title: oriental spinach salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except bacon in a large salad bowl.
Mix in bacon just before serving so that it stays crispy; top with dressing.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour hot water over oleo and oatmeal and let stand 20 minutes. Mix together remaining ingredients with the oatmeal mixture. Bake at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 minutes (grease and flour pan).

title: jello cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed on package.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes, then poke with fork at 1/2-inch intervals.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cold water and spoon over cake. Chill for 3 to 4 hours.
Top with thawed Cool Whip.

title: no peeking beef stew
directions: Mix together the soup, soup mix and water in a casserole dish. Add beef.
Cover dish; cook at 350° for 3 hours.

title: meat-za-pie
directions: Thoroughly mix hamburger, milk, bread crumbs and garlic salt. Pat evenly over bottom and up sides of 9-inch pie pan.
Spread on ketchup, then Cheddar and Mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle with oregano and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes until meat is done and cheese is browned.

title: kraut salad
directions: Boil vinegar and sugar, let cool.
Pour mixture over chopped ingredients.

title: chicken and gravy
directions: Melt butter in large skillet over medium heat; brown chicken parts about 5 minutes on each side. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Pour 1/2 cup water into skillet; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; simmer partially covered 30 to 35 minutes or until chicken is fork tender and juices run clear, turning once during cooking. Transfer meat to serving platter; keep warm.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions.

Pour 1/2 of batter in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Melt caramels in butter and milk over low heat, stirring constantly. On cake that has baked 15 minutes sprinkle 1 cup nuts, chocolate chips and pour caramel mix over this.
Pour remaining batter and sprinkle with last cup of nuts.
Bake 20 minutes more.

title: instant spiced tea
directions: Add 2 heaping teaspoons to 1 cup of boiling water.

title: peas - purple hull or crowder
directions: Cut bacon into several pieces; place in a heavy boiler and cook until almost done; drain.
If you use ham then put it on in the water and cook for several minutes before adding the peas; do not drain.

Add peas, dash of salt, sugar and water to cover; bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer until peas are tender. After several minutes of cooking taste liquid to see if you need more salt, if so add it now and finish cooking.
Add warm water if needed to keep the peas just covered.

title: dill dip(double batch)
directions: Mix ingredients together and sprinkle in dill weed to taste.

title: italian hamburger bake
directions: Cook meat and onions together until browned.
Stir in soup, cottage cheese and seasonings.
Heat to boiling.
Pour into a 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Add cheese on top.
Cut biscuits in half and arrange on hot mixture.
Bake at 400° until biscuits are done.

title: curry dip(cauliflower dip)
directions: Mix all ingredients together; cover and refrigerate several hours.
Serve with cauliflower and other vegetable dippers.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Melt together the chocolate and margarine over very low heat; cool.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Gradually add sugar to eggs in separate bowl, mixing thoroughly.
Add vanilla and cooled chocolate.
Mix, blending well.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Blend in chopped nuts.

title: reese's peanut butter candy
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together and press in a brownie pan.
Melt chocolate in a double boiler.
When melted, spread on top of peanut butter mixture.
Cut into squares when chocolate sets.

title: cream cheese brownie pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and 1 egg.
Beat until smooth, set aside.	Combine brownie mix, oil, 1 Tbsp. water and 2 eggs.
Beat for 50 strokes with a spoon.
Spread 1/2 c. of brownie mixture on bottom of crust.
Carefully spread cream cheese mixture over brownie layer.
Top with remaining brownie mixture.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 40-50 minutes, or until center is puffed and crust is golden brown.
Warm fudge packet and 1 Tbsp. water in the microwave.
Drizzle over top.	Keep in refrigerator.

title: potato meatballs
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except tomato juice.
Shape into meatballs.
Brown meatballs in skillet, cover with tomato juice and simmer for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter chocolate candy cookies
directions: Mix together peanut butter, margarine, confectioners sugar and cracker crumbs.
Put mixture into a well-greased cookie sheet. Melt chocolate morsels and pour over first mixture.
Refrigerate for 15 minutes.
Remove from refrigerator and slice into 2 x 2-inch squares.
Leave in pan and put back in refrigerator.
Serve cold.

title: sopa
directions: Mix all ingredients except tortillas and cheese.
Layer tortillas and soup mixture in a large casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: smothered steak
directions: Mix together all but water and soup.
Form into balls and fry until brown.
Pour the condensed mushroom soup in pan.
Add water. Add meatballs; simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: festive ham rolls(appetizer)
directions: Clean and trim green onions.
Take 1 slice of ham and spread a thick layer of cream cheese. Lay a green onion at one end of ham, cut to size and roll.
Once you have the long roll, cut into small wheel shapes.
Arrange on a small platter and serve.

title: southern oven fried chicken(heart healthy)
directions: Combine cornflakes, paprika, garlic powder and thyme and put in plastic bag.
Use no-stick cooking spray.
Brush chicken breasts with buttermilk, then put in bag.
Coat chicken.
Place in baking dish.
Cook for 45 minutes or until done at 400°.

title: apple vivian crunch
directions: Mix first five ingredients together and put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour melted butter over first part.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Sprinkle over first part.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: green chile rice casserole
directions: Grease a casserole.
Stir sour cream into rice.
Alternate layers of rice, green chilies and cheese, ending with a layer of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese is bubbly.

title: coney island sauce
directions: Place ingredients in saucepan in order listed.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally until hamburg is crumbled up quite fine.
Turn heat low and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.

title: lemon torte
directions: Crush crackers; add butter.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan. Beat egg whites, cream of tartar and vinegar until soft peaks form. Gradually add the sugar.
Beat until you taste no grains of sugar. Spread on cracker crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until it turns light brown.
Cool.
Spread with lemon filling.
Top with whipped cream.
I sometimes use 1 1/2 recipes for the schaum torte for a higher torte.
This torte refrigerates well for a few days and so good.

title: pizza crust
directions: Knead the ingredients together. Spread out on pizza sheets. Add the following toppings: browned hamburger (drained) or 1/2 venison, onions, green bell peppers, mushrooms, Cheddar cheese, Mozzarella cheese and black olives. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Boil molasses, sugar and milk.
When forms a soft ball in water, take off.
Stir as you add peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme.

title: blue ribbon carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use 2 (9-inch) round pans.
Combine flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Set aside.
Combine eggs, oil, buttermilk, sugar and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Stir in flour mixture, pineapple, carrots, coconut and walnuts.
Pour into layer pans.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Spread with Orange-Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: meat balls and sauce
directions: Mix hamburger meat and next 5 ingredients together and form into meat balls.
Bake at 350° until very light brown.
Mix next 6 ingredients together to make sauce.
Pour over meat balls and continue baking for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: lamb's wool pie
directions: In large bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk, bananas and pecans; mix well.
Add whipped topping; mix well and pour evenly into pie shells.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Refrigerate at least 6 hours before serving.

title: ken and mark's world famous corn and tomato relish
directions: Combine vegetables in a saucepan.
Blend turmeric and a little vinegar; add mustard seed and cumin.
Dissolve sugar and salt in remaining vinegar.
Put all together, pouring over vegetables in saucepan.
Boil, then reduce heat, simmering at least one hour, no more than two.
Adjust seasonings to taste.
Bottle in pint Mason jars.
Makes about 10 pints.

title: josie's texas pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat eggs with sugar and syrup.
Add vanilla, butter and pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: gooey lemon bars
directions: Blend flour, butter and powdered sugar.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
While crust is baking, beat eggs; add sugar, juice and flour.
Pour over baked crust.
Return to oven for 30 minutes at 325°.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix ingredients in order and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: omaha casserole
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; crumble.
Cook ground beef until pink is gone.
Mix meats, onions, beans, catsup, vinegar and mustard. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: all-purpose barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
In slow cooking pot, cook on low 2 to 3 hours.
(Meat can be added last 1 1/2 hours, if desired.)
Good on spareribs, chicken, pork chops, sliced roast beef, etc.

title: escalloped pineapple
directions: Mix and toss butter and bread cubes.
Mix eggs, sugar and flour.
Add pineapple and mix all well.
Put liquid in buttered 2-quart casserole.
Press cubes into it.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Make ahead and refrigerate.
Reheat at 350° for 20 minutes. Wonderful served with ham.
Perfect for a "take along".
It surprises everyone!

title: stuffed potatoes
directions: You may add any meat (chicken or pork) that you'd enjoy.

title: apple or peach strudel
directions: Into bottom of a buttered baking dish, put thick layers of apples (or peaches).
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon, mixed. Dot with lumps of butter.

title: barbecue sauce for chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients. Bring to boil. Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Mix together rhubarb, sugar and pineapple.
Add apple and cook 20 minutes.
Add Jell-O and mix.
Pour into clean hot jars and seal.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers to fill the gallon jars.
(Do not peel cucumbers!)
Slice onions.
Put a layer of onions and then a layer of cucumbers and press down until jar is full.
Pack down very firmly.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over contents of jar. Will keep up to 9 months in refrigerator.

title: festive frozen mint pie
directions: In large bowl, combine Eagle Brand milk, peppermint extract and food coloring.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Turn into crust and cover. Freeze 6 hours or until firm.
Garnish as desired.
Freeze leftovers.

title: skillet cookies
directions: In a large bowl, combine Rice Krispies and pecans.
In a heavy saucepan, combine dates, margarine, sugar, egg and salt.
Bring to a boil for 6 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Pour over Rice Krispies and nuts.
Stir to coat.
When it gets just cool enough to form balls, roll with hands into balls and place on waxed paper.
Roll in coconut.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: For crust, mix pretzels, butter and sugar together in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: cream cheese quiche crust
directions: Mix butter and cheese together with pastry blender.
Add salt and flour.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Fill with quiche fillings and bake according to quiche recipe directions.

title: nut bread
directions: Grind walnuts and raisins.
Add to rest of the ingredients. Put in two loaf pans.
Raise 15 minutes before baking. Bake in a 350° oven for about 1 hour.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: In small amount of water, boil broccoli; just before tender, add salt, pepper and onion.
Do not drain.
Add cheese and melt. Add soup; cook on low heat, stirring frequently.
When thoroughly heated, add milk and continue to stir until heated.
Do not boil.

title: pork chop bean bake
directions: Brown chops in skillet in small amount of fat.
Remove chops from pan.
Pour off drippings.
Blend in soup and thyme.
Stir in beans.
Put mixture in bottom of ovenproof casserole.
Place chops on top of mixture.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes or until chops are tender.
Uncover and cook 5 to 10 minutes more until sauce thickens.
Good with mashed potatoes!

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Steam broccoli to get apart.
Place in bottom of dish.
Add mushroom soup; spoon on Cheddar cheese soup (soup is not diluted). Top with grated cheese.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs mixed with melted butter over top.
Bake 45 minutes or until done at 375°.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Boil pineapple with juice, sugar and flour until thickened. Remove from heat and cool.
After cooled, add nuts.
Cut bananas and place in bottom of pie crusts.
Pour mixture over bananas; top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with coconut.
Makes 2 pies.
Keep refrigerated.

title: potato curry
directions: Saute chopped onion until it is translucent.
Cook potato (chopped) in saucepan.
Add turmeric powder, chili powder and salt to taste.
Remove from the stove.
Garnish with chopped coriander before serving.
Makes 1 serving.

title: baked corn
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Add flour.
Blend well.
Add milk slowly. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add corn and sugar. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Add eggs.
Mix thoroughly. Turn into greased baking dish (1 1/2-quart size).
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: swiss steak
directions: Fry steak. Put in casserole dish. Add onion and peppers; drizzle butter and sprinkle salt. Add soup and cover with water. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes, then at 325° for another 20 minutes.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Mix chili powder, garlic powder, cumin and salt in bowl and set aside. Chop onion and bell pepper and set aside. Cut chicken into cubes. Spray pan and add oil on medium heat. Set timer for 20 minutes. cook chicken cubes for 7 minutes or until no longer pink. Stir often. After cooking chicken for 7 min., add all spices
and stir. Then add onion and pepper. Cook for remaining 13 minutes stirring constantly. Warm tortilla shells in microwave about 1 minute. Spoon mixture in shells and serve.

title: swedish meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: potatoes and onions
directions: Put oil
and bacon in a 12-inch Dutch oven.
Cook until almost done.
Add potatoes and onions.
Sprinkle on plenty of salt and pepper.
Cook
minutes.
Check often and stir as needed. Drain
off	grease.
Sprinkle
cheese over top during the last 5 minutes of cooking.

title: french breakfast puffs
directions: Mix together thoroughly the shortening, sugar and egg.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Add dry ingredients to shortening mixture alternately with 1/2 cup milk. Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake until golden brown at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Immediately roll in 6 tablespoons melted butter, then in mixture of 1/2 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon.
Freezes beautifully.

title: beef bean enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute beef and onions until meat is browned; drain.
Add beans, olives, taco sauce, salt and garlic powder.
Bring to a boil; remove from heat.
In small pan, heat enchilada sauce; pour half the sauce into ungreased 3-quart baking dish.
Dip tortillas in hot oil, one at a time, to soften.
Put 1/3 cup of meat filling on each tortilla; roll to enclose.
Place, seam side down, in dish with sauce.
Pour remaining sauce over tortillas; cover with cheese and bake, uncovered, 20 to 25 minutes until cheese is melted.
Serve with sour cream, salsa and sliced, pitted ripe olives.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Whip the potatoes until light. Add wine, salt, sugar, beaten eggs and butter.
Mix well. Turn into greased baking dish. Sprinkle with nut meats. Bake at 375° for 1/2 hour.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Mix cold water, sugar and cream of tartar.
Bring to boil and cook for 10 minutes.
Add crackers and boil 1 1/2 minutes.
Pour into pastry-lined pie pan; sprinkle with cinnamon.
Dot with margarine and cover with lattice crust.
Bake 25 minutes or until crust is brown at 425°.

title: raisin energy bars
directions: Simmer raisins, water, sugar, starch and salt until thickened. Remove from heat, add extract.
Cool well.
(Can be blended in blender, so it looks like date bar filling.)
Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Combine with brown sugar, oats and nuts.
Mix in shortening.

title: stuffing on pork chops
directions: Brown chops in oil; place in an ungreased 9 x 12-inch pan. Combine soup, celery, onions, egg, pepper and poultry seasoning. Mix well.

title: creamed peas and potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes until tender. Cook peas according to directions. Add the sugar. Melt the butter. Add flour, salt and pepper to form a paste. Gradually stir in milk and boil for 1 minute stirring constantly. Add dill. Cook until thick. Drain peas and potatoes. Pour sauce over and stir to coat.

title: apple-celery-nut salad
directions: Dice apples, celery and nuts.
Place in large bowl.
Mix Miracle Whip, lemon juice, milk and sugar.
Pour on fruit and toss.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: red devils food cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add cocoa.
Add eggs.
Add flour alternately with milk which the soda has been dissolved in.
Add boiling water and vanilla.
Very good moist chocolate cake.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 9 x 13-inch or 2 layers.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1/4 c. of the juice and set aside. In a large bowl sift flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt and set aside.

title: hedda's (coconut) cookies
directions: Crem sugar, shortening, eggs and almond extract.
Add flour and salt; mix well.
Fold in coconut.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 18 minutes, slightly golden around edges.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: cheesy vegetable casserole(microwave)
directions: Melt Cheez Whiz or cheese chunks with 1/4 cup butter in a 1-quart casserole in microwave on Medium-high for about 4 minutes or until melted.
Stir every 1 1/2 minutes.
Add vegetables to casserole and mix.
Melt remaining butter in bowl on High for 30 seconds.
Stir in cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle butter crumbs over casserole.
Microwave at Medium-high, uncovered, for about 10 minutes, rotating 1/2 turn after 5 minutes.
Let stand 2 to 3 minutes before serving.

title: golden mushroom chicken dish
directions: Brown chicken in skillet with 2 teaspoons oil or spray pan with Pam at medium-high heat.
When browned, add carrots and soup. Turn to simmer and cook 15 to 20 minutes.
Add potatoes and cook until soft, about 1/2 hour.
You can remove chicken and debone it at this time.
Add deboned chicken to skillet 15 minutes before end of cooking time.
Stir occasionally to prevent vegetables from sticking.
If chicken dish becomes dry, add 1/2 cup of water. Simmer until finished.

title: crab & wild rice salad
directions: Cook rice according to instructions.
Cool.
Add the dressing after all ingredients are added to container or bowl.
Enjoy!

title: three meat baked beans
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Saute onion in 1 teaspoon butter.
Combine sausage, ground beef and onion with remaining ingredients in lightly greased casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Simmer on low for 45 minutes.

title: spinach salad
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients in jar. Cover tightly. Shake until well mixed. Set aside.
Tear spinach to bite size pieces and place in a large salad bowl.
Just before serving, pour dressing over spinach and toss. Garnish with crumbled bacon and egg slices.

title: play doh
directions: Mix dry ingredients in bowl.
Boil water and oil.
Pour into dry ingredients and mix quickly.
Let cool.
Knead.
Store in Ziploc bags.

title: zucchini-mushroom bake
directions: Cook bacon until done and drain on paper towel.
Get a skillet and put 1/2 inch of water in it.
Cook zucchini in water until it softens.
Stir in mushrooms, tomato, salt, pepper and oregano. Cook until vegetables are tender, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Stir and sprinkle with crumbled bacon before serving.

title: no-cook cheesecake cupcakes
directions: Line muffin cups with cupcake liners.
Dissolve the gelatin in the boiling water in a mixing bowl.
Stir well.
Cut the cheese into small pieces and place in the dissolved gelatin.
Add the vanilla and the sweetener and beat well with an electric mixer. Pour into the prepared muffin cups.
Chill until firm, about 2 hours.
(Add 6 sweeteners and a chocolate square for chocolate cheesecake.)

title: dirt pudding
directions: Crush Oreos and spread half in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Save other half for top.
With mixer, mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Set aside.
In another bowl, mix milk and pudding. Combine pudding and Cool Whip mixture, spread on top of cookies and put the rest of cookies on top.

title: spinach omelet
directions: Pour beaten eggs in a hot pan sprayed with nonfat spray. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cook until dry around outer edge. Cover with onion, spinach and cheese. Fold omelet and cook an additional 2 minutes or until egg is done and cheese melted.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients except chips or cornflakes and place in a well-greased baking dish (2-quart).
Top with chips or cornflakes.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: swiss cheese bread
directions: Trim top and side crusts from bread, leaving bottom crust intact.
Make diagonal cuts, 1-inch thick, through the bread, but not through bottom.
Combine all remaining ingredients.
Spread half the butter mixture between bread slices.
Use remaining mixture to frost top and sides of bread.
Place bread in foil boat; cover loosely with another sheet of foil.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Uncover for the last 5 minutes.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix egg yolks, flour, sugar and milk; cook until comes to a boil and thickens.
Add vanilla flavoring and pineapple.
Stir until mixed.
Pour in a baked pie shell and top with meringue. Brown.

title: creamy cucumber salad
directions: Peel cucumbers and slice thin; slice onions and separate into rings.
In small mixing bowl, blend mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar until smooth and creamy.
Pour over cucumbers and onions.
Toss. Cover bowl with Alcan plastic wrap and place in refrigerator at least 2 hours before serving.

title: curried four-fruit bake
directions: Drain fruit and dry.
Add other ingredients and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: mushroom pasta scampi
directions: Cook linguine according to package directions.
Drain, reserving 1/2 cup pasta water; set aside.
Meanwhile, heat olive oil in large skillet.
Add mushrooms and garlic; cook and stir about 5 minutes or until tender and mushroom liquid is almost evaporated.
Add shrimp; cover and cook about 5 minutes or until shrimp is almost cooked through.
Stir in spinach and reserved 1/2 cup pasta water.
Cover and cook about 1 minute or until spinach is wilted.
Place pasta in serving bowl; stir in mushroom and shrimp mixture, Parmesan cheese and red pepper.
Toss to combine.
Season with salt, if desired.

title: pickled asparagus
directions: Wash asparagus.
Cut in spears; 4-inch pints or 6-inch quarts. Combine water, vinegar and salt to a boil.
Blanch asparagus in boiling water for 2 minutes.
Cool in ice water for 2 minutes. Pack asparagus in jars, tip ends down.
Add one clove garlic, 1/4 teaspoon sugar and 1/8 teaspoon dill.
Cover with boiling brine to within 1/2-inch of top of jar.
Adjust lids and process in boiling water bath for 10 minutes.

title: anniversary pound cake
directions: Grease and flour bottom of a 10-inch tube pan. Cream the butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Sift flour and salt into baking powder and cocoa. Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk and vanilla, beating after each addition.
Pour in pan.
Bake at 325° for
1 hour to 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Cool in pan 5 minutes.

title: death by chocolate
directions: The night before serving, cut cake in half and pour Kahlua and freeze.
Smash candy to bits and freeze.
Prepare mousse according to directions on box.

title: sour cream apple squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In large bowl, combine first 3 ingredients; blend at low speed until crumbly. Stir in nuts. Press 2 3/4 cups crumb mixture into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: cheese ball
directions: Use 1/2 cup pecans in cheese ball.
Roll ball in other half. Prepare a day ahead.
Set at room temperature for several hours before serving.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Spray 9-inch pie plate with oil.
Place all ingredients in blender in order.
Blend until smooth.
Pour in pie plate. Sprinkle with topping.

title: impossible pie
directions: Beat eggs well and add remaining ingredients.
Pour into 2 well-greased and floured pie pans.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: my mom's broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Add to cooked rice.
Saute onion in butter (or margarine).
Mix onions, balance of butter from saute and cheese (3/4 cup) to broccoli rice mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for abut 20 minutes.
If prepared the day before, bake 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: jewel's famous eggnog
directions: Separate 1 egg per person.
Add 1 extra for the bowl.
Add 1 tablespoon of sugar per egg yolk and beat together.
Add 1 tablespoon bourbon for each plus one for the bowl.
Beat the egg whites separately and stir into the mixture.
Add 1/2 pint whipped cream and fold into mixture.

title: chicken cheese roll-ups
directions: Place equal portions of chicken on each piece of crescent roll.
Roll up with chicken inside.
Place in sprayed baking pan. Sprinkle cheese over rolls.
Combine soup with milk and pour over top of rolls.
Bake at 375° until browned on top, approximately 30 to 40 minutes.

title: party sausage
directions: Cut and brown sausage.
Blend cornstarch and water.
Combine with 1/2 cup pineapple syrup, Karo, vinegar and salt in skillet. Bring to boil; simmer 5 minutes.
Add all other ingredients.
Heat and serve.

title: electric skillet meal(sausage and limas)
directions: Set dial at medium and cook until golden brown the butter, onions and celery.
Push vegetables to 1 side of skillet and brown sausage.
Add limas.
Cook until tender, about 8 minutes.
Add tomato juice, brown sugar, salt and pepper.
Cook for several minutes, then serve.

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: Brown beef in hot oil.
Stir in both cans of soup.
Simmer for 1 hour or until tender.
Stir in container of sour cream and mushrooms.
Serve over noodles.

title: uncle walt's whole wheat bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add milk and softened margarine.
Mix well.
Add 2 cups whole wheat flour and beaten egg.
Mix well.
Add rest of flour gradually.
Knead on a floured board for 5 minutes or so.
Put in a greased bowl; let rise until doubled in size.
Punch down and divide in half.
Knead again. Place in a greased pan and let rise until even with top of pan. Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and bake in oven for 6 minutes at 400°.
Let cool completely.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip together and spread over crust.
Let jello, strawberries and boiling water cool for a few minutes and pour on top of Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: bagels
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cups flour, 3 tablespoons sugar, 1 tablespoon salt and yeast.
Heat 1 1/2 cups water and margarine to 120° to 130°. Add to yeast mixture.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Add 1/2 cup flour; beat at high speed 2 minutes.
Add enough flour to make a stiff dough.

title: hobo soup
directions: Brown and drain beef.
In a large stock pot add beef and all other ingredients.
Cook on low heat for 1 hour.
If soup is too thick, add water.

title: new england chicken
directions: Mix ingredients
and
dip chicken.
Cover sour cream on both sides of chicken
and bake in covered dish at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Boil first 2 ingredients until a hard boil, then boil 10 minutes more.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Grease pan with butter.
Pour in candy mixture.
Cut in squares.

title: star-kist tuna casserole
directions: Saute onions and pepper in butter or margarine.
Cook noodles in boiling salted water for 10 minutes, or until tender; drain. Add salt and pepper to mushroom soup.
In greased 2-quart casserole, put half the noodles.
Cover with half the mushroom soup, half the onion mixture, half tomatoes and half can tuna, plus peas.
Repeat the layers.
Sprinkle with herb seasoning.
Top with potato chips.
Bake in a 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes, or bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: creole sauce
directions: Melt butter in medium saucepan.
Cook green pepper, onion and garlic until limp.
Stir in tomato puree and mushrooms; simmer 25 to 30 minutes.
May be served on meat balls or with cooked rice.

title: hot beef dip
directions: Chop beef in food processor.
Add cream cheese, sour cream, garlic powder and Worcestershire sauce.
Blend until creamy.
Put in pie pan and top with chopped pecans.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Serve with Melba toast.

title: peanut soup
directions: Saute onions and celery in butter until tender.
Add flour. Stir until smooth.
Add chicken broth; bring to a boil and add peanut butter, celery salt, salt, pepper and lemon juice.
Heat to simmer.
Serve and sprinkle with chopped peanuts.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Precook broccoli and drain, saving a little of the cooking liquid.
Put broccoli in a shallow casserole.
Mix soup and mayonnaise with a little broccoli cooking liquid.
Pour over broccoli; sprinkle with either grated Cheddar or Parmesan cheese. Spread crushed cracker crumbs on top of cheese.
Top with crumbled onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut each biscuit into quarters.
Roll in 3/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon until well coated.
Drop into greased pan.
Boil 1 cup sugar and cinnamon; add 1 cup butter.
Pour over biscuits.
Sprinkle with crushed nuts. Bake 50 minutes and place on large cake plate.

title: vanilla pudding
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt together in 1-quart casserole. Add milk gradually, stirring constantly.
Cook 5 to 6 minutes on High power, stirring every minute.
Stir in vanilla.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: beet relish
directions: Put the beets and cabbage through the food chopper and add other ingredients in the order given.
Let stand at least 24 hours before using.
This relish will keep well in a covered crock with a little salad oil poured over it.

title: pheasant stew
directions: Stew pheasants until tender.
Add chopped carrots, turnips, onions, potatoes, mushrooms and parsley.
Add water, if necessary, to make about 1 quart of stock.
When veggies are tender.
Serve at once.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Chop onion.
Brown beef and onion.
Drain.
Put in casserole dish.
Mix ketchup and water; pour over beef.
Cut potatoes into 1/4-inch slices.
Layer on beef and top with cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.

title: cold spaghetti salad
directions: For every pound of pasta, use 1 pepper and 1 tomato.
Cook pasta and drain.
Mix green peppers and tomatoes (diced small), 3/4 jar of Salad Supreme and the whole bottle of Italian dressing. Chill for 3 to 4 hours.

title: pesto pasta
directions: If desired, you can roast the garlic before crushing by placing a small amount of olive oil on a piece of foil with the garlic and baking at 425 for 10 - 15 minutes. Cook pasta according to package directions. In a food processor or blender place the basil, tomato and garlic. It blends easier if you put half the tomato in first and then the garlic and basil. Put the second half of tomato in last. Add a pinch of salt and some fresh pepper and blend. Add olive oil to blender one tablespoon at a time until pesto sauce is smooth in consistency, not more than six tablespoons. Add salt and pepper to taste. Pour pesto sauce and 1/4 c. grated cheese to drained pasta and toss. Top individual servings with additional grated cheese. Serve with warm French bread.

title: chicken and peppers
directions: About 75 minutes before serving, remove bones from chicken breasts.
Cut each breast in half.
In 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat in hot salad oil, cook chicken until lightly browned.
Arrange chicken breast, skin side up, in 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In drippings remaining in skillet over medium-high heat, cook green peppers, onion and mushrooms until peppers and onion are tender-crisp and lightly browned, stirring frequently.
Add tomatoes with their liquid and remaining ingredients.
Over high heat, heat to boiling.
Pour tomato mixture over chicken breasts.
Bake casserole uncovered 20 to 30 minutes until chicken is fork-tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Stir together the buttermilk and oats.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Stir together both flours, soda, cinnamon and salt and set aside.
Beat egg, sugar, oil and vanilla into oat mixture.
Stir in flour mixture just until blended.
Cook on griddle.

title: beef-cheese enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add refried beans, 1/2 sour cream and taco seasoning.
Stir until well mixed.
In a large saucepan, heat soup, milk, chiles and cheese.
Spread meat mixture on shells and roll up.
Pour sauce over enchiladas.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: spenatsoppa(spinach soup)
directions: Combine the soup, milk and boiling water in a large pan in which you have already dissolved the bouillon cubes.
Chop the spinach finely in a blender or food processor, taking care not to puree.
(You may wish to use some of your liquid with the spinach in order not to puree the spinach.)
Add the spinach to the pan and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add the salt and pepper.
Garnish with the chopped parsley and eggs.

title: millet stew
directions: In large skillet, beginning with potatoes, alternate layers of fish and potatoes.
Place whole pepper pods through layers.
(For spicier dish, chopped peppers are stronger.)
Divide shortening into three spoonfuls and place at edge of pan.
Fill skillet to top of mixture.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat to simmer and cook, covered, for about 1 hour.
When potatoes are soft, you're done. Serve with rice.

title: apple walnut cake
directions: Mix apples, sugar and eggs together and let stand.
Mix remaining ingredients and add to apple mixture.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with ice cream.

title: southern corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Beat the eggs well, combine with corn. Mix flour, sugar, salt and pepper, then add to corn mixture. Stir in butter and cream, mixing well. Pour into a greased 2 quart casserole. Bake for about an hour, or until firm and golden brown. Great served with ham. Yield: 6 servings.

title: cabbage bundles
directions: Remove 8 to 10 leaves from cabbage and immerse into boiling water for 2 minutes.
Drain.
Combine meats, salt, pepper, catsup, onion, egg and rice; mix thoroughly.
Spoon mixture into each leaf; roll and fasten with toothpick.
Place in tightly covered pan. Dissolve bouillon cube in hot water; pour over cabbage rolls. Cover.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: eggplant au gratin
directions: Boil eggplant in small amount of water after peeling.
Fry onion in bacon fat.
Add tomatoes, eggplant, crumbs and eggs; mix well.
Grease casserole; add mixture.
Top with cracker crumbs or bread crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: molasses cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil; add eggs and milk.
Then add nutmeg, cinnamon and flour.
Grease and flour 11 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in casserole which has been buttered and bread crumbs spread over bottom.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
(Serve over rice which can be cooked in tightly covered ovenproof container in oven at the same time to conserve energy.)
Serves 4 to 6.

title: microwave chocolate sauce
directions: In medium microwave-safe bowl, place chocolate and butter. Microwave at High, 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until chocolate is melted and mixture is smooth when stirred.
Add sugar, evaporated milk and salt.
Blend well.
Microwave at High, 2 to 3 minutes, stirring with wire whisk after each minute or until mixture is smooth and hot.
Stir in vanilla.
Serve warm over ice cream or other desserts.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups sauce.

title: french dressing
directions: Beat mixture well.
Blender or food processor works well.

title: nutritious steamed vegetables
directions: Using a steamer or steamer basket with a Dutch oven, heat 2 cups of water until boiling.
Place whole potatoes in steamer. Steam for 10 minutes; then add squash and broccoli.
Steam and additional 5 to 10 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: "twice baked potatoes"
directions: Slice potatoes in half. Scoop out insides. In large bowl, mix potato insides, sour cream, Parmesan cheese, bacon, horseradish, salt and pepper. Spoon into potato skins. Top each with 1 teaspoon butter. Divide sharp cheese and place on top of each potato. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: grandma's soup
directions: Cut short ribs into 2-inch cubes.
Put in 12-quart pan with 20 cups water.
Using food processor, process carrots and celery into small chunks.

Process onion and cabbage to a finer consistency. Add to meat and water with 8 ounce can tomato sauce and spices. Bring to a boil, then turn down heat and simmer until meat is tender, about 4 to 5 hours.
Add noodles; cook according to directions on package.
Add more water if needed.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash and drain broccoli; cut into small flowers.
Peel stem. Cut into small strips.
Fry bacon and crumble into small pieces. Combine everything and toss.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni.
Combine eggs, sugar, mustard and vinegar.
Mix well.
Microwave 1 1/2 to 2
minutes on Medium-high.
Stir. Continue to microwave and stir at 30 second intervals until thick. Add Miracle Whip and celery seed.
Combine sauce with cooked macaroni and mix well.
Cool before serving.

title: pineapple cheesecake
directions: Mix cracker crumbs and butter; press into bottom of an 8-inch square pan and chill.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water and cool. Blend cottage cheese and sugar with mixer or fork.
Slowly add to gelatin and mix well.
Pour the mixture into crust and chill until firm.
Stir cornstarch and tablespoon of water in a saucepan until smooth.
Blend pineapple and its juice into constarch mixture and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cool 15 minutes.
Spread cooled pineapple mixture over cheesecake and chill 1 hour or more. Makes 12 servings.

title: divinity
directions: Mix sugar, salt, corn syrup and water in saucepan over low heat. Stir until dissolved, then cook to 252°. While cooking, beat white of egg until stiff. Pour syrup slowly into the egg white, beating all the time. Add vanilla just before candy looses its gloss. When it has lost the gloss, drop from teaspoon onto wax paper.

title: homemade noodles
directions: In a mixing bowl combine egg, milk and salt.
Stir in enough of the flour to make a stiff dough.
Cover and let rest for 10 minutes.

title: peppermint patties
directions: Cream the butter and sugar, adding flavoring.
Cream thoroughly until a firm ball forms.
Shape into balls.
Flatten to form patties.
Melt chocolate and paraffin; dip each patty into mixture.
Lay patties on waxed paper.
Add a walnut half to each piece.
Store in refrigerator.
Yields 25 to 30 pieces.

title: refrigerator buns
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Stir in sugar, salt, shortening, and egg.
Add flour and mix well.
Place in greased bowel, and cover with wet towel.
Put in refrigerator for at least 1 hour. Shape into buns (small, medium, or large).
Let rise 2 hours. Bake 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Can also make into dinner rolls. Shape and put in a 9x13 pan.

title: reuben dip
directions: Mix together, heat & serve on cocktail rye bread or rye crackers.

title: italian love cake
directions: Mix cake mix.
In a bowl, blend until smooth the Ricotta cheese, eggs, vanilla and sugar.
Pour mixture on top of cake mix. Bake 1 hour at 350° in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Blend together chocolate pudding and milk.
When thick, fold in 8 ounces Cool Whip.
Spread on cake after cake is very cold.

title: tortellini soup
directions: Saute garlic in butter; add broth and bring to a boil.
Add tortellini and cook al dente.
Add cheese, tomatoes and spinach to tortellini and chicken broth.
Cook until spinach wilts, then add basil, salt and pepper.
Serve immediately.

title: buttermilk scone for two
directions: In a bowl combine flour, 1 1/2 tablespoons of sugar, baking powder and soda.
Add butter. Rub with your fingers to form fine crumbs. Stir in currants and peel.

title: irish bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, milk and flour sifted with baking powder and salt.
Mix alternately, then add the raisins.
Sprinkle top with sugar.
Bake in floured and greased loaf pan for 1 hour.
Test for doneness.
May take a little longer.
Remove from oven; brush top with butter.
Remove from pan.
Cool 10 minutes on rack.

title: sloppy joes
directions: In skillet, brown meat with pepper and onion; pour off fat. Add remaining ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve on buns.

title: bread pudding
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients into a large bowl.
Blend in pieces of bread, mixing well.
Pour mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until set.
Do not overcook.
I like to use day old bread or hot dog buns for this recipe.

title: chili dip
directions: Melt cheese in small crock-pot or microwave until softened. Add chili and heat, mixing well.
Add other ingredients; mix well. Heat as desired.
Serve with chips.

title: banana nut muffins
directions: Spray 12 (2 1/2-inch) or 6 (3-inch) muffin cups with cooking spray.
In medium bowl, combine cereal, bananas, egg whites, milk and oil.
Let stand 5 minutes.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar and baking powder.
Add cereal mixture to flour mixture, stirring just until moistened.
Spoon into prepared muffin cups. Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake in 400° oven about 20 minutes or until lightly browned and firm to touch.
Serve warm with Mazola margarine.
Makes 12 standard or 6 large muffins.

title: homestyle beef stew
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, combine all ingredients and simmer until heated through.
(Optional:
thicken stew by mixing 2 tablespoons cornstarch with 1/4 cup cold water, then add mixture to heated stew.)
Stir until thickened.
Serve over hot rice or egg noodles.
Serves 3 to 5.

title: pag's new england boiled dinner
directions: Put brisket in a 5-quart Dutch pan and cover with water.
Bring brisket to a boil; lower heat and simmer 2 1/2 hours on stove.
The last 20 minutes of cooking time for the brisket, add the vegetables that have been washed, peeled and cut up.
Place them in the pan and cook until desired doneness.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: This should be sticky to form a ball.
Place a large marshmallow in the center.
Don't let it show.
Roll in corn flake crumbs and fry until brown.
This compliments any dish and it is so easy to fix.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly.
Add egg yolks one at a time.
Add soda to flour.
Alternately, add flour and sour cream to creamed mixture.
Beat egg whites stiff and fold into mixture. Don't add any flavoring.
Bake in large tube pan, which has been heavily greased and lined on bottom with brown paper, also greased.
Then flour pan carefully.
Bake at 275° for 2 hours. Turn out immediately.

title: supper nachos
directions: Spread beans on bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Brown hamburger with onion, salt, pepper and garlic; drain.
Spread on top of bean layer, then distribute Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Allow to cool 5 minutes.
Spread on sour cream.
Serve with chips.

title: cream puffs
directions: Melt oleo in boiling water.
Add flour and salt all at once. Stir vigorously. Cook and stir until mixture forms a ball that doesn't separate.
Remove from heat. Cool slightly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each until smooth.
Drop by heaping tablespoonfuls 3-inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° until golden brown and puffy (about 30 minutes).
Remove from oven and split.
Cool on rack.
Fill inside with pudding.
Place top on it and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Makes 10.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chocolate chips, peanut butter and margarine.
Pour over Crispix.
Mix until well coated.
Put powdered sugar in a bag and add cereal mixture.
Shake until all coated.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix egg yolks and lemon juice together.
Cook sugar and hot water together until it becomes clear and add to the other ingredients.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Brown the onion and celery in butter in a heavy skillet. Combine with bread cubes, corn bread and seasonings.
Pour on the broth and stir lightly to blend.
Stuff fowl and roast according to weight of bird.
If desired bake dressing in the oven.
Heat oven to 350°.
With hands, shape dressing into pones or balls and place in baking pan.
Cover and bake 20 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 more minutes.

title: star croutons
directions: You will need 1 tiny star shaped cutter, 1-inch.

title: kahlua coffee
directions: Put in blender.
Add more ice cream to thicken.
Serve in martini glasses with light sprinkle nutmeg.

title: iceberg dill pickles
directions: Drain pickles and soak in ice water for 2 hours.
Drain on several
layers
paper.
Slice pickles in half lengthwise, then slice
into
3/4-inch pieces.
While soaking, mix sugar, vinegar, spice and garlic.
Pour over pickles and let stand 5 days.	Stir each
day.	Put in jars and seal.
Use plastic or enamel pans.

title: beef enchiladas with salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: swiss steak
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper together.
Pound this mixture into the Swiss steak on both sides.
Fry the steak in a skillet with about 1/2-inch oil in it until crisp or shorter time if in a hurry on both sides.
Place steak in bottom of ovenproof pan.
On each piece of steak, place a slice of onion and about 1 tablespoon ketchup.
Pour tomato sauce in plastic bowl and add 8 ounces more of water.
Stir and pour down the side of your steak pan.
You may add green pepper between the steak layers.
Bake at least 1 hour at 350°.
The longer you bake it, the more tender it becomes.

title: broccoli parmesan
directions: Saute' chopped onions in butter.
Add salt, flour, bouillon cube and milk to make a white sauce.
When thick, add 1/2 c. Parmesan Cheese.
Pour over broccoli that has been cooked, but not mushy.
Dot with butter, remaining cheese and paprika.

title: delicious pancakes
directions: Beat egg whites separately.
Mix all ingredients except egg whites until smooth.
Fold in whites.
Grease heated griddle with butter. Turn pancakes as soon as they are puffed and full of bubbles.

title: seasoned toasted pecans
directions: In heavy skillet melt margarine.
Stir in pecan halves until well coated.
Sprinkle seasoned salt over pecans.
Stir well. Pour on cookie sheet and bake at 325° about 30 minutes or until toasted.
Stir often while baking.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix together in casserole dish, 3-quart size.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cinnamon cake
directions: Mix all together and beat on medium speed for 4 minutes. Prepare cinnamon mix by combining the following in a small bowl: 1/4 cup sugar, 2 teaspoons cinnamon and 3/4 cups chopped pecans.

title: key lime pound cake
directions: Combine butter and cream cheese in large bowl.
Beat until blended. Add sugar and beat well. Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Combine the all-purpose flour with the self-rising flour. Stir to mix.
Add to the creamed mixture alternately with the Key Lime juice.
Stir in the extracts and coconut.

title: heavenly hash
directions: In a heavy saucepan, warm Eagle Brand milk warm to touch.
Add chocolate chips.
Stir constantly until melted.
Add marshmallows and nuts.
Stir until marshmallows start to break down.
Pour in 13 x 9-inch wax paper-lined cake pan.
Chill 2 hours.
Turn firm hash onto cutting board.
Peel off paper.
Cut into squares.
Store loosely covered in refrigerator.
Makes about 2 pounds.

title: cheese dip
directions: Combine ingredients in a saucepan; stir over low heat until cheese spread is melted.
Serve warm with chips or fresh vegetables.
Makes 2 1/2 cups dip.

title: garden chicken rolls
directions: With flat edge of meat hammer, pound chicken breast halves between sheets of plastic wrap to 1/8 to 1/4-inch thickness. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cut zucchini and sweet pepper lengthwise into 1/4-inch thick sticks.
Place several vegetable sticks at one end of each flattened breast.
Roll up and secure with wooden picks.
Brown rolls in butter in large skillet with mushrooms.
Add wine and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.
Remove rolls and simmer to reduce sauce, about 3 minutes.
Pour over chicken rolls.
Can serve on bed of rice of your choice.

title: blueberry-pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Stir in pineapple with juice and pie filling.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch dish and chill until firm.
Blend cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and vanilla. Stir in pecans.
Spread over congealed mixture.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Cook green pepper and celery in butter until tender, but not brown.
Blend in soup and mix well.
Add mushrooms and remaining ingredients; season to taste.
Heat.
Serve over rice or toast. Serves 6.

title: broccoli and rigatoni
directions: In a frying pan or saucepan, brown garlic in oil.
Cut up broccoli into small pieces; add to oil.
Fill with water until almost covered.
Add salt and pepper.
Cover; simmer until broccoli is soft.
Smash with fork.

title: nannie's cream puffs
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
In medium saucepan, heat water and butter to a rolling boil.
Over low heat stir in flour vigorously until mixture forms a ball (about 1 minute).
Remove from burner.
Beat eggs in, one at a time, until smooth.
Drop onto ungreased baking sheet, forming at least 8 mounds.
Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and continue baking for 25 minutes until golden brown. Allow to cool slowly, away from drafts.
Remove soft dough from center and fill with fresh fruit and whipped cream, or with custard and topped with chocolate icing.
Serves 8.

title: chicken-cashew casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Add soup and broth and season with soy sauce, pepper and hot pepper.
Add chicken and simmer.
Pour into casserole and sprinkle with noodles and nuts. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: spicy harvest punch
directions: Combine ingredients. Chill. Serves 6 to 8.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and onions in skillet, stirring until crumbly.
Pour off drippings.
Add Ragu sauce, mixing well and simmering.

title: bed and breakfast egg casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease (Pam is good) a 7 x 11-inch pan. Brown and drain sausage well.
Cut bread into 1-inch cubes.
Layer bread, cheese and sausage twice.
Mix the remaining ingredients and pour over the sausage layers.
Bake covered for 35 minutes.
Remove cover and continue baking for 15 more minutes until firm.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients, except oil, together.
Make patties out of mixture.
Heat oil to 400°.
Fry patties until crisp and golden.
Drain on absorbent paper.

title: brownie cake
directions: Heat oven at 350°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Spread in a greased 8 x 1 1/2-inch pan.
Bake 35 minutes or until top appears dry.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool completely.
Put topping onto brownie.

title: pepper hash
directions: Chop
peppers,	apples	and onions.
Cover with boiling water and let stand 5 minutes.
Drain.
Add vinegar, sugar and salt. Boil
until
transparent
(about 20 minutes).
Put into hot jars and seal immediately.

title: almond meringue cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add powdered milk.
Mix well. Add extracts and Equal.
Spoon drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 275° for 45 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet and dust with cinnamon.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Take chicken, cut into strips and place in egg wash.
Let soak in egg wash.
Mix bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese in large bowl. Take 3 chicken strips in bread crumb mixture and bread them on all sides.
After you have breaded all chicken strips, place them on a flat cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: squash dressing
directions: Prepare cornbread as directed on package.
Peel squash and slice into 1/4 inch slices.
Boil until tender.
Saute onion, celery and bell pepper in butter until tender-crisp.
Crumble cornbread in pan.
Add cream of chicken soup, sauteed vegetables and squash.
Add milk until desired consistency.
Pour into baking dish and bake in 350° oven 25 to 30 minutes.

title: teresa's dinner rolls
directions: Combine all ingredients and spoon into muffin pan (about 1/2 cupful) and bake at 400° until brown.
(Very good and very easy.)

title: raspberry luscious gelatin salad
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine jello and unflavored gelatin. Pour boiling water over mixture; stir until dissolved.
Add cold water, then pineapple, bananas and raspberries.
Stir.
Pour half of gelatin mixture into glass serving bowl or 13-inch baking dish. Chill until firm.
