(Let remaining half sit at room temperature.) When gelatin is firm, spread sour cream evenly on top, then carefully pour remaining mixture over the sour cream.
Chill until firm.
Yield:
16 servings.
This is a good salad for diabetics.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine butter, sugar, vanilla and salt. Add eggs, beating well. Blend in syrup and pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Arrange additional pecan halves over top for decoration, if desired. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Fry bacon, drain and then crumble.
Preheat oven to 425°. Spread crumbled bacon into pie crust.
With wire whisk, beat eggs, cream, salt and nutmeg.
Stir in cheese.
Pour egg mixture into crust.
Bake 15 minutes, then turn oven control to 325° and bake an additional 35 minutes.

title: dutch apple pie
directions: Brush bottom and sides of crust evenly with egg yolk.
Bake on baking sheet until light brown (5 minutes).
Combine apples, lemon juice, 1/2 cup sugar, 1/4 cup brown sugar, 3 tablespoons flour, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix and spoon into crust.
Mix remaining flour, sugar, brown sugar and butter with pastry blender until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples and bake until bubbly, about 50 minutes.
Cool.

title: pizza puff
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Put stuffing mix into 12 x 18-inch baking dish; set aside.
Mix cheese, pepperoni and mushrooms.
Spoon over mix.
Beat the eggs, flour and milk.
Pour over mixture.
Bake 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Serve with heated pizza sauce.
Serves 6.

title: pizza snacks
directions: Cook Italian sausage, hot sausage, onion and green pepper. Drain well. Return meat mixture to skillet and add seasonings. Heat gently over low heat.
Stir in cheese until melted. Remove from heat.
Spread a scant tablespoon of meat mixture on each bread slice.
Place slice in a single layer on a large baking sheet.
Freeze; store in plastic bags.

title: jumbo raisin cookies
directions: Simmer raisins and water for 5 minutes.
Cream sugar and butter or margarine.
Add eggs and mix well.
In a separate bowl, stir together dry ingredients.
Add sugar-butter-egg mixture to dry ingredients and mix well.
Add vanilla and nuts or coconut. Add raisins and water.
Mix together well.
Drop by teaspoonful onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350 degrees for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: microwave chocolate chip bars
directions: Combine butter, egg, vanilla and brown sugar; mix well. Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix with butter mixture. Add chocolate chips.
Pour into a greased square glass pan and microwave 5 minutes.
Time may differ with microwaves.
Frost, if desired.

title: chocolate chip bundt cake
directions: Mix ingredients with electric mixer for seven minutes! Pour into greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 65 minutes.
Cake is done when toothpick comes out clean.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all together and spread in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan which has been greased and floured.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: evelyn's pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add flavoring; add 1 egg at a time and beat until smooth.
Bake in ungreased pan.
Put wax paper in bottom. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Put chicken breasts and broccoli in baking dish.
Combine other ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: skewered grilled potatoes
directions: Microwave potatoes and water in covered casserole dish on High for 12 minutes (stir at 8 minutes). Drain potatoes. In medium bowl, mix remaining ingredients. Add potatoes and refrigerate 1 hour.
Drain potatoes and reserve juice.
Skewer and grill for 8 to 10 minutes, rotating and basting with reserved juice.

title: bulgogi(korean barbecued beef)
directions: Cut steak in 1/4-inch thick strips.
Mix next 8 ingredients. Marinate at least 2 hours (12 to 24 hours is even better!).
Grill (much better!) or pan-fry.
Sprinkle with sesame oil just before serving.
Substitute chicken breast for steak and chicken bouillon for beef for a great variation.
This marinade also is great for deer meat.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix first three ingredients with most of the vanilla wafers. Pour into crust.
Top with remaining crushed wafers.
Serve chilled.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients with electric mixer until well blended. Form a ball and roll in chipped beef, nuts or both.
Refrigerate to set up.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and peanuts; stir in margarine and mix well.
Press mixture firmly and evenly into 9-inch pie plate. Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Mix all icing ingredients.
Blend until creamy smooth.

title: old fashioned mashed potatoes
directions: Peel and cut potatoes into eighths.
Finely chop onion.
Cook potatoes and onion in boiling water to cover for 15 minutes, or until tender.
Drain and mash.
Add 1/2 cup milk and remaining ingredients.
Add more milk, if needed, for desired consistency.

title: punch
directions: Heat water and sugar to boil.
Cool.
Cool tea; chill juices and then combine.

title: beef rice-a-roni
directions: Brown ground beef. Cook Rice-A-Roni as directions call on box. When rice is done, add the ground beef to the rice.
Simmer for 20 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Cake:
Mix and beat 2 or 3 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: polish stuffed cabbage
directions: Take 1 cabbage leaf.
Put in a good scoop meat mixture.
Roll and put in layers. In baking pan, pour soup over rolls.
Either bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or cook on top of stove for 2 hours.

title: picadillo(serve with black beans and rice)
directions: Saute onions, garlic and green pepper in 2 to 3 tablespoons of olive oil.
Add tomato sauce and meat and mix well.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally.
Add raisins and olives last.
Serve with black beans and rice.

title: microwave dipped chocolate treats
directions: In 2-cup glass measuring cup, melt 1/2 pound chocolate on High until shiny.
Stir until smooth.
For easier dipping, you can stir in 1 to 2 teaspoons salad oil.

title: snack crackers
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Add crackers; toss lightly every now and then for 1 hour.
Bake at 200° for 10 minutes.
Serve. May be heated in the microwave for a few seconds before serving.

title: spiced cucumbers
directions: Bring vinegar, sugar and spices to a simmer.
Pour over cucumbers and onions.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: "more"
directions: Cook ground beef and onions together until browned.
Set aside.
Mix all remaining ingredients (except the cheese) together.
In a baking dish, layer 1 row of noodles, adding half of the ingredients over top.
Then add another layer of noodles and the rest of the remaining ingredients.
Cover with the Velveeta cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: apple nut squares
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine and blend eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla.
Sift together flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Stir into egg mixture.
Mix well.
Bake in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 325° for 1 hour.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: chicken in foil
directions: Cut two 15 x 12-inch pieces of heavy-duty foil; place a chicken breast in center of each.
Top with onion and remaining ingredients.
Wrap well; place on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 2.

title: my version of chicken divan
directions: Simmer chicken in water for 20 minutes.
Cool, then slice each breast into 4 to 5 pieces.
Arrange raw broccoli in bottom of lightly greased 2-quart oblong pan.
Layer pieces of chicken on top of broccoli.
Mix soup and mayonnaise together (lemon juice optional).
Pour on top of chicken and broccoli.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top.
(You can also mix 1 cup breadcrumbs and margarine together, then sprinkle on top of Cheddar cheese.)
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef and onion together.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: frozen cole slaw
directions: Mix 8 cups water and salt; pour over cabbage, peppers, onion and carrots.
Stir.
Let stand 1 hour.
Squeeze out excess water.

title: looks gross tastes great casserole
directions: Cook and drain vegetables.
Brown and drain sausage.
Combine vegetables, sausage, water chestnuts, mayonnaise and mushroom soup.
Put in a 3-quart casserole dish.
Top with whole tomatoes and Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
During the last 5 minutes of baking, sprinkle with onion rings.

title: chicken eggrolls
directions: Boil chicken until meat is falling off easily.
Debone it and put in food processor on medium speed for 1 minute.
Cut scallions into one-inch pieces and set apart.

Put all vegetables into food processor one by one and cut into small one-inch pieces or smaller. Pour small amount of oil into pan and put scallions in first. Saute 2 minutes, then gradually add rest of veggies, starting with the carrots, celery, bamboo shoots, mushrooms and bean sprouts. Continue sauteing 3 minutes; do not overcook.
Add 2 teaspoons of soy sauce and mix well together with the chicken.
Roll into wrappers and seal with water.
Sprinkle cornstarch over wrappers before wrapping.
Deep fry one by one until golden brown.

title: peanut butter vanilla squares
directions: Melt candy coating in large heavy saucepan over low heat, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cereal and remaining ingredients.
Stir gently until morsels are partially melted.
Spoon mixture into a greased 9-inch square pan.
Let cool completely.
Cut into squares.
Yield:
3 dozen.

title: cucumber dressing for seafood salad
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups dressing.
Serve on seafood cocktail, such as shrimp or crab meat and on seafood salads or with tray of chilled, cooked lobster and other cold fish.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Clean and peel potatoes.
In the bowl coarsely shred potatoes and onion into lined colander.
May line with cheesecloth or clean towel.
Wrap potatoes and onion in towel; squeeze to remove as much water as possible.
In large bowl, beat eggs.
Return potatoes and onion to bowl; add flour, salt and pepper and toss until mixed.
In 12-inch skillet heat 1/3 cup of oil.
Drop potato mixture by scant 1/3 cupfuls, 3 inches apart.
With pancake turner, flatten each to make 4 inch pancakes.
Cook until golden brown, about 4 minutes, then turn to cook other side.
Remove and put on a towel lined cookie sheet.
Let drain and enjoy.

title: cincinnati chili
directions: Combine ground beef, onions and water in a saucepan.
Simmer until beef turns brown.
Add tomatoes with their liquid, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, chili powder, cumin, allspice, salt, cayenne, cinnamon, garlic powder and bay leaves.
Cover; simmer 3 hours.
Spoon off fat.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in skins until done.
Cool and peel grated potatoes.
Melt butter and cheese together.
Remove from heat. Stir in potatoes.
Add sour cream, salt, pepper and onions. Pour into greased 11 x 7-inch casserole.
Sprinkle with
paprika. Bake uncovered 30 minutes at 350° until heated through.
Do not overbake.

title: ranch style baked fish
directions: Mix chicken bouillon in hot water; pour into baking pan. Place fish in pan, skin side down.
Sprinkle with Hidden Valley mix.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, or until fish flakes.
Squeeze juice from lemon wedge over fish.
Serves 2.

title: chop suey
directions: Brown pork in hot oil. Add onions, celery and green pepper. Cook for 3 minutes. Combine cornstarch with a little water, then add remaining water and bouillon cube. Add to vegetable mixture. Cook just until thick. Add bean sprouts, water chestnuts, salt and soy sauce. Heat thoroughly. Vegetables should be crisp, not overdone. Serve with hot rice. Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate fudge cake
directions: Mix the sugar and flour together in large bowl.
In a 2-quart saucepan, bring to a boil the margarine, cocoa, oil and water. Pour over dry ingredients; stir.
Add the eggs, buttermilk and soda; mix together.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan (ungreased). Bake for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shells and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes until done.

title: cooked fruit casserole
directions: Drain all fruit well in colander; put in large bowl.
Boil 3/4 cup sugar and butter until sugar is melted; add applesauce to this mixture.
Pour this over fruit in the bowl and mix; refrigerate overnight.
Next morning, butter a 2-quart casserole.
Put mixture in casserole; slice and add bananas.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Take out and mix 3 tablespoons brown sugar with almonds and sprinkle over fruit casserole.
Return to oven for 15 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12 people.
Peanuts or other nuts may be used.

title: wreath roll
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Scald milk and pour over shortening,
sugar
and salt.
When mixture cools to lukewarm, add the
dissolved
yeast
and
add
the flour and beat until smooth, add
the
remaining flour until soft dough is formed. Knead about
minutes, place dough in greased bowl until it rises to double its size.
Take dough out and roll until about a
fourth of inch thick.
After you have rolled it out spread both cans
of the
filling over it.
Roll up and shape into a wreath.
Slit
top of
roll.
Let
rise
30 minutes.
Bake on greased
pan at 325° for 35 minutes or until done.
Glaze with powdered
sugar
icing while still warm.
Decorate with pecans and cherries as desired.

title: hidden valley ranch quiche lorraine
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Sprinkle cheese in pie crust. Whisk eggs until frothy.
Add other ingredients and mix.
Pour over cheese.
Bake
15 minutes; reduce heat to 350°.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes, until center is set.
Cool.
Serves 8.

title: mystery pecan pie
directions: Beat sugar, cream cheese, egg and vanilla and set aside.
Blend remaining ingredients well (except pecans).
Spread cream cheese mixture in pie shell.
Sprinkle with pecans, then gently pour syrup mixture over pecans.
All 3 layers will change position.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until firm to touch.

title: chicken every sunday
directions: Place precooked rice on bottom of buttered casserole dish. Place mushroom soup and Lipton soup mix (mixed with 1 can of water) on top of rice.
Arrange chicken breasts on top.
Cover with foil and cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: corn chowder
directions: Fry bacon.
Crumble and set aside.
Reserve 2 tablespoons of drippings. Saute onion in drippings until tender. Add potatoes and water.
Cover and simmer until tender. Stir in milk, corn, salt and pepper.
Cook over medium heat stirring frequently until thoroughly heated.
Sprinkle with crumbled bacon.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sausage supper
directions: Mix applesauce, sauerkraut, wine and brown sugar.
Place in 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Arrange potatoes and onions around edge of dish.
Place sausage in center.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until heated thoroughly (baked uncovered).
When done and out of oven, sprinkle with parsley before serving.

title: roast persian lamb
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Make 12 insertions into the meat using a sharp knife and place one piece of garlic into each one.
Put the lamb in a roasting pan.

title: horseradish cream sauce
directions: Whip heavy cream until it forms soft peaks.
Combine mayonnaise, horseradish and mustard in another bowl.
Using a rubber spatula, fold in the whipped cream.
Add the sugar, salt and pepper.
Stir well.
Excellent with prime rib or corned beef.

title: easy fettuccine
directions: Preparation Time:
10 minutes.
Cooking Time:
10 minutes. Eating Time:
Maybe 20 minutes.
Very good and easy and fast.

title: sweet-sour green beans
directions: Break tips from green beans and cook in 1-inch boiling water for 25 to 35 minutes.
Cut bacon into 1/2-inch pieces.
Fry until crisp, then drain.
Add chopped onion to bacon drippings and saute for 2 or 3 minutes.
Stir in vinegar, sugar, salt and dry mustard; bring to a boil.
Drain beans and pour hot mixture over them. Sprinkle bacon pieces on top and toss lightly.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and garlic in roux (butter and flour) until onion is clear. Add tomatoes and soup.
Simmer for 15 minutes. Add crawfish and parsley.
Season to taste (salt, pepper and white pepper).
Serve over rice.
May substitute shrimp, cooking 1/2 hour.

title: caramel corn
directions: Bring the brown sugar and syrup to a rolling boil.
Boil 5 minutes; take off fire and add soda.
Mix popped corn, syrup and peanuts; spread on cookie sheet.
Bake 1 hour at 250°.
Break in pieces.
Cool.
Put in airtight container.

title: homemade chili rellenos
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix cheese and onion together.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Boil peppers for 2 minutes; cool.
Slit peppers down side and remove seeds; rinse loose seeds out with cold water.
Stuff peppers with cheese mixture (save 1/4 cup for topping).
Close peppers tightly.
Roll gently in flour.
When all peppers are covered with flour, set aside.

title: coconut oatmeal cake
directions: Let oats and boiling water stand 20 minutes.
Cream the next 3 ingredients together.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add to oat mixture. Sift remaining ingredients together and add to mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: playdough
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook over medium heat for 3 minutes until mixture forms a ball.
Knead on wax paper.

title: kahlua chocolate cake
directions: Mix together and bake in lightly greased and floured Bundt pan at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: german cole slaw
directions: Put cabbage, onion and green pepper in large bowl.
In a saucepan, bring the sugar, oil, vinegar, mustard, salt and celery seed to a boil.
Pour over the cabbage, onion and pepper and stir. Cover and keep in the refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: peach crisp
directions: Peel and slice peaches.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine all other ingredients and put on top.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cover sweet potatoes in water and cook until tender enough to mash.
Drain, mash and measure for pie.
Melt butter and add to potatoes.
Add sugar, eggs, vanilla, salt and milk.
Blend until mixture is thoroughly mixed.
Pour into pastry shell.
Preheat oven to 450° and bake for 10 minutes.
Lower oven to 350° and bake for 40 minutes.

title: apricot ginger chicken breasts
directions: For sauce: In a small saucepan, cook onion in hot oil until tender. Stir in all ingredients, except chicken. Bring to a boil; reduce heat. Cover and simmer for 3 minutes. Remove from heat. Preheat grill to medium. Grill chicken, uncovered, for 12 to 15 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink (160°), turning once and brushing with sauce during last 5 minutes of grilling. Reheat remaining sauce and pass with chicken. Serves 4.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook bacon; cut up onions and green pepper in grease.
Add tomatoes and turn up heat.
Add salt and black pepper.
Cook rice and set out to cool.
Add rice to tomato mixture.

title: parisian balls
directions: Mix all ingredients except chocolate and paraffin well.
Using about 1 teaspoonful of batter, roll into a ball and place on cookie sheet.
When finished, freeze candy balls.
When frozen, dip into a mixture of chocolate chips and paraffin melted together over water in double boiler.
Dip candy balls 2 or 3 at a time.
Cool on waxed paper.

title: cheese tortellini seafood salad
directions: Cook tortellini according to package directions. Drain and chill. Place cooked tortellini, shrimp, onion, peppers and crabmeat in a large bowl. Add dressing, mayonnaise and Parmesan. Stir to combine. Season to taste. Chill until ready to serve.

title: jalapeno dip
directions: Melt Velveeta cheese.
Stir in jalapeno relish and chopped peppers.

title: salmon souffle
directions: Make white sauce of margarine, flour and milk.
Slowly add small amount of sauce to egg yolks and stir into remaining sauce. Add salt, nutmeg, pepper and salmon.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake in greased individual baking dishes or casserole in a moderate oven at 325° for 45 minutes.
Serve immediately.
Garnish with lemon. Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: pecan puffs cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and continue creaming until well blended.
Add salt and vanilla.
Add nuts to the flour and then to butter mixture.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 45 minutes.
While warm, roll in powdered sugar.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: homemade lye soap
directions: Put 3 gallons water in old-time wash pot.
Melt lye, then grease.
Let boil.
When grease melts, gradually add the remaining water.
Cook slow or it will boil over.
Use wooden paddle to stir constantly.
When soap is done, lift paddle from the pot and it will string.
To test, put a little soap in cold water and it will form a ball.
Can be put in molds.
Do not use aluminum.

title: shipwreck casserole
directions: Layer in greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until potatoes are done, about 1 hour.
Good with a salad.

title: upside-down berry cobbler
directions: Mix oil, egg and milk.
Sift dry ingredients and add to the first mixture.
Add 2 tablespoons more milk.
Fry on hot griddle. Waffles, too!

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix together the pineapple and pudding.
Stir in Cool Whip and marshmallows.

title: bean rolls
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add next 4 ingredients and simmer. Take soft shell tortillas and place meat mixture inside.
Sprinkle in Colby and Monterey cheese.
Roll up and place in baking dish. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and top with Cheddar cheese, sour cream, onion, tomato, lettuce and taco salsa.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Drain zucchini.
Combine ingredients except dressing and butter or oleo.
Melt butter, add seasoning from dressing.
Add stuffing crumbs to margarine mixture.
Place 1/2 of stuffing mix in bottom of 2-quart baking dish.
Add zucchini mixture and top with remaining dressing.
Bake in 350° oven 40 minutes, uncovered.

title: easy summer salad
directions: Prepare macaroni according to package directions.
Rinse with cold water to cool.
Combine macaroni with remaining ingredients. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: tuna pea wiggle
directions: Will also need a big mixing bowl.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: Mix together 1 cup brown sugar, flour, 3 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt. Stir in milk and vanilla. Spread over bottom of slow cooker. Mix together 3/4 cup brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa; sprinkle over mixture in slow cooker. Pour in boiling water.
Do not stir. Cover and cook on high 2 to 3 hours. Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: kansas dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreo cookies in blender.
Press 1/2 mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a bowl, mix cream cheese and softened butter, then add sugar and fold in whipped topping.
In another bowl, mix pudding with milk and vanilla.
Fold in the cheese mixture and pour over cookie crust.
Sprinkle rest of Oreo crumbs on top. Freeze and eat partially frozen.
It's a dirty mess.

title: rice pie
directions: Cook rice.
Add eggs, milk, lemon flavor and sugar.
Put into pie plate and bake at 350° about 45 minutes until done.

title: beef stew
directions: Heat Crisco.
Add stew beef and brown 20 minutes.
Slice onion.
Add with 4 cups water, garlic salt, lemon juice, sugar, Worcestershire sauce, pepper, paprika, bay leaf and allspice. Simmer in a large pan for 2 hours.
Add vegetables and cook for 30 minutes, until vegetables are tender.

title: st. patty's day colcannon
directions: Peel and boil up a bunch of potatoes until tender.
Mash with some milk and butter until they look good.
Slice some green cabbage thinly and fold into the steaming hot mashed potatoes. Let it set a bit to slightly cook the cabbage.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: pinto bean dip
directions: In a bowl, mash beans with a fork.
Stir in 3/4 teaspoon salt, pepper and hot pepper sauce.
Spread onto a 12-inch serving plate. Mash avocados with lemon juice and remaining salt.
Spread over bean mixture.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning. Spread over avocado layer.
Sprinkle with onions, tomatoes, cheese and olives.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: chicken tetrazzini(for kids too!)
directions: Cook chicken in water with veggies.
Remove chicken and cut up.
Save water (broth).
Cook bow pasta or spaghetti.
Saute mushrooms in butter.
Stir into pasta.

title: tuna salad
directions: Boil macaroni, then cool.
Add the rest of the ingredients. Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and put in refrigerator.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Mix softened cream cheese together with Marshmallow Creme and butterscotch topping.
Enjoy with fresh, cut up apples.

title: mint julep disneyland
directions: Combine sugar and soda water in a saucepan, stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add lime and lemonade concentrate.
Bring to a full boil.
Remove from heat and add creme de menthe.
Chill.

title: stewed collards and salt pork
directions: Trim stems off collards unless very young and tender. Wash thoroughly. Cook pork until crisp. Remove meat and pour off 1/2 of drippings. Saut onions in this until tender. Add collards, salt, pepper and water. Cook, covered, over low heat 15 minutes or until collards are tender. If necessary, add a little more water. Return meat to cooked greens; heat through and serve immediately.

title: cap'n bob's salmon steaks
directions: Whisk together olive oil, soy sauce, dill weed lemon juice and clove to make a sauce; brush over salmon steaks.
Place on broiler pan and broil steaks on both sides until lightly browned and fish flakes easily.
Do not overcook.

title: russian tea
directions: Dilute juice according to directions.
Dip tea in 1 quart boiling water.
Boil
cloves in another quart of water.
Mix all together.

title: artichoke cracker spread
directions: Separate artichokes (save marinated juice).
Mix all ingredients, except paprika.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake at 350° in large pie tin 20 minutes.
Cool; serve with crackers.

title: savory chicken squares
directions: Blend cream cheese and 2 tablespoons margarine. Add the chicken, salt, pepper, milk, chives and pimiento.
Mix well. Separate rolls and make into 4 rectangles.

Press edges together to seal. Spoon 1/2 cup of chicken mixture into each rectangle. Pull up corners and seal. Brush with butter. Sprinkle with the croutons. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and eggs thoroughly.
Sift together the flour, cream of tartar and soda.
Mix together with margarine mixture until well blended.
Roll into balls the size of small walnuts.
Roll balls in mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Place 2 inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes, until brown but still soft.
Dough may need to be refrigerated awhile to handle better.
Yields about 10 dozen.

title: three favorites in one
directions: Cream butter or margarine and sugars.
Add vanilla, eggs, flour, salt and baking soda.
Stir in peanut butter, oatmeal and chocolate chips.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 2 to 3 dozen cookies.

title: scratch shortbread
directions: Mix together butter and brown sugar.
Add flour, 1/2 cup at a time.
Roll out between waxed paper 1/2-inch thick.
Cut in squares and prick each piece with a fork.
Bake in an ungreased pan for 15 minutes in 350° oven.

title: italian-style pork chops and stuffing
directions: Heat oil in large skillet (medium-high).
Add chops; brown on both sides.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce, green peppers and pepper.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes until chops are cooked through.
Remove chops from skillet.

title: french dressing
directions: Blend in bowl; beat.
Add 1 cup oil and blend in with your vinegar very slowly.
Beat until your sugar is dissolved good. Keep covered in cool place.

title: homemade chocolate ice cream
directions: Blend Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip with mixer; add sugar if desired.
Mix well.
Pour into ice cream freezer; add Food Lion chocolate milk (do not mix).
Freeze as usual.

title: mom's lemon pie
directions: Mix; put into pie shell and refrigerate until thick.

title: herb seasoned popcorn
directions: Combine margarine, basil, oregano and cayenne; pour evenly over popcorn.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Toss gently.

title: chocolate torte
directions: Mix and press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan (will be thin). Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: lane cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together until very light.
Sift flour and baking powder 3 times; add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Fold in well beaten egg whites and vanilla.
Bake in four 8-inch or three 9-inch pans sprayed with Pam and lined with waxed paper for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken and rice in a bag
directions: Place all ingredients in a Reynolds browning bag.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
I put the ingredients in a baking dish and put the dish in the bag.
Set the bag on a cookie sheet or in a broiling pan.
This is easier to handle.

title: breakfast pita pockets
directions: Slice pita bread in half. Heat in microwave or oven. Melt margarine in skillet and saut vegetables. Stir in ham and eggs, stirring frequently until eggs are set (but still moist). Stir in cheese and remove from heat. Fill each pita pocket with 1/4 scrambled egg mixture.

title: hamburger noodle casserole
directions: While noodles are cooking, brown ground beef and onion in 2 tablespoons fat in frypan.
Mix tomato sauce, soup and Worcestershire sauce.
Add drained and rinsed noodles to the mixture.
Add noodle mixture to meat mixture in frypan.
Mix well and sprinkle grated cheese over all.
Melt cheese before serving.

title: basic pie filling
directions: Mix the sugar and flour; add enough milk to make a thick paste.
Add egg yolks and beat.
Add remaining milk and salt; mix well.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.

title: pancakes
directions: Combine all ingredients; beat until smooth.
Pour out onto a hot griddle or skillet; make sure it is greased.
Cook until golden brown.

title: tropical waldorf salad
directions: Sprinkle apples with sweetener and lemon juice.
Add pineapple, celery and nuts.
Add yogurt and mix well.
Cover bowl and chill.

title: bacon chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wrap each chicken breast in two pieces of bacon.
Place chicken in a 9 x 13-baking dish.
Mix soup, milk and optional spices; pour mixture over the chicken.
Cover the dish with foil.
Bake in the preheated oven for 50 minutes or until done.
Remove the foil the last 15 minutes of baking to brown the bacon.
Serve the gravy this makes over rice or mashed potatoes.

title: tuna stuffed jalapenos
directions: Mix tuna, egg, onion and pickle with enough mayonnaise to make a salad.
Stuff jalapeno halves with tuna mixture and refrigerate until serving.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Melt together marshmallows, margarine and oil.
After marshmallows are melted, stir in the popcorn, nuts and gumdrops. Tightly pack the mixture into a buttered Bundt pan.
Let cool. Turn upside-down to knock it out of pan and serve.

title: crunchy munchy krispie bars
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs, beating well. Blend in flour, baking powder and salt.
Add vanilla.
Spread into bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 25 minutes or until done.
Cover with marshmallows and return to oven for 2 minutes.
Cool.

title: hot orange cream drink
directions: Heat orange juice and apple cider, cloves and cinnamon sticks. Add pint of sherbet until melted.
Add 1/2 cup Brandy if desired. Top with miniature marshmallows.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix and roll into walnut size balls.
Bake on greased cookie sheet in a 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
May be frozen and then baked.

title: minted peas
directions: Drain peas.
Cook liquid until 1/4 cup remains.
Add all ingredients and simmer to blend flavors.

title: meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients; shape into 1-inch meatballs.
Brown in skillet.

title: broiled open-faced sandwiches
directions: Combine chicken, tomato, mushrooms, sour cream, Parmesan cheese, mayonnaise, green pepper, onion powder and tarragon. Spread half of the mixture on one side of each muffin.
Place muffin, spread side up, on rack of unheated broiler pan.
Broil for 5 to 7 minutes, or until spread is bubbly.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
This can be served chilled or warm.

title: mayonnaise salad
directions: Boil potatoes, eggs and carrot for about 20 minutes.
Take out the carrot 10 minutes earlier.
After it's ready, remove it from the water and peel potatoes while it's hot.
Let everything cool off and start cutting the potatoes in small, half-a-bite pieces. The eggs, carrot, pickles and onion should be chopped in small pieces.
Cut the dill.
Add mayonnaise and peas and start mixing. Add 1/4 teaspoon of salt and a touch of pepper.

title: coconut cream cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and margarine.
Add egg yolks and vanilla; beat well.
Dissolve baking soda into buttermilk.
Sift flour; mix with coconut and nuts.
Add milk mixture alternately with flour mixture to sugar mixture, beating well after each addition.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into cake mixture. Bake in 3 well-greased and floured 9-inch cake pans for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: indian pudding
directions: Combine 2 cups of milk with cornmeal.
Heat until boiling. Add rest of the ingredients and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir often.

title: ranch potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes	(do
not
peel)
and
cube.
Boil until almost done.
Drain and place in baking dish.
Cover with oleo (I use squeeze butter).
Sprinkle with dry Ranch dressing mix. Cover with shredded
Cheddar
cheese.	Bake
at
350°	for
15 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: fresh fruit salad with creamy banana dressing
directions: In medium-size bowl, toss oranges, apples and strawberries. Chill until serving time.
In blender or food processor, puree remaining ingredients except poppy seed.
Pour into small bowl and stir in poppy seed.
Makes 1 cup dressing.

title: good and spicy meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Using level tablespoon, shape into 48 to 50 meatballs.
Bake on foil-lined cookie sheet, with edges of foil turned up, at 400° about 12 minutes or until browned.

title: spiced peaches
directions: Dip peaches quickly in hot water and remove skins.
Boil sugar, vinegar and spices for 20 minutes.
Place a few peaches at a time in syrup and cook until tender for canning.
Pack in clean hot jars.
Fill jars with hot syrup.
Adjust lids and seal immediately.
Process in hot water bath.

title: beef-vegetable stir-fry over rice
directions: Slice beef across grain into thin strips.
Combine soup mix, cornstarch and water.
In skillet over medium-high heat in 1 tablespoon hot oil, stir-fry half of the beef until browned. Remove; set aside.
Repeat with remaining beef.
Over medium heat in 1 tablespoon hot oil, stir-fry vegetables with garlic powder and ginger until tender-crisp.
Add reserved soup mixture.
Cook until mixture boils and thickens, stirring occasionally.
Serve over Oniony Rice.
Serves 4.

title: baked french onion soup
directions: Add 3 tablespoons oil to a large soup pot or saucepan over medium/high heat. Add the sliced onions and saut for 20 minutes until the onions begin to soften and start to become translucent. You don't want them to brown. Add the beef broth, water, salt, garlic powder and black pepper to the pan; bring mixture to a boil. When soup begins to boil, reduce heat and simmer for 45 minutes.

title: congealed salad
directions: Drain pineapple; sprinkle with jello.
Mix in cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Pour into mold and refrigerate.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Mix and
beat
until smooth.
Bake in Bundt pan at 350° for 45 or
50 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched.

title: farmer's breakfast
directions: In 10-inch skillet, cook onion and potatoes, water and 1/4 teaspoon salt in butter until tender, stirring occasionally.
Beat together eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Stir in ham.
Pour over potatoes and cook without stirring until mixture begins to set on bottom and side of pan.
Using a large spoon lift and fold partially cooked egg mixture so uncooked portions flow underneath. Cook on medium heat about 4 minutes or until done.

title: noodle pudding souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in a greased dish at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: "miss" ena's 1-2-3-4 pineapple cake batter
directions: Cream butter well.
Add sugar slowly, beating constantly. When well creamed/fluffy, add eggs, one at a time, beating constantly.
Sift flour and baking powder together, then beat in flour, a small amount each time, beginning and ending with flour mix.
Bake in 3 greased and lightly floured 9-inch cake pans at 350° for approximately 25 minutes.

title: barbecue rice and beans
directions: Cook and stir onion and pepper in hot oil in saucepan until tender but not browned.
Stir in beans, water, barbecue sauce, bouillon cube and garlic powder.
Bring to boil.
Stir in rice. Cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork. Makes 6 servings.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: chicken curry
directions: In a large saucepan, melt the butter; saute chopped onion, juice of lemon and diced apple until tender.
Cut chicken into chunks and toss in flour and spices.
Add to onion and apples. Saute chicken until 3/4 cooked.
Add cream, chicken stock and chutney.
Bring to a simmer and place in casserole.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: german sweet chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate with butter over low heat, stirring until blended.
Remove from heat; gradually blend in milk.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Gradually blend in chocolate mixture.
Pour into pie shells.
Combine coconut and nuts.
Sprinkle over filling.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes. Filling will be soft, but will set while cooling.
Cool at least 4 hours before cutting.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops which have been salted and peppered to taste in 2 tablespoons of cooking oil.
Arrange pork chops in bottom of casserole dish and add rice.
Bring can of soup to a boil in 1 can of water.
Pour over rice.
Make sure all rice is covered.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: angel hair carbonata
directions: Cook the angel hair and drain.
In a large frying pan, heat the heavy cream.
When it comes to a boil, shut off heat and quickly beat in the eggs, one at a time, until it is smooth and blended.
Place back on low heat and add pasta to cream mixture. Blend well.
Add a teaspoon of Parmesan cheese to mixture to thicken.
Use a teaspoon at a time and blend well before adding more.
Do not make mixture too thick.
When it's just right, serve immediately.

title: chile casserole
directions: Place chilies and cheese in a greased casserole dish.
In a bowl, beat eggs; add milk and mix well.
Pour mixture over cheese and chilies.

title: fruit pudding delight
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1 cup liquid.
Combine fruit and 1/2 cup Grape-Nuts in large bowl; toss gently. Combine pudding with reserved pineapple juice in a mixing bowl.
Beat on high speed of electric mixer one minute.
Pour pudding over fruit and Grape-Nuts.
Coat well.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup Grape-Nuts over top. Yields 12 servings.

title: garlicky stuffed quahogs
directions: Open quahogs (easily done by putting them in the freezer for a short time).
Roughly chop.
In food processor, mince parsley and garlic.
Add crackers and bread and pulse until coarse crumbs are formed.

title: marinade sauce(almost like winners)
directions: Mix together.
Pour over meat.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 to 4 days, flipping twice a day.
Grill or oven bake.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Beat chicken breasts with mallet.
Mix egg and milk.
Place ham and cheese on top of chicken and fold over.
Dip in milk mixture and then in cracker crumbs.
Place on cookie sheet with a pat of butter on top.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: homemade sugar cookies
directions: Combine flour, salt and baking powder in bowl and set aside. In a separate bowl, blend margarine, 1 cup sugar and vanilla.
Add remaining sugar and eggs and mix well, while slowly pouring in flour mixture.
Chill thoroughly.
Roll dough to 1/8 to 1/4-inch thickness on a well floured surface and cut out with cookie cutters.
Place cookies on greased cookie sheets and bake 8 to 10 minutes in preheated 400° oven.
Let cookies cool before decorating.

title: frozen sliced sweet dill pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers, onions, salt and water in 2 quart bowl (not aluminum) and let stand about 2 hours.
Drain, but do not rinse. Return vegetables to bowl, and add sugar, vinegar and dill.
Let stand, stirring from time to time, until sugar has dissolved completely and liquid covers the vegetables.
Pack in glass or plastic freezer containers (leave one inch of head space).
Seal tightly and freeze.
To serve, defrost in refrigerator or at room temperature.
These are very crisp.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: mexican steak with beans and rice
directions: Trim fat from steaks. Combine chili powder, cumin, sugar, salt and pepper.
Pound into both sides of steaks.
Place in warm frypan
and brown on both sides. Add 1/4 cup beef broth, onion and garlic.
Cook until tender. Add remaining broth and beans. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat. Stir in sour cream. Serve with rice.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli; put in baking dish.
Boil and cut up chicken breasts and place on top of broccoli.
Mix sour cream and soup, then pour over chicken.
Place cheese on top, then sprinkle with crackers.
Melt butter and pour over crackers.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry bavarian cream
directions: Thaw and drain juice from frozen berries.
Prepare Jell-O (1 cup boiling water and berry juice plus cold water to make 1 cup). Chill until almost firm.
Whip until stiff 1 cup cream.
Beat Jell-O until foamy.
Fold cream, Jell-O and berries.
Chill about 1 hour.

title: pickled cauliflower
directions: Separate flowerets of cauliflower.
Add salt.
Cover with cold water; drain and rinse with cold water.
Tie spices in muslin bag and boil with vinegar and sugar 10 minutes.
Add cauliflower; cook 3 minutes until nearly tender.
Pack in sterilized jars and fill with boiling syrup and seal.
May add peeled pickling onions and strips of green pepper to cauliflower, if desired.

title: frog eye salad
directions: In small saucepan mix sugar, flour and salt.
Stir in pineapple juice and egg.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add lemon juice.
Set aside and cool.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream all ingredients except eggs and pecans.
Once creamed, beat eggs into mixture, one at a time.
When batter is smooth, pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle pecans or walnuts on top.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours or until firm at 300°.
Do not overcook.
Enjoy!

title: kris kringle cookies
directions: Mix as for any cake.
Put soda in buttermilk.
Put cherries in last.
Bake at 275° until light brown.

title: pudding cake
directions: Mix first four ingredients well. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Add chocolate chips and pecans on top.
Bake at 350° until done (40 to 45 minutes).
Can use butterscotch chips and butterscotch pudding in yellow cake mix (non pudding mix).

title: raisin oatmeal cookies
directions: Blend sugars, shortening, eggs and molasses until light and fluffy.
Sift flour, salt, spices, soda and baking powder together. Add dry ingredients alternately with Carnation until well mixed. Stir in oats, raisins and nuts.
Drop by heaping spoonfuls on greased baking sheet.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes or until light brown.
Cool on wire racks.

title: mother's rice pudding
directions: Mix all in electric cooker.
Put on medium high until milk is hot.
Turn down to medium low (250°).
Stir at least every hour. Takes about 4 hours.
Put a chunk of oleo in at last.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese, butter and sugar.
Add vanilla flavoring.
Alternate layers of cookies, pudding and cream cheese mixture in a plastic flowerpot.
Finish with layer of cookies on top.
Gummy worms may be added.
Place a silk flower in the middle and serve with a gardening spade.

title: easy ice cream
directions: Add all ingredients and enough plain milk to make 1 gallon and pour into ice cream freezer.

title: chicken delight
directions: Place chicken pieces in baking dish.
Combine cream of chicken soup, onion, salt, pepper, parsley and thyme in saucepan.
Add the liquid (water).
Mix well; bring to boil, stirring constantly. Add rice.
Mix and pour over chicken.
Bake 1 hour or until chicken is done in 350° oven.

title: shortbread caramel cookie bars
directions: Cut 1 cup butter into chunks. In food processor combine 2 cups flour, 1/2 cup sugar, cornstarch and butter chunks. Whirl until dough. Press evenly
over buttered 9 x 13 baking pan. Bake in oven at 325 until top feels dry and is just beginning to brown (about 25 minutes). Cool completely.

title: indoor s'mores
directions: Butter baking pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Heat corn syrup, butter and real milk chocolate morsels just to boiling in 3-quart saucepan, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour over cereal in a large mixing bowl.
Toss quickly until completely coated with chocolate.
Fold in marshmallows 1 cup at a time.
Press mixture evenly in pan with buttered back of spoon.
Set until firm.
Cut.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix and bring to a boil.
Set aside to cool.

title: a meal in one
directions: Brown ground beef.
Mix both soups together with ground beef. In a large casserole dish, layer potatoes, cut 1/4-inch thick, in bottom.
Top potatoes with carrots, then green beans.
Add sliced mushrooms, then top with soup and ground beef mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.
Delicious!

title: strawberry salad
directions: Cream sugar and cream cheese together.
Stir in Cool Whip. Add nuts, bananas, pineapple and strawberries; mix well. Refrigerate.

title: spoon bread
directions: Stirring constantly, slowly mix the scalded milk and corn meal.
Stir until thick and smooth.
Beat the egg yolks and corn meal mixture.
Slowly, blend in the cheese, salt, sugar and butter; beat until smooth.
Beat the egg whites until they peak and fold into the mixture.
Turn into a buttered casserole dish. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: eggnog pudding
directions: In mixer, whisk in bowl the milk, 1/4 cup bourbon and pudding mix about 2 minutes or until smooth.
Pour into serving dish or 4 individual dessert dishes.
Chill.
Beat cream, sugar and remaining 1 teaspoon bourbon until stiff.
Spoon on pudding; sprinkle with nutmeg.
Good with gingersnaps.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Butter bottom of 9 x 13 cake pan. Line pan with graham crackers.
(Do not crunch.)
Mix pudding with milk.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Blend in whipped topping.
Pour 1/2 mixture over graham crackers.
Add second layer of grahams and pour remaining mixture over.
Add another layer of grahams. Refrigerate for 2 hours, then frost.

title: oven roasted potatoes
directions: Cut up potatoes into bite-size pieces.
Can either leave skin on or peel.
I like to use red-skinned potatoes.
In plastic bag put all ingredients and shake until potatoes are well coated. Cover and bake in 350° oven until done, approximately 45 minutes. Stir midway.

title: miniature quick pizza
directions: Separate hamburger buns and place middle side up on baking sheet.
Lightly toast.
Spread pizza sauce, cheese and pepperoni on top of each bun.
Bake until cheese is bubbly.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and set aside.
Butter bread and cube.
Put bread cubes in bottom of pan.
Put drained sausage on bread cubes. Sprinkle cheese on sausage.
Beat eggs; add milk, salt and mustard.
Pour over sausage and bread cubes.
Chill overnight. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chip dip
directions: Put in bowl and mix.

title: no fat deluxe corn bread
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Mix egg,
milk,
onion	and applesauce and add to dry mixture. Mix until
smooth.
Bake
at
425° in greased pan.
For 8-inch square pan,
bake	20
to	25
minutes;
muffins bake 15 to 20 minutes; sticks bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: "free" salad dressing
directions: Mix all together and store in refrigerator.

title: crab soup
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan and heat thoroughly; do not boil.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, using all of the green onion; beat well. Make ahead.
Can be served with raw vegetables or hollow rye bread; cube.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix cream cheese with sugar and vanilla.
Whip cream cheese mixture.
Arrange in a pan a layer of crackers and layer of cream cheese mixture.
Add cherries last and chill.

title: orange cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until smooth; add eggs 1 at a time and beat well after each. Dissolve soda in buttermilk and add to creamed mixture. Place flour in large bowl and cut candy and dates, letting fall in flour. Add nuts to flour. Stir to coat each piece and add mixture with coconut to creamed mixture. This makes a very stiff dough that should be mixed by hand. Put in a greased and floured 13 x 9 pan. Bake at 250° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: tom's stiff eggnog
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff. Slowly add 3/4 cup sugar to the egg whites.
Whip the cream until stiff and slowly add 1/4 cup sugar.
Beat the egg yolks and slowly add the bourbon. Fold in the egg whites and whipped cream.
Do not beat.
Serve immediately in cups or silver goblets.
Sprinkle nutmeg on eggnog before serving. You may need to use a spoon in the eggnog when served because it is thick.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in boiling water; cool.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy; add egg yolks one at a time.
Add chocolate and water.
Sift flour with soda and salt; add alternately to chocolate mixture with buttermilk.
Fold in egg whites (beaten until stiff) with a spoon.
Pour into three 8 or 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Frost with Coconut Pecan Frosting.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all together.
Put in pan and place in a 350° oven while mixing topping.

title: pineapple-banana punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in water.
In blender, mix 1/2 of orange juice, pineapple juice and bananas together.
Add rest of orange juice and lemon juice.
Blend well.
Freeze mixture.

title: lemon veal
directions: Pound veal slices between sheets of waxed paper until very thin.
Place a little flour on one sheet of waxed paper.
Combine cheese, crumbs and parsley on another sheet.
Grate the rind from the lemon and add to the cheese and crumbs, mixing well.
Slice the lemon into 8 thin slices and set aside.
Dip each piece of veal first into the flour, then in egg, then into the crumbs. Heat the oil in a frying pan and saute each veal slice.
Keep warm until serving time and garnish with lemon slices.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
well.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Roll in coconut or chopped nuts.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and let simmer for 1/2 hour.

title: dry hot chocolate mix
directions: Use 1/3 cup mix; add boiling water.
Store in airtight container.

title: baked potato strips
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Slice unpeeled potatoes lengthwise into large pieces. Place on a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Coat with butter and sprinkle with garlic salt. Bake for 1 hour.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake until cheese is melted.

title: spoonburgers
directions: In skillet, brown beef and onion until tender; drain fat.
Add soup and seasonings.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Serve on buns.

title: chilean chicken corn pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
In heavy skillet, cook onion and garlic in 1 tablespoon butter over medium heat for 3 to 4 minutes, until soft.
Stir in 1 tablespoon flour and chicken broth.
Cook, stirring until thickened, then add chili powder, chicken, olives and raisins.
Spoon into prepared casserole.

title: black magic cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees. Grease bundt pan. In microwave safe bowl; combine butter, syrup and Milky Ways. Heat 5 to 5 1/2 minutes, whisking once then beat until smooth. Whisk in sugar, buttermilk, vanilla and eggs. Stir in flour, cocoa, salt and soda. Pour batter into pan. Bake 1 1/2 hours or until toothpick comes out clean. Cool in pan on wire rack 10 minutes. Loosen cake from pan; invert unto rack to cool completely.

title: jewish pound cake
directions: Mix raisins and water in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat; add baking soda and set aside.
Mix together sugar, oil, eggs, vanilla, flour and nuts.
Add raisin mixture.
Grease and flour tube pan and bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: fudge topping
directions: Combine ingredients in saucepan.
Stir over medium heat until boiling rapidly.
Serve over ice cream.

title: pizza sauce
directions: Saute onions in enough oil to keep from sticking.
Do not brown.
Add other ingredients; more or less seasoning may be used to suit individual taste.
Simmer until tomatoes comes to small pieces and mixture becomes rather thick.

title: frogmore stew
directions: Fill large Dutch oven with water.
Add Old Bay seasoning. Bring to boil.
Add potatoes, return to boil.
Cook 10 minutes. Add corn, return to boil.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add sausage, return to boil.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add shrimp and return to boil.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes, until shrimp turns pink.
Remove with slotted spoon onto serving platter.
Serve with cole slaw, French bread, cocktail sauce and key lime pie.
Serves a crowd.

title: pistachio pudding dessert
directions: Blend together.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: chocolate silver cake
directions: Cream the butter, add the sugar and beat well.
Sift the flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with the milk and vanilla.
Beat the egg whites until stiff and fold into cake. Bake in 2 layers in a 365° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Top with chocolate butter icing.

title: green tomato mincemeat
directions: Mix all together. Bring to boil in large kettle. Mix and boil rapidly 1 minute. Turn down heat and simmer until thick. Put in hot jars; seal while hot. Makes about 8 pints.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix all together.
Cook in a 350° oven about 1 hour.

title: sausage balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix sausage and Cheez Whiz together, then knead in Bisquick mix (will look like dough).
Pinch off small balls and put 1 1/2 inches apart in pan.
Bake until golden brown (10 to 15 minutes).

title: soft frosting for cakes
directions: Cook flour and milk until thick and let cool.
Cream well the last 4 ingredients.
After creaming, add cooked mixture and beat with a mixer until smooth and creamy.
Real delicious!

title: quick and easy meat sauce
directions: Crumble the ground meat and brown in the cooking oil in a large skillet.
Stir in the seasonings (salt and pepper) and the onion.
Add the tomato sauce.
Cover the skillet and let the mixture simmer for about 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: perfect bread pudding
directions: Combine milk and eggs; pour over bread cubes.
Add remaining ingredients; toss lightly to blend.
Spread in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Set in shallow pan on oven rack.
Pour hot water around 1-inch deep.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: low-fat oven fried chicken
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Combine yogurt, paprika, thyme (if desired), salt, pepper and garlic powder; mix well.
Coat chicken with mixture.
Chicken may be covered and refrigerated overnight or until baking, or baked immediately.
Spray shallow roasting pan or jelly roll pan with vegetable spray.
Combine bread crumbs and margarine in shallow dish, mixing well.
Coat chicken in crumbs; place in pan.
Bake breasts 25 minutes, thighs 30 to 35 minutes or until chicken is tender and juices run clear.
Makes 6 servings. Serving size:
1/6 recipe.

title: mexican dip
directions: In a bowl, mix together with a mixer the cream cheese and salsa.
Pour into a bowl and top with chopped lettuce, diced tomato and green or black olives.
Keep chilled until ready to serve.
Serve with chips.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Slowly add boiling water, stirring constantly.
Add butter and vanilla.
Cook until slightly thickened.

title: italian twist salad
directions: In large bowl, stir chicken broth, vinegar, corn oil, garlic, basil, salt and crushed red pepper.
Add twist trio and Parmesan; toss to coat well.
Stir in broccoli, tomatoes and red pepper. Serve at room temperature.
Makes 8 servings.

title: hardtack candy
directions: Mix sugar, corn syrup and water in large saucepan. Stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves. Boil without stirring until temperature reaches 310° or until drops of syrup forms hard brittle threads in cold water. Remove from heat.

title: orange mint tea
directions: Boil sugar, water and grated orange rind together for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add crushed mint leaves.
Cool. Combine tea and orange juice.
Half-fill ice tea glasses with crushed ice.
Add tea and sweeten with mint syrup.
Serves 6.

title: frosting(excellent for decorating)
directions: Cream Crisco and extracts until real creamy; add water.
Add powdered sugar a little at a time until creamy.

title: fluffy white frosting
directions: Beat egg whites.
While beating, add baking powder and cream of tartar.
Boil sugar, Karo and water to thread stage.
Add slowly to beaten egg whites.
Add vanilla and beat until smooth.

title: no peek beef
directions: Combine all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook for 12 hours on low.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add enough flour so that dough doesn't stick to hands, but is not real stiff.

title: potato casserole
directions: Melt margarine, then saute onion until clear.
Grate cheese and mix everything together except potatoes.
When ready to bake, add potatoes and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve while warm.

title: sweet white sauce
directions: Sift flour and sugar.

title: morning glory carrot muffin wake you ups!
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray tins with cooking spray or oil with vegetable oil.
Mix flour, brown sugar, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, ginger and cloves in a large mixing bowl.
Add the oil, applesauce, egg, egg white, vanilla, strained carrots, juice and the crushed pineapple in its own juice.
Mix well.
Stir in coconut.
Fill pans 2/3 full.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Turn muffins out onto a wire rack.
Once cooled, store in airtight container.
Will make 18 muffins.
These muffins are lo-cal.
They contain 168 calories per muffin and 5 grams of fat each.

title: bread pudding
directions: Soak bread in milk for 5 minutes.
Add sugar and butter.
Pour slowly over eggs.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake in pan of hot water at 350° until firm, about 1 hour.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel, core and thinly slice apples.
Place in baking dish. Pour water over apples.
Mix sugar, flour, margarine and cinnamon until very fine.
A food processor works well for this.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm.
Very good with ice cream.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Microwave chicken 15 minutes.
Let cool.
Then deskin and cut up.
Boil noodles according to package directions.
Mix chicken, noodles, soups and milk.
Sprinkle cheese over top after putting in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour to 45 minutes, until cheese melts.

title: chocolate donuts
directions: Mix powdered sugar and cocoa.
Add water; mix and set aside. Heat 1/2-inch oil in small skillet on medium heat.
Cut or punch holes in biscuits.
When oil is hot, drop biscuits (a few at a time) into oil.
Cook until golden brown on both sides. Dip fried donuts into chocolate mix.
Place on a platter and sprinkle with decorator sprinkles, chopped pecans, coconut, etc.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Dough will be stiff.
Chill dough.
Roll 1/4 inch thick.
Cut with favorite cutters.
Bake at 400° to 425° for 12 minutes. Makes about 3 dozen.

title: breakfast quiche
directions: Melt margarine and add flour to make a paste (set aside). Whip eggs in a large bowl; add cheeses, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Add flour/margarine paste.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish (glass is best) and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Can also mix night before, refrigerate and bake in morning.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: strawberry fig jelly
directions: Mix figs, sugar, and jello and cook 7 minutes after comes to a rolling boil.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash and onion until tender; then drain and mash cooked squash.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased 1-quart casserole dish and bake at 375° for about 40 minutes. Yields 6 servings.

title: dessert coffee
directions: In a blender, combine all ingredients.
Cover and blend 30 seconds.
Serve immediately. Makes 6 (8 ounce) servings.

title: easy party punch
directions: Mix all together in gallon jug.
Add enough water to fill jug.

title: daddy's pecan pie
directions: Mix together and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chickpea salad
directions: Whisk first 5 ingredients in a large bowl until blended.
Add remainder of ingredients and toss to mix and coat.

title: christmas strawberry
directions: Mix jello, pecans, coconut and milk.
Chill 1 hour.
Shape into berries and roll in colored sugar.
Use green colored almonds for stems.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Combine all of the ingredients.
Cook 40 minutes over low heat.
Makes about 12 cups of soup.
Can be frozen.

title: sour cream apple squares
directions: Mix flour, sugar and margarine.
Use 2 2/3 cups of mixture. Press in bottom of pan.
Bake in oven at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Mix remaining flour mixture with the rest of the ingredients. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Add 1 package spinach and 2 1/2 cups ditalini after soup boils.
Makes 4 to 5 gallons.

title: finnish cardamon bread
directions: Cream the sugar, oleo, eggs, salt and cardamon seed.
Dissolve the yeast and sugar in the warm water.
Let rise and add to creamed mixture.
Makes 3 rolls.

title: chicken wings
directions: Combine ingredients and marinade wings for 24 hours in refrigerator.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: easy crust chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken; remove bones and skin.
Cut up and place in baking dish.
Mix broth and celery soup, beating and stirring until smooth.
Pour over cut-up chicken.
Mix flour, salt, milk, pepper and baking powder and pour over chicken.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: velveeta fudge
directions: Melt cheese and margarine.
(Works great in microwave but need to watch carefully to keep from burning.)
Add powdered sugar, cocoa, vanilla and nuts.
Beat and spread in large sheet pan. Makes 7 pounds.
The fudge is very rich and creamy.
You can cut recipe in 1/2 very easily.

title: veal with mushrooms and peppers
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients. Pour marinade over veal; marinate 15 minutes. Remove meat and save marinade. Dredge veal in flour; brown on both sides in butter. Place veal in a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Combine marinade, broth, green pepper and mushrooms. Pour over veal. Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Remove cover; top with onion rings. Bake, uncovered, 15 minutes. Yield: 2 servings.

title: hershey cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake at 325°. Cool completely. Makes 3 (9-inch) layers. Slice each layer in half and frost. (I bake in 6 different pans; it's easier.)

title: brunswick stew
directions: Brown pork and beef with onions in 4 tablespoons of oil for about 15 minutes.
Add cut up chicken and rest of ingredients. Cook for 2 hours.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix ingredients in the order given. Stir well.
Grease and flour three loaf pans (9 x 4-inch).
Pour batter into the loaf pans.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes or until an inserted toothpick comes out clean.
Great to give as a gift!

title: beef roast with wine and beer
directions: Place roast in large pan.
(If roast is frozen, add an extra 45 minutes to cooking time.)
Pour wine and beer over roast. Sprinkle dry onion mix over.
Cover.
Roast for 3 hours at 325°. Last hour, put in vegetables.

title: cranberry grape salad
directions: Cover cranberries with sugar and let stand overnight.
Drain juice and mix other ingredients in before serving.

title: baked chicken
directions: Spray chicken with Pam spray.
Put ingredients together.
With your fingertips, sprinkle mixture over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, until well done.

title: chess pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, melted butter, cornmeal, vanilla, vinegar and cream.
Pour into a pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: easy doozit cookies
directions: Mix together.
Make balls, then roll in powdered sugar. Chill.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: strawberry sundae
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Stir in one 8 ounce tub of Cool Whip.
Pour into Jell-O mold to set.
When set, invert mold onto plate.
Slice and have a perfect sundae!

title: divinity candy
directions: Cook sugar, syrup, water, vinegar and salt to 262° or very firm ball stage.
Beat slowly into well beaten egg whites.
Add nuts and vanilla when mixture begins to thicken.
Drop by spoonfuls on heavy waxed paper.
Store in an airtight container.

title: drunken meatballs
directions: Mix hamburger with next six ingredients into meatballs and set aside.
Bring the 2 cans of beer and ketchup to boiling.
Place meatballs into boiling soup; reduce heat to simmer.
Simmer for 1 to 2 hours.

title: chicken costa brava
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
Sprinkle chicken with salt. Brown chicken in oil.
Combine spices; sprinkle over chicken.
Add garlic and onion; saute.
Add reserved juice with next 4 ingredients.
Cover.
Simmer 25 minutes.

title: regular white bread
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine 2 1/2 cups flour and yeast. In a saucepan, heat milk, sugar, shortening and salt until lukewarm and shortening almost melts.
Add to flour mixture and beat at low speed until mixed.
With a spoon, put in the rest of the flour, a little at a time, until you have used as much flour as possible.

title: easy cherry roll surprise
directions: Heat filling, lemon juice aand water until thickened.
Pour into 9-inch pie plate.
Cover with danish rolls and bake as directed until rolls are done.

title: coconut bonbons
directions: Pour margarine over coconut.
Stir until blended; add milk, blend sugar in gradually.
Mix well and chill.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Chill at least 3 hours.
Melt paraffin and chocolate in double boiler.
Using a toothpick as holder, dip coconut balls into chocolate mixture.
Set on waxed paper.
Remove toothpick.

title: potato salad
directions: In large bowl put potatoes, onions,
parsley, salt and pepper. Toss lightly. Combine mustard, sweetener and vinegar in small bowl, mixing well.
Pour over potatoes.
Stir until well blended. Arrange on greens 1/2 cup salad per person.
Serves 6.

title: mustard sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
It keeps almost indefinitely in a covered jar in refrigerator.

title: amish oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring water and raisins to boil and let set.
This is how you get raisin juice.

title: yellow rice
directions: Bring water to a boil (in a pot).
Drop in bouillon cubes; wait for them to dissolve.
Add the rice.
Add the butter.
Add saffron threads (try to separate them).
Cover pot tightly and reduce flame to simmer.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Garnish with parsley.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Let cream cheese and Cool Whip soften. Mix cream cheese and peanut butter together until smooth. Add powdered sugar. Can add a little milk at this time if needed. Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into crust and chill several hours or overnight.

title: spicy peach salad
directions: Drain peaches, save juice and add it to vinegar and enough water to make 2 cups.
Boil 5 minutes with the spices.
Strain over jello and stir to dissolve.
Chill until thickened.
Add peaches and chill until set.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Spread roll dough on cookie sheet.
Bake crust for 10 minutes at 375°.
Cool.
Mix cheese, dry Ranch dressing and mayonnaise. Spread on crust.
Cool.
Before serving, top with veggies; broccoli, cauliflower, grated carrots, cheese of your choice and black olives (sliced).
Serve, enjoy!

title: pineapple cake(no eggs)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Frost cake with the following frosting.
Refrigerate until serving time and also refrigerate any leftovers.

title: chicken wings
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large container, prefer one with a cover.
Mix together and then add wings to the mixture and let them soak.
Occasionally turn.
It is best to refrigerate overnight.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put batter into greased and floured cake pans.
Best in two 8-inch pans.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican rellenos
directions: Grate cheeses and chop chilies.
Layer a 9 x 13-inch pan starting with cheeses, then chilies, then cheeses, etc.
Then beat eggs, milk and flour and pour over cheese and chilies layers.
Bake at 350° for 45-50 minutes.
Let set for a few minutes before serving.

title: canadian pork meat pie
directions: In a large pan, put ground pork with enough water to cover pork. Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: date squares
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly. Spread half of the mixture into pan. Pour filling on top. Pour remaining mixture on top of filling. Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: rouladen
directions: Cut steak in 2 1/2 to 3-inch lengthwise strips.
Sprinkle chopped onion and diced bacon on each beef strip and roll; close with toothpick.
Season with salt and paprika; roll in a little flour and fry until brown.

title: overnight french toast(serves 6)
directions: Place bread cubes in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
In medium bowl, beat together remaining ingredients until well blended.
Pour over bread and lightly toss until bread is evenly coated.

title: grama's christmas jello
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
When cool, add strawberries and pineapple.
Chill until partially thick; fold in bananas. Pour 1/2 of mixture into 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until firm. Spread sour cream and cream cheese mixture over firm jello; pour remaining jello mixture over sour cream.
Chill until all is firm. Before serving, spread Cool Whip over jello and sprinkle with pecans.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: ricotta pancakes
directions: Mix ingredients in blender.
Add milk if too thick.
Cook on griddle.

title: chicken spaghetti provincial
directions: Simmer tomatoes and 2 cups chicken stock until liquid is reduced by half.
Season with chopped parsley, onion, garlic, Worcestershire, salt, basil and thyme.
Slice and saute fresh or canned mushrooms in butter until golden and drain.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix and form into patties.
Brown in sprayed frypan.
May also be baked in a 1 pound pan, making loaf, approximately 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: southern corn pudding
directions: Grind corn using a medium coarse grinder.
To beaten eggs add flour, salt, sugar and melted butter; mix well.
Next add the milk and ground corn, mixing well.
Pour into a well buttered casserole and bake at 350° until firm, approximately 40 minutes.

title: aunt bessie wilson's chicken and dumplings
directions: Brown chicken.
Cover with hot water and bring to a boil. Lower temperature to low boil stage until chicken is tender. Remove chicken and debone.
Mix flour, egg, chicken fat and enough water until dough does not cling to bowl.
Roll out on wax paper with plenty of flour.
Add to boiling broth, then add chicken. Don't peek until ready to serve.

title: fresh blueberry pie
directions: Mix together; put in a pie crust.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup brown sugar.
Bake at 400°.

title: jello cake
directions: Stir the jello and boiling water for 3 minutes to dissolve jello.
Add the cold water; stir 3 minutes.
Prepare a white cake mix according to box directions and bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Cool.
Using table fork or meat fork, punch holes every 1/2 inch in cake.
Slowly pour jello on top of cake.
Chill 3 to 4 hours. Frost with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: baked beans
directions: Soak lima beans overnight.
Boil approximately 1 1/2 hours with salt pork.
Add other ingredients and bake at 350° for approximately 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: easy yeast rolls
directions: Mix flour, yeast and sugar; beat in water, oil and egg.
Cover bowl; refrigerate until ready to bake.
Grease muffin tins and fill 2/3 full.
Bake at 425° for about 20 to 25 minutes.
Does not have to rise before baking.
Will keep in refrigerator 3 to 4 days.

title: fried apple pie crust
directions: Mix flour and Crisco, then sugar.
Beat eggs; add to cream and mix well.
Mix egg mixture with flour mixture.
Chill overnight or at least 3 hours.
Prepare filling.
Pinch off enough dough to roll out (a little larger than saucer), put filling on 1/2 of crust. Wet edge and fold over other half and press edge together with fork.
Slit top to release air, fry in hot Crisco or oil.
Drain on paper towel.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Mix with the first 3 ingredients.
Add zucchini, vanilla, nuts and raisins; mix well. Pour into bread pans and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate-covered cherries
directions: Pat cherries dry with paper towels; set aside.
In a small mixing bowl, combine the sugar, butter, corn syrup and salt; mix well.
Knead until smooth.
Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Roll into 1/2 inch balls; flatten each into a 2 inch circle.
Wrap each circle around a cherry and lightly roll in hands.
Place cherries with stems up on waxed paper-lined baking sheets.
Cover loosely and refrigerate for 1 hour.
In a microwave or heavy saucepan, melt chocolate chips and shortening; stir until smooth.
Holding onto the stem, dip each cherry into chocolate; set on waxed paper. Refrigerate until hardened.
Store in a covered container. Refrigerate for 1 to 2 weeks before serving.
Yield:
5 dozen.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Cool completely.
This is essential.
Split layers with sewing thread and frost between layers with:

title: scalloped apples
directions: Slice apples and arrange in shallow dish.
Melt butter and add flour, brown sugar, cinnamon and lemon juice.
Stir together and drizzle over apples.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes. Good served as a side dish with pork or chicken.

title: fresh fruit-pudding compote
directions: Pour milk and orange juice into a bowl.
Add pudding mix and beat slowly with hand beater or at lowest speed of mixer for 1 minute.
Add 1 cup of whipped topping and beat 1 minute longer, just until blended.

title: pudding pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Stir pudding mix into corn syrup in medium bowl until blended.
Stir in milk and egg.
Mix in pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 45 minutes or until top is firm and just begins to crack.
Cool 3 hours.
Serve with whipped topping or ice cream.

title: golden french dressing
directions: Measure all ingredients into bottle.
Shake.
Cover tightly and chill.
Makes 2 cups.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Spread bottom of 9 x 9-inch baking dish with pie filling. Sprinkle cake mix over filling.
Drizzle margarine over cake mix and top with nuts.
Bake about 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm with ice cream or whipped cream topping.

title: easy baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place rice in a tightly greased baking dish.
Wash and pat the chicken dry.
Arrange chicken pieces over rice.
In a medium bowl combine remaining ingredients, mixing to blend.
Spoon evenly over chicken.
Cover and bake for 1 hour until done.

title: broiled orange roughy
directions: Use fresh orange roughy or thaw frozen orange roughy.
Rinse fish in cold water; pat dry.
Preheat broiler to 350°.
Place fish in broiler pan.
Sprinkle with lemon pepper, paprika and dill. Crush garlic gloves and spread thinly on top of fish.
Broil for 10 to 15 minutes until fish is crispy on top.
Check for doneness by breaking off edge of fish with fork.
Should break off easily if done.

title: upside-down peach-pineapple cake
directions: Mix pineapple and peach chunks and drain.
Melt butter or margarine in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan in 350° oven.
Sprinkle brown sugar evenly over butter in pan.
Arrange mixed fruit over brown sugar and sprinkle lightly with nutmeg.
Prepare yellow cake mix from your favorite recipe.
Pour batter over fruit in pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until done.
Let cool in pan 4 to 5 minutes, then turn over on serving plate and carefully lift pan off.
Garnish with whipped topping or serve with ice cream.
Eat with a smile.

title: buckaroo beans
directions: You may substitute or add any of your favorite beans (green, pinto, lima or black-eyed peas).

title: raisin cream pie
directions: Cook raisins until done, then blend all ingredients together. Bake in a double crust.

title: meat and bean burrito
directions: Heat turkey, onion, green chilies and picante sauce in a large skillet.
Drain beans and mash with potato masher.
When meat is browned, add beans.
Place mixture in tortilla and fold in sides. Heat in microwave for about 7 to 10 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: jail house rolls
directions: Mix dry yeast in water; blend and set aside.
Mix potatoes, margarine, eggs, salt and sugar; blend into flour.
Add yeast water; blend well.
Place in greased bowl; cover with cold, damp cloth.
Place in icebox until ready for use.
Roll out like pie crust (not as thin); cut in desired size.
Butter tops; let stand for several hours.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: cowboy dip
directions: Cook and drain hamburger and sausage.
Melt Velveeta.
Stir in Ro-Tel and mushroom soup.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: lef cookies - german
directions: Mix all together, then add flour to make stiff.
Roll out 1/4-inch thick and cut with pizza cutter.
Can be doubled.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour all ingredients by layers into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch oblong pan.
Do not mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: party smokies
directions: Mix jelly and mustard into sauce pan. Heat until hot, stirring constantly. Add smokies, let simmer until ready to serve. You can use hot flavored jelly, if you like them hot and spicy.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix oatmeal and boiling water.
Pour over oatmeal.
Let stand while mixing Wesson oil, white sugar, brown sugar, flour, eggs and vanilla.
Then add all together; mix well.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 300°.

title: angela's chocolate chip cookies
directions: By hand or mixer cream brown sugar, sugar, butter flavored Crisco, vanilla and salt.
