Then add baking powder, chocolate chips and flour.
Stir good.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: irish bread
directions: Soak raisins for a few minutes to plump them, then dredge them with 1/4 cup of the flour in the recipe.
Mix all ingredients together with a little bit of love; bake in a greased Bundt pan at 350° about 45 minutes or until well done in the center.
Any good cook will know when that is.

title: grandma's devil's food cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, cocoa, soda and salt.
Add salad dressing, cold water and vanilla.
Mix well and bake in well-greased, floured pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Very good and moist.

title: vidalia onions
directions: Slice onions into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread mushroom soup over onions.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake in 350° oven about 45 minutes or until tender.

title: four egg sponge cake
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Add sugar gradually.
Add cold water and mix thoroughly.
Sift flour before measuring, then sift 4 times with salt, baking powder and cornstarch.
Add eggs and sugar; mix.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites and bake in ungreased tube pan in slow 320° oven for 1 hour.

title: my favorite peanut brittle
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and water to hard boil stage.
Add oleo and peanuts.
Cook, stirring constantly.
Cook until the syrup turns brownish and the peanuts look a little brown.
Set off heat.
Add vanilla and soda and stir the soda in very gently but thoroughly. Pour at once onto a greased cookie sheet.
Let cool well, then break into small pieces.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Mix by hand until well blended.
Grease 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until golden brown on top.
Bake at 325° if using a glass dish.

title: giant blueberry muffins(fat-free)
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Toss blueberries with 2 tablespoons sugar. Set aside.
Stir flour, sugar, baking powder and salt together. Combine Egg Beaters, skim milk and applesauce and add to dry ingredients.
Stir only until ingredients are moistened.
Gently stir blueberries into batter.
Divide evenly into muffin pan sprayed lightly with nonstick spray coating.
Sprinkle top of each muffin with 1/4 teaspoon of sugar.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Let cool about 5 minutes in pan, then remove and cool.
Yield:
6 giant muffins.

title: glazed walnuts
directions: Boil sugar and sour cream until makes a ball. Remove from heat. Add vanilla and walnuts. Pour out onto waxed paper and let cool. Break up in pieces and put in bag to seal.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Grease a 1/2-quart casserole dish with butter.
Cut potatoes in thin slices and put in the bottom of dish.
Salt and pepper. Brown pork chops and put on top.
Pour soup over chops.
Cover; bake at 350° for 1 hour until potatoes are tender.

title: party punch
directions: Makes 1 gallon and 1 quart.

title: drop biscuits
directions: Mix the biscuit mix and milk. Drop by heaping teaspoonful on a greased cookie sheet. bake at 450° about 10 minutes until delicately brown. Serve with freshly made butter and homemade strawberry jam.

title: heavenly divinity fudge
directions: Cook sugar, syrup, salt and water until it forms a soft ball (240°) in cold water.

Take out 1/2 cup of this mixture and cook the rest until it forms a hard ball (250° to 265°) in cold water. On the beaten egg whites pour very slowly the 1/2 cup of liquid that was taken out, beating constantly.
Then all the remainder. Add nuts and vanilla; keep beating until mass thickens and becomes heavy.
Drop from a spoon on greased surface, or pour into a buttered pan and cut when cold.

title: sauteed shrimp pernod with fettuccine
directions: Place raw shrimp in pot and cover with water.
Add salt and boil for 15 minutes.
In another pot, add butter and flour to make a light roux (do not brown).
Add to shrimp, stirring constantly, so that it will be a smooth mixture.
Add all ingredients, except fettuccine and cream, and simmer approximately 15 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Cream margarine, cream cheese and vanilla; add peanut butter and mix until creamy.
Add sugar and mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.
Form into balls.
Melt chocolate pieces over double boiler.
Dip peanut butter balls in chocolate.
Put on wax paper to cool.

title: glazed lemon cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
Mix powdered sugar, lemon juice and oil.
Remove cake from oven and poke holes in cake with a straw or meat fork.
Pour glaze over top of cake.
Cool and enjoy.

title: italian zucchini pie
directions: Cook together zucchini and onion in butter (about 10 minutes until onions are clear).
Stir in all the spices.
After cooking the mixture, combine and add the beaten eggs and the Mozzarella cheese; mix well.
Unroll and press the unbaked dinner rolls into a 10-inch pan, making a pie crust; press in and up sides. Into this unbaked pie crust, pour zucchini mixture.
Bake in a 350° to 375° oven, uncovered, for 25 to 30 minutes, or until browned and hot.

title: perfect apple pie
directions: Core and slice apples.
Add 1 tablespoon lemon juice if apples are not tart.
Combine dry ingredients.
Mix with sliced apples. Prepare 9-inch pastry.
Put in pie pan.
Add apple mixture; dot with butter.
Cover with top crust.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes or until done.

title: green beans basilico
directions: In a large skillet saute garlic, onion and green pepper in margarine
until
soft.
Stir
in
basil, oregano and salt. Toss green
beans
with
the vegetables until beans are bright green. Cover
skillet
and
let vegetables cook for 1 minute. (If beans are
crisp, but tender, they are ready for serving. Otherwise, cook longer.) Serves 6.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook hamburger and drain.
Add seasoning (with water as stated on the package) and cook with hamburger.
Add beans and simmer. Throw in a large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and toss.

title: cheese ball
directions: After
letting the cream cheese set in room temperature for 15 to
minutes, chop the cream cheese completely in a mixing bowl.
Add salt, Worcestershire sauce, onions, peppers and 1
cup of nuts. Mix completely, forming the mixture into a ball.
Spread other
cup
of
nuts
on
waxed
paper and roll cheese ball
in the nuts.
Refrigerate, then serve with crackers.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and egg.
Mix tomato soup with the soda; let dissolve.
Add to mixture; mix well.
Sift flour with next 6 ingredients; mix all together.
Add raisins and walnuts. Bake in Bundt pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: vegetable lentil soup
directions: About 1 1/2 hours before serving: dice carrots, celery and onion, cut potatoes into 1/2-inch pieces and mince garlic.

In 5-quart Dutch oven over medium-high heat, in hot oil, cook carrots, celery and onion until tender, stirring occasionally. Add garlic and cook, stirring just until garlic begins to brown. Stir in stewed tomatoes with their liquid, dry lentils, chicken broth, potatoes and 3 cups water; stir with spoon to break up tomatoes.
Over high heat, heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer for 50 minutes.

title: tropical sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine sweet potatoes with salt, cinnamon, brown sugar, half the pineapple and 2 tablespoons butter. Beat well.
Place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole; spread remaining pineapple with coconut. Bake in moderate oven (375°) until heated through, about 30 minutes.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt margarine in heavy 10-inch skillet.
Sprinkle brown sugar over melted margarine.
Drain juice from pineapple and reserve. Arrange drained fruit and pecans over margarine-sugar coating. Beat until thick and lemon colored the 2 eggs.
Add sugar. Gradually beat in pineapple juice and vanilla.
Beat in flour, baking powder and salt.
Pour batter over pineapple arrangement. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: buckingham palace scones
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place first 4 ingredients in food processor.
Process until mixture is of cornmeal consistency.
Add sugar and raisins; blend mixture briefly.
Do not overmix. Scrape sides of processor if necessary, to balance mixture.
Add egg and milk.
Process quickly.
Mixture should form tight, smooth dough and be slightly moist.

title: blueberry-oatmeal muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Mix wet ingredients.
Combine dry with wet ingredients.
Batter will be lumpy.
Fold in blueberries. Divide evenly in muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: bruffins
directions: Mix together egg and sugar. Add bananas, crushed pineapple and Grape-Nuts cereal. Add Bisquick and salt.
Stir about 25 strokes until blended but not smooth. Fill greased muffin tins. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: pepperoni pizza dip
directions: Beat together cream cheese, sour cream, oregano, garlic powder and red pepper.
Spread evenly in a 9-inch pie plate.
Spread pizza sauce over top.
Sprinkle with pepperoni, onions and pepper. Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Top with cheese and bake 5 minutes more.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: lemon butter sauce
directions: Bring first four ingredients to a boil and reduce until saucepan is almost dry. Add whipping cream; bring to a boil again and reduce by half. Add butter very slowly. Do not let mixture boil or it will separate. Squeeze lemon juice into mixture and keep warm. Serve over baked, broiled or sauteed fish or serve as a dipping sauce for crab legs, lobster or shrimp.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, beat eggs until frothy; add sugar, pumpkin, oil, pie spice and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Add flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and nuts; mix gently to combine.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until cake is golden brown.
Cool one hour before frosting.

title: lazy daisy vegetable casserole
directions: Use a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Layer rice, 1/2 hamburger over rice, potatoes over hamburger, onions over potatoes, carrots over onion and other 1/2 of hamburger over carrots.
Pour stewed tomatoes over all.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: yeast muffins
directions: Combine ingredients in order given, adding flour last.
Batter can be made day before and will keep up to 3 days.
Do not stir down.
Add a little oil in each muffin tin and heat before dropping in batter.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Makes 24 muffins.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Combine chicken and cooked rice.
Add onion.
Add pimentos, water chestnuts and beans.
Combine soup and mayonnaise.
Mix into other ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and beginning to brown.
May be frozen before baking.
Defrost in refrigerator if frozen.

title: cowboy caviar
directions: Mix all but the last 2 ingredients. Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour. Spread cream cheese on a serving plate. Spoon bean mixture evenly over cream cheese. Sprinkle with green onion. Serve with white corn tortilla chips.

title: fresh tomato soup
directions: In a large saucepan, saute onions and garlic in margarine until onions are tender.
Add remaining ingredients except basil; simmer, stirring occasionally, 15 minutes or until slightly thickened.
Remove from heat; cool slightly.
Puree in blender (don't overblend).
Return to saucepan.
Stir in basil; heat gently.

title: sand
directions: Let cream cheese and margarine soften and then cream together with sugar.
Mix dry vanilla pudding and the milk; set aside to thicken.
After the pudding thickens, add to the cream cheese mixture.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Blend the flour, soda and salt together in a small bowl.
In a larger bowl, mix together the remaining ingredients, except nuts and chocolate chips, as listed.
Mix the small bowl of ingredients slowly into the larger bowl.
After mixing the two bowls together, stir in the nuts and chocolate chips.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: squash dressing
directions: Cook bread according to directions.
Crumble.
Place squash, onion and oleo in a skillet and cook until tender.
Mash.
Add beaten egg, soup and bread crumbs.
Mix well.
Put in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix gelatin, water and fruit.
Place in refrigerator until set.

title: cottage cheese jello salad
directions: Dissolve 1 cup boiling water with Jell-O.
Add pineapple juice. Boil 2 minutes.
Add marshmallows.
Boil 1 minute.
Jell until slushy.
Then add pineapple and cottage cheese.
Blend together whipped whipping cream and sugar, then add to Jell-O.
Jell until firm in a pan.

title: holiday orange balls
directions: Mix wafer crumbs, coconut and sugar.
Add orange juice and mix well.
Form into balls and roll in confectioners sugar.
Chill overnight.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook
chicken
breasts	until
tender
in salted water. Remove chicken from broth and cook vermicelli spaghetti, green peppers and
onions
in
broth
and 1 stick butter until done. Remove chicken
from
bones
and add to spaghetti, peppers and onions. Add remaining
ingredients and bake in casserole dish in a 325° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: easy rhubarb cobbler
directions: Place diced fruit in bottom of pan.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: layered banana pineapple dessert
directions: Beat cream cheese in large bowl with wire whisk until smooth. Gradually beat in milk.
Add pudding mixes.
Beat until well blended.
Spread cream cheese mixture over sliced bananas arranged in pie mixture.
Spread whipped topping over pineapple. Refrigerate 3 hours before serving.

title: lottie's cherry squares
directions: In a large bowl, cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs and flour.
Mix in vanilla and extract.
Blend well.
Spread batter into a greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan.
Cut surface of batter into 28 squares.
Spoon filling in center of each square.
During baking, batter puffs up around filling.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Cut squares.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Cool and remove from pan.

title: apple cake
directions: Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon and salt and add to apple mixture.
Mix well.
Stir egg, oil and vanilla into apple mixture. Add pecans.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: graham cracker crust
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended. Press into a 9 inch pie plate. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Melt butter; mix with sugar, flour, eggs, vanilla and nuts. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Just before cake is done, sprinkle marshmallows on top, then ice cake with chocolate icing.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Spread chicken breasts flat; fold cheese and ham slices to fit on top; fold breasts over filling and fasten edges with toothpicks.
On waxed paper, mix flour and paprika; use mixture to coat chicken pieces.
In a 12-inch skillet over medium heat, in hot butter or margarine, cook chicken until browned on all sides. Add wine and bouillon.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 30 minutes or until fork-tender.
Remove the toothpicks.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, mixing well.
Add buttermilk, melted margarine, lemon extract, vanilla and salt.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: frozen applesauce
directions: Whip egg whites and fold in fruit.
Flavor with lemon or pineapple, etc.
Freeze.

title: meat cabbage casserole
directions: In a medium skillet, saute onion in butter until soft, but not brown.
Add ground meat.
Cook, breaking up the meat until meat loses its pink color.
In a 2-quart buttered casserole or baking dish, layer carrots and 1/2 cabbage.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add meat mixture; press down slightly.
Add remaining cabbage.

title: "real" boston baked beans
directions: Saute cut up bacon on medium heat until 1/2 cooked (about 3 minutes).
Add onion and continue cooking until onions are translucent and bacon is almost brown.
Drain and reserve cooking fat.
Add beans (drain as much as possible so that most of tomato juice is out of can).
Add all other ingredients and combine until mixed.
Be careful not to mash up beans.
Add reserved bacon drippings and mix.
Cook in preheated oven at 400° for 45 to 60 minutes until brown and bubbling.
You can add cooked cut up hot dogs if wanted.
Serves 4 to 6 adults.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour oblong pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches or 2 round layer pans or 8 or 9 x 1 1/2-inches.
Beat all ingredients in large mixer bowl on low speed, scraping bowl constantly, 30 seconds.
Beat on high speed, scraping bowl occasionally, 3 minutes.
Pour into pan(s).

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook until clear and thick.
Add dry strawberry Jell-O and 3 drops red food coloring.
Stir and let cool.

title: breakfast bread
directions: Measure corn flakes.
Crush to 3/4 cup.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
Measure margarine and sugar into large mixing bowl.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and orange peel.
Beat well.
Stir in orange juice.
Add dry ingredients, mixing only until combined.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Spread in well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in oven at 350° for about 50 minutes or until wooden pick inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool about 10 minutes before removing from pan.
Cool completely before slicing.
Yield:
1 loaf.

title: lasagna
directions: Mix cottage cheese and Ricotta cheese together.
Combine browned hamburger and spaghetti sauce.
Spread cup of sauce in 9 x 13-inch pan; layer 1/2 each of noodles, "uncooked" cheese mixture, Mozzarella and sauce.
Repeat."
Pour water around sides.
Cover tightly with foil, bake 1 hour at 350°.
Remove foil, bake 15 minutes longer.
Let stand 20 minutes before serving.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Chop celery and onion, add to melted margarine and cook until almost done. Combine all ingredients in a large bowl, add broth to mix. Put in a greased pan. 13 x 9 inch pan will make thick dressing, use cookie sheet pan for thinner dressing. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until top is brown. Do not over bake or dressing will not be moist.

title: ham and pimiento spread
directions: Combine all ingredients; stir well. Chill. Serve on party rye bread or crackers. Yields about 3 cups.

title: chicken italiano
directions: Spray skillet with Pam.
Heat skillet, add chicken and brown. Add stewed tomatoes and Italian seasoning.
Cover and simmer until chicken is tender.
Stir frequently to prevent sticking.
Good served with pasta.

title: rumaki
directions: Wrap each water chestnut with a liver, then with bacon. Secure with a toothpick.
Fry in deep fat until bacon is crisp. Serve hot, with the dry mustard.
Mix with water to moisten on the side.

title: better than pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Reserve 1 cup of the cake mix.
Melt 1/2 cup of the margarine and mix with remaining cake mix and 1 egg.
Spread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch greased Pyrex dish.
Mix together brown sugar, milk, cinnamon, 3 eggs and pumpkin.
Pour over cake mix layer.
Combine the reserved cake mix, 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup softened margarine.
Crumble over second layer and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve with whipped cream. Refrigerate.

title: dill vegetable dip
directions: Mix well; chill and serve with fresh vegetables.

title: chicken and macaroni casserole
directions: Boil chicken; debone and cut into small pieces.
Mix together all ingredients.
Pour into large casserole dish.
Cook in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: apple puffs
directions: Pour lemon juice over apples and let stand a while.
Beat eggs and combine remaining ingredients with apples.
(Batter will be thin.)
Drop by spoonfuls in hot fat like doughnuts.
Roll in 10x sugar.

title: easter egg dye
directions: For each color desired for dyeing, measure food color, water and vinegar into a small bowl; mix well with a spoon.
Leave the spoon in the bowl, so the colors don't get mixed together from one bowl to another.

title: mulled cider
directions: Combine all ingredients in order listed.
Heat to boiling and simmer 15 minutes.
Allow to stand for 12 hours or overnight. Strain and serve hot.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Melt butter in a large pizza pan.
Add flour and sugar (and nuts) to butter.
Mix well with a fork.
Spread dough in pan with fingers to form crust.
Make a slight ridge around edge.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Let cool.

title: "mock" lobster tail
directions: Bring to boil and simmer 20 minutes.

title: low country boil
directions: Fill container with water.
Add crab boil.
Bring to boil. Add potatoes, let boil, cook 10 minutes.
Add sausage and shrimp, cook 3 to 5 minutes or until shrimp turns pink.
Remove with slotted spoon.
Serve with cocktail sauce.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine and 1 egg in a medium bowl with mixer until doughy. Press in greased 9 x 13 glass dish. Beat 3 eggs and add box confectioners sugar and softened cream cheese. Pour and spread over dough. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Cool. Sprinkle reserved sugar on top. Cut into squares to serve.

title: corn flake candy
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler. Mix cereal into melted chocolate.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Let sit until set. Store in airtight tins or plastic containers.

title: easy barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook over low heat for 5 minutes.

title: scalloped apples
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Pare, core and slice apples.
Place in buttered shallow casserole dish.
Mix next 5 ingredients and pour over apples.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: country steak
directions: Pound steak; cut into serving size pieces.
In skillet, brown steak in shortening; pour off fat.
Stir in soup and water.
Cover and simmer 1-1/2 hours or until done.
Stir often.

title: easy banana muffins
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add bananas and Bisquick. Mix until blended.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into muffin tins.
Bake at 350° about 20 minutes.

title: nut cookie crust
directions: Mix margarine and brown sugar in large bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients just until crumbly.
Press mixture against bottom and side of ungreased Foley pie pan, 9 x 1 1/2-inches, building up 1/2-inch edge; flute if desired.

title: cranberry coffee cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add almond extract.
Alternately add flour and sour cream.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Blop cranberry sauce on top and knead lightly.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: tortoni cups(italy)
directions: Stir together all ingredients.
Put into 10 individual cupcake papers in a muffin pan.
Freeze until firm.
Top each with a maraschino cherry flower.

title: coconut-pecan filling and frosting
directions: Mix milk, sugar, margarine, egg yolks and vanilla in a large saucepan. Cook and stir on medium heat about 12 minutes or until thickened and golden brown. Remove from heat. Stir in coconut and pecans. Cool to room temperature and of spreading consistency. Makes about 4 1/2 cups.

title: fillet of sole with oyster sauce
directions: Separate fillets; arrange in 1 1/2-quart utility dish.
Blend together the oyster stew, mushrooms and salt.
Pour over fillets; sprinkle paprika as desired.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Cook in Radarange oven, covered, on Full power for 5 to 7 minutes, or until flakes easily with fork.

title: cora's cheese crackers
directions: Mix.
Roll thin on a cookie sheet dusted with flour.
Mark into bars.
Bake at 400°, watching closely.
May sprinkle with sesame or poppy seed, rolling it in.

title: lemon glazed carrots(microwave)
directions: In 1-quart microwave-proof casserole dish, combine carrots and water.
Cover; cook 6 minutes.
Stir in green pepper.
Cover and cook 12 to 15 minutes, or until carrots are tender.
Stir once during cooking time.
Drain.

title: miracle custard pie
directions: In blender, combine milk, eggs, flour, margarine, vanilla and salt.
Blend about 10 seconds.
Do not overblend.
Stir in coconut.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle a little ground nutmeg on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean. Allow to cool, then chill in refrigerator for at least 3 hours. This pie makes its own crust.

title: homemade no ham lentil soup
directions: In large kettle, saute onions and garlic until onions are pearly.
Add all other ingredients to kettle.
Add water to cover about 1-inch above ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, stirring frequently, for 2 hours.
Soup will thicken dramatically.
You may have to add more water to your liking.
Soup is done when lentils are tender.

title: crispy corn dogs
directions: You will need 10 wooden skewers.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt margarine.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Remove from oven and immediately cover with miniature marshmallows, then cover with frosting.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix together coconut and pecans.
Spread in bottom of pan. Prepare cake mix as directed on the package.
Pour over nuts and coconut mixture.
Mix cream cheese, margarine and sugar together until well blended.
Place mixture on top of cake by teaspoonfuls. Bake for 45 minutes.
Cake will be shaky, but it will set up as it cools.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti twists according to directions.
Drain.
Put in large bowl and add bottled dressing, Good Seasons pack of dressing, green pepper, tomato and onion.
Stir well.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: orange juice cookies(easy and no bake)
directions: Mix in order, except coconut.
Shape in small balls and roll in coconut.
Keep in tight containers.

title: cheese straws
directions: Let cheese and butter stand out of refrigerator until softened overnight.
Grate cheese fine.
Cream cheese and butter well. Add flour, salt, pepper and baking powder.
Dough should be firm enough to handle.
Roll in rolls to run through press.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
(Can roll into a roll, refrigerate and then slice and bake if you don't have a press.)

title: glazed doughnuts
directions: Mix together yeast, 1 teaspoon sugar and warm water.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and let rise until double.
Roll out, cut as desired and let rise again.
Deep fat fry and glaze.
Glaze made with powdered sugar moistened with boiling water.

title: jalapeno pepper corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 8.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients except the potatoes; mix well.
Place potatoes in a greased casserole.
Pour mixture over potatoes. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: pecan bread
directions: Sift flour.
Take out 1 tablespoon flour to dredge pecans. Add salt, baking soda and sugar.
Sift again; beat eggs and add to dry ingredients.
Add milk gradually.
Add shortening or butter. Add nuts.
Bake in well-greased pan at 350° for 1 hour or until well done.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit and mix juice with pudding.
Whisk.
Add fruit. Mix all together well.
Refrigerate.

title: date and nut rolls
directions: Chill in icebox.
Divide batter into 2 parts.
Roll and spread with date and nut mixture.
Store in icebox overnight.
Slice and bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: In medium bowl, combine ground beef, soup mix, water and stuffing mix.
Blend well.
Press into an 8 x 4-inch microwaveproof dish.
Top with wax paper.
Microwave on High 10 minutes, rotating dish once.
Drain off dishes.
Combine ketchup, brown sugar and mustard.
Spoon over meat loaf.
Microwave uncovered 3 to 4 minutes or until loaf is cooked in center (test with knife).
Let stand a few minutes before serving.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Drain liquid from pineapple and blueberries.
Save liquid. Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water. Add enough water to reserved liquid to make 1 3/4 cups liquid.
Add to jello.
Fold in pineapple and blueberries.
Refrigerate until set in a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: frito pie
directions: Heat chili in pan. Put Fritos in bowl. Cover with chili. Sprinkle with cheese.

title: "tea" time tassies
directions: Mix with fork, take in hand and keep dividing until you have 24 small balls.
Spread balls in small tassie pans.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Mix chicken, potatoes, soup, Veg-All and 1/2 cup milk in large greased casserole. Bake at 400° until bubbly.
Mix biscuit mix with 3/4 cup milk.
Beat with fork until well blended.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on top of bubbly chicken mixture.
Bake covered 15 minutes.
Bake uncovered another 15 minutes until golden brown.

title: crab cheese puffs
directions: Place margarine, mayonnaise, garlic salt and cheese together. Gently stir in crab meat.
Spread mixture evenly over English muffins.
Cut each muffin half into quarters (4 wedges).
Place on cookie sheet.
Broil muffins until lightly browned on top.
Serve hot. (Can be frozen up to 3 months.)
Freeze uncooked; broil before serving.

title: fruited stuffed pork chops
directions: Saute onion and celery in 1/4 cup butter until tender; remove from heat.
Add stuffing mix, mixed dried fruit and raisins; stir well and set aside.

title: buffet potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and cut as for French fries.
Place in center of large piece of aluminum foil (use double thickness or heavy-duty). Shape foil to form baking dish.
Dot potatoes with margarine; sprinkle with salt and pepper, parsley and cheese.
Pour cream over.

title: bride's happiness cake
directions: Mix all ingredients with a pint of sympathy and understanding combined.
Flavor with loving companionship.
Bake well all your life.
Frost with kisses, fond hopes and tender words.
This cake keeps well and should be served often.

title: circus peanut salad
directions: Dissolve jell-O in boiling water.
Stir in circus peanuts, stirring until almost dissolved.
Add cold water.
Allow to set until syrupy or partially set.
Using an electric mixer, beat in Cool Whip until smooth and fluffy.
Pour into large Pyrex dish and chill.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces and stir-fry.
Break spaghetti into short pieces and cook.
Drain and set aside. Saute onion and celery until soft.
Add chicken stock, soup, cheese, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Add spaghetti to mixture and let stand 1 hour.
Add chicken to spaghetti mixture and mix well.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch casserole 30 minutes at 350°.

title: egg in hole
directions: This is from my grandmother's book, "Domestic Cookery," printed in 1951.

title: corn casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 11-inch pan.
Combine first 4 ingredients.
Pour butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fish pudding
directions: Bake fish with a little seasoning; bone and flake.
Place in a bowl and add eggs, mixing well.
Add milk and half the butter. Add half the cracker crumbs, parsley, onion, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Mix, then place in buttered baking dish.
Top with remaining cracker crumbs and butter.
Place baking dish in pan of hot water and bake at 325° for about 50 minutes.
Serve with tartar sauce.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: hardee's biscuits
directions: Place
all
ingredients
in mixing bowl, except buttermilk. Gradually
add
buttermilk.
Mix
with
hand
or spoon. Roll dough out on board and cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake at 450° to 475° for 11 to 12 minutes.

title: beef roast with vegetables
directions: Cook roast in roaster pan at 325° for 1 hour.
Then add all other ingredients in pan.
Cook for 30 minutes.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Drain kidney and pinto beans.
Lightly brown bacon and onion in a skillet.
Combine with rest of ingredients and pour into a buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 5 minutes longer.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Brown onion in butter; combine with soup, broth and chilies. Add chicken to soup mixture; heat well.
In a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish, place a layer of tortillas, a layer of chicken and a layer of cheese.
Repeat the layers until casserole is filled. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: swedish pancakes
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add milk and dry ingredients.
Add melted butter.
Use mixer to mix batter.
Fry on hot greased pan.

title: spaghetti sauce(to can)
directions: Peel tomatoes and cut up.
Cook down.
Can leave chunky or strain juice (2 to 2 1/2 gallons).
Chop other ingredients and cook with tomato juice for 1 1/2 hours.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook 45 minutes.
Put in jars in a boiling water bath just until boiling.

title: apple milk
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Cover and blend for 15 seconds at high speed.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking dish, melt 1/2 stick margarine.
Pour in apples and spread evenly.
Sprinkle with cinnamon to your liking.
Melt 1/2 cup peanut butter and drizzle over apples.
Mix oats, Bisquick and brown sugar.
Melt remaining margarine and pour over mixture.
This makes the topping and it should be moist and a bit crumbly.
Sprinkle over and bake for 20 minutes.

title: georgia peach cobbler
directions: Combine peaches, sugar, flour and nutmeg in a Dutch oven; set aside to allow syrup to form (15 to 20 minutes).
Bring peach mixture to boil; reduce heat to low and simmer 10 minutes or until peaches are tender.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla and margarine.
Roll half of pastry to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut to fit a 2-quart baking dish.
Spoon half of peach mixture into lightly buttered baking dish; top with pastry.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O in boiling water until dissolved.
Pour in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Cool; add strawberry while they are still frozen.

title: gingered vegetables
directions: In 10-inch skillet or wok over high heat in hot oil, stir-fry carrots, celery, red pepper and onion for 3 minutes.
Add broccoli, snow peas, garlic and ginger.
Sprinkle cornstarch over vegetables. Add broth.
Cook until mixture boils and thickens, stirring often. Serve over rice with soy sauce if desired.
Makes 4 cups or 4 to 6 servings.

title: creamed chicken
directions: For easy mixing, divide recipe.
Melt 1 1/2 cups margarine. Add 1 cup flour.
Cook 3 minutes.
Stir in 1 quart chicken broth and 1 1/2 quarts milk.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Continue with next batch of cream sauce. When finished, pour all into electric roaster and add chicken. Heat.
Serve over biscuits, potatoes or waffles.
Serves 85.

title: barbecued hot dogs
directions: Simmer the first 6 ingredients for 5 minutes.
Put the hot dogs in baking dish.
Pour sauce over hot dogs.
Bake for 20 minutes at 325°.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until done and boil eggs for 10 minutes on high. Dice pickles and onion.
Mix these ingredients together; add the rest of ingredients.
Mix well and put in refrigerator.
Can chill for 2 hours.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt margarine in 2-quart casserole.
Add all other ingredients (do not drain corn).
Stir all together and bake 30 to 45 minutes or until browned on top at 350°.

title: onion rings
directions: Slice onions; coat with flour.
Dip into batter.
Heat oil to 375°.
Fry onion rings until golden brown.
May also use other vegetables.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well in an extra large bowl.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: corn pups
directions: Cut wieners into thirds.
Dip into cornbread mixture and deep fry.
May add minced onions to cornbread mixture.
Serves house full of young'uns.
Serve with ketchup/mustard dip.

title: strawberry and pretzel salad
directions: Crush pretzels to chopped nut size. Spread in 8 x 11-inch pan. Pour melted butter over pretzels. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: sausage ball
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine ingredients, mixing thoroughly. Shape into small bite size balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: indian cookies
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients; place on high heat until it begins to boil well, then turn to medium heat and time for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat at once.
Add the vanilla and oatmeal, then stir and add the chopped nuts.
Blend well; drop onto waxed paper by teaspoons.

title: cabbage and potato bake
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Rinse cabbage under cold running water and remove the tough outer leaves.
Cut the cabbage into quarters and remove the hard core.
Cut the cabbage quarters into halves and place, rounded side down, in a roasting pan.
Cut the potatoes in half crosswise and peel.
Cut the peeled potato halves into quarters and arrange in roasting pan, alternating with cabbage pieces.
Fry bacon in a heavy medium skillet for 7 minutes.
Add the sliced onions, salt and pepper to the pan and cook until onions are soft, about 5 minutes.
Evenly distribute the bacon mixture and pan drippings over the vegetables.
Pour chicken stock on top.
Tightly cover the pan with aluminum foil and bake for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove the pan from the oven and allow to sit, covered, for 15 minutes before serving.
Serve the vegetables with the bacon and broth spooned over them.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Mix sugars, butter and oil together.
Add eggs and beat well. Sift dry ingredients together and add to mixture.
Add vanilla.

title: baked beans and more
directions: Fry bacon and hamburger. Drain off fat. Combine all ingredients in crock-pot.
Simmer for 3 hours on medium heat.

title: mexican salsa
directions: Dice all vegetables, then drain liquid.
Add tomato sauce. Stir and refrigerate.

title: fresh blueberry cobbler
directions: *If using self-rising flour, omit baking powder and salt.

title: brownies
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Melt butter with chocolate in top of a double boiler over hot water.
Beat the sugar into eggs.
Slowly beat in chocolate mixture.
Stir in vanilla.
Sift in flour, 2 tablespoons at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in salt, sour cream and walnuts.
Pour into a greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake 30 minutes.
(Be careful not to overcook; brownies should be moist.)
Cool and cut into 20 squares.

title: heartland energy bars
directions: Melt margarine, peanut butter and marshmallows.
Combine oats, Rice Krispies, raisins and peanuts in large bowl.
Pour marshmallow mixture over dry ingredients and mix well with wooden spoon.
Press mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
While warm, cut into bars; chill.
Makes 24 bars.

title: nacho popcorn
directions: In a saucepan melt the margarine.
Stir the paprika, red pepper and cumin into the margarine.
Let cool for 5 minutes. Place popped corn in large bowl.
Pour spice mixture on top. Sprinkle with cheese.
Toss until popped corn is coated.

title: party meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients and shape into balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Drain well.

title: peanut butter logs
directions: In mixing bowl, blend together peanut butter and margarine. Stir in confectioners sugar.
Add cereal, mixing well with hands, crushing slightly.
Shape into 3 logs.
On waxed paper, roll logs in chopped peanuts, pressing into logs slightly.
Wrap in foil or plastic wrap and chill or freeze.
Slice to serve.
Makes 1 pound. Good, easy and nutritious!

title: cherry fluff
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 20 minutes at 350°.
Let cool completely.
Spread with Dream Whip, then with cherry pie filling. Chill to set before serving.
Makes 15 to 20 servings.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.
Prepare several days in advance. Serve with radishes, cauliflower, celery or carrots.

title: reid's incredible chocolate chippers
directions: Cream shortening, butter, brown sugar and granulated sugar together in large bowl.
Beat eggs and vanilla into mixture. Combine flour, baking soda and salt in medium bowl.
Stir dry ingredients gradually into creamed mixture and add nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375°
for 8 to 10 minutes for
7 dozen cookies.

title: hot rolls
directions: Mix flour and 1/2 cup sugar.
Mix together.
Cut in Crisco. Set aside and let rise.
Combine yeast, lukewarm water and 1 teaspoon sugar.
Put yeast and buttermilk in.
Mix and put in greased bowl and turn.
Punch down once a day.
Will keep up to 30 days.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Add boiling water to oatmeal, molasses, salt and butter.
Let stand a few minutes.
Add 2 cups of flour and yeast dissolved in 1/4 cup warm water.
Beat until well mixed.
Add about 3 cups more flour to make a stiff dough.
Knead well on floured board.
Place in greased bowl and let rise until doubled.
Knead again; form into 2 loaves and place in two 8 x 4-inch bread pans.
Allow to rise again.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add strawberries (thawed). Add pineapple and bananas.
Pour half of mixture into mold.
Let sit in refrigerator until set.
Spread on sour cream, then add remaining mixture.

title: orange punch
directions: In a punch bowl, combine the juice, soda and orange drink. Stir in ginger ale. Top with scoops of sherbet and serve.

title: rhubarb mold
directions: Simmer rhubarb chunks in small amount of water until tender. Sweeten to taste.
Mix Key lime with small amount of cold water and add, stirring.
Add cornstarch and cold water until mixture gets very thick.
Put in mold and chill.
Makes a wonderful spread for lunch on bread or use as a condiment.

title: pork chow mein
directions: Melt shortening.
Brown meat.
Reduce heat.
Add salt, pepper and water.
Cover.
Cook 25 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients except cornstarch.
Cover and cook 10 minutes.
Thicken with cornstarch and water paste.
Serve over chow mein noodles and rice.
Delicious.
